2841static inline void ixgbe_irq_enable_queues(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
2842 u64 qmask)
2843{
2844 u32 mask;
2845 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2846
2847 switch (hw->mac.type) {
2848 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
2849 mask = (IXGBE_EIMS_RTX_QUEUE & qmask);
2850 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIMS, mask);
2851 break;
2852 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
2853 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
2854 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
2855 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
2856 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
2857 mask = (qmask & 0xFFFFFFFF);
2858 if (mask)
2859 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIMS_EX(0), mask);
2860 mask = (qmask >> 32);
2861 if (mask)
2862 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIMS_EX(1), mask);
2863 break;
2864 default:
2865 break;
2866 }
2867 /* skip the flush */
2868}
2869
2870static inline void ixgbe_irq_disable_queues(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
2871 u64 qmask)
2872{
2873 u32 mask;
2874 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2875
2876 switch (hw->mac.type) {
2877 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
2878 mask = (IXGBE_EIMS_RTX_QUEUE & qmask);
2879 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIMC, mask);
2880 break;
2881 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
2882 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
2883 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
2884 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
2885 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
2886 mask = (qmask & 0xFFFFFFFF);
2887 if (mask)
2888 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIMC_EX(0), mask);
2889 mask = (qmask >> 32);
2890 if (mask)
2891 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIMC_EX(1), mask);
2892 break;
2893 default:
2894 break;
2895 }
2896 /* skip the flush */
2897}
2898
2899/**
2900 * ixgbe_irq_enable - Enable default interrupt generation settings
2901 * @adapter: board private structure
2902 **/
2903static inline void ixgbe_irq_enable(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter, bool queues,
2904 bool flush)
2905{
2906 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2907 u32 mask = (IXGBE_EIMS_ENABLE_MASK & ~IXGBE_EIMS_RTX_QUEUE);
2908
2909 /* don't reenable LSC while waiting for link */
2910 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE)
2911 mask &= ~IXGBE_EIMS_LSC;
2912
2913 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_TEMP_SENSOR_CAPABLE)
2914 switch (adapter->hw.mac.type) {
2915 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
2916 mask |= IXGBE_EIMS_GPI_SDP0(hw);
2917 break;
2918 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
2919 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
2920 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
2921 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
2922 mask |= IXGBE_EIMS_TS;
2923 break;
2924 default:
2925 break;
2926 }
2927 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FAN_FAIL_CAPABLE)
2928 mask |= IXGBE_EIMS_GPI_SDP1(hw);
2929 switch (adapter->hw.mac.type) {
2930 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
2931 mask |= IXGBE_EIMS_GPI_SDP1(hw);
2932 mask |= IXGBE_EIMS_GPI_SDP2(hw);
2933 /* fall through */
2934 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
2935 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
2936 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
2937 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
2938 if (adapter->hw.device_id == IXGBE_DEV_ID_X550EM_X_SFP ||
2939 adapter->hw.device_id == IXGBE_DEV_ID_X550EM_A_SFP ||
2940 adapter->hw.device_id == IXGBE_DEV_ID_X550EM_A_SFP_N)
2941 mask |= IXGBE_EIMS_GPI_SDP0(&adapter->hw);
2942 if (adapter->hw.phy.type == ixgbe_phy_x550em_ext_t)
2943 mask |= IXGBE_EICR_GPI_SDP0_X540;
2944 mask |= IXGBE_EIMS_ECC;
2945 mask |= IXGBE_EIMS_MAILBOX;
2946 break;
2947 default:
2948 break;
2949 }
2950
2951 if ((adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_HASH_CAPABLE) &&
2952 !(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_FDIR_REQUIRES_REINIT))
2953 mask |= IXGBE_EIMS_FLOW_DIR;
2954
2955 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_EIMS, mask);
2956 if (queues)
2957 ixgbe_irq_enable_queues(adapter, ~0);
2958 if (flush)
2959 IXGBE_WRITE_FLUSH(&adapter->hw);
2960}
2961
2962static irqreturn_t ixgbe_msix_other(int irq, void *data)
2963{
2964 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = data;
2965 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2966 u32 eicr;
2967
2968 /*
2969 * Workaround for Silicon errata. Use clear-by-write instead
2970 * of clear-by-read. Reading with EICS will return the
2971 * interrupt causes without clearing, which later be done
2972 * with the write to EICR.
2973 */
2974 eicr = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_EICS);
2975
2976 /* The lower 16bits of the EICR register are for the queue interrupts
2977 * which should be masked here in order to not accidentally clear them if
2978 * the bits are high when ixgbe_msix_other is called. There is a race
2979 * condition otherwise which results in possible performance loss
2980 * especially if the ixgbe_msix_other interrupt is triggering
2981 * consistently (as it would when PPS is turned on for the X540 device)
2982 */
2983 eicr &= 0xFFFF0000;
2984
2985 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EICR, eicr);
2986
2987 if (eicr & IXGBE_EICR_LSC)
2988 ixgbe_check_lsc(adapter);
2989
2990 if (eicr & IXGBE_EICR_MAILBOX)
2991 ixgbe_msg_task(adapter);
2992
2993 switch (hw->mac.type) {
2994 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
2995 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
2996 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
2997 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
2998 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
2999 if (hw->phy.type == ixgbe_phy_x550em_ext_t &&
3000 (eicr & IXGBE_EICR_GPI_SDP0_X540)) {
3001 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_PHY_INTERRUPT;
3002 ixgbe_service_event_schedule(adapter);
3003 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EICR,
3004 IXGBE_EICR_GPI_SDP0_X540);
3005 }
3006 if (eicr & IXGBE_EICR_ECC) {
3007 e_info(link, "Received ECC Err, initiating reset\n");
3008 set_bit(__IXGBE_RESET_REQUESTED, &adapter->state);
3009 ixgbe_service_event_schedule(adapter);
3010 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EICR, IXGBE_EICR_ECC);
3011 }
3012 /* Handle Flow Director Full threshold interrupt */
3013 if (eicr & IXGBE_EICR_FLOW_DIR) {
3014 int reinit_count = 0;
3015 int i;
3016 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++) {
3017 struct ixgbe_ring *ring = adapter->tx_ring[i];
3018 if (test_and_clear_bit(__IXGBE_TX_FDIR_INIT_DONE,
3019 &ring->state))
3020 reinit_count++;
3021 }
3022 if (reinit_count) {
3023 /* no more flow director interrupts until after init */
3024 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIMC, IXGBE_EIMC_FLOW_DIR);
3025 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_FDIR_REQUIRES_REINIT;
3026 ixgbe_service_event_schedule(adapter);
3027 }
3028 }
3029 ixgbe_check_sfp_event(adapter, eicr);
3030 ixgbe_check_overtemp_event(adapter, eicr);
3031 break;
3032 default:
3033 break;
3034 }
3035
3036 ixgbe_check_fan_failure(adapter, eicr);
3037
3038 if (unlikely(eicr & IXGBE_EICR_TIMESYNC))
3039 ixgbe_ptp_check_pps_event(adapter);
3040
3041 /* re-enable the original interrupt state, no lsc, no queues */
3042 if (!test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state))
3043 ixgbe_irq_enable(adapter, false, false);
3044
3045 return IRQ_HANDLED;
3046}
3047
3048static irqreturn_t ixgbe_msix_clean_rings(int irq, void *data)
3049{
3050 struct ixgbe_q_vector *q_vector = data;
3051
3052 /* EIAM disabled interrupts (on this vector) for us */
3053
3054 if (q_vector->rx.ring || q_vector->tx.ring)
3055 napi_schedule_irqoff(&q_vector->napi);
3056
3057 return IRQ_HANDLED;
3058}
3059
3060/**
3061 * ixgbe_poll - NAPI Rx polling callback
3062 * @napi: structure for representing this polling device
3063 * @budget: how many packets driver is allowed to clean
3064 *
3065 * This function is used for legacy and MSI, NAPI mode
3066 **/
3067int ixgbe_poll(struct napi_struct *napi, int budget)
3068{
3069 struct ixgbe_q_vector *q_vector =
3070 container_of(napi, struct ixgbe_q_vector, napi);
3071 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = q_vector->adapter;
3072 struct ixgbe_ring *ring;
3073 int per_ring_budget, work_done = 0;
3074 bool clean_complete = true;
3075
3076#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA
3077 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED)
3078 ixgbe_update_dca(q_vector);
3079#endif
3080
3081 ixgbe_for_each_ring(ring, q_vector->tx) {
3082 if (!ixgbe_clean_tx_irq(q_vector, ring, budget))
3083 clean_complete = false;
3084 }
3085
3086 /* Exit if we are called by netpoll */
3087 if (budget <= 0)
3088 return budget;
3089
3090 /* attempt to distribute budget to each queue fairly, but don't allow
3091 * the budget to go below 1 because we'll exit polling */
3092 if (q_vector->rx.count > 1)
3093 per_ring_budget = max(budget/q_vector->rx.count, 1);
3094 else
3095 per_ring_budget = budget;
3096
3097 ixgbe_for_each_ring(ring, q_vector->rx) {
3098 int cleaned = ixgbe_clean_rx_irq(q_vector, ring,
3099 per_ring_budget);
3100
3101 work_done += cleaned;
3102 if (cleaned >= per_ring_budget)
3103 clean_complete = false;
3104 }
3105
3106 /* If all work not completed, return budget and keep polling */
3107 if (!clean_complete)
3108 return budget;
3109
3110 /* all work done, exit the polling mode */
3111 napi_complete_done(napi, work_done);
3112 if (adapter->rx_itr_setting & 1)
3113 ixgbe_set_itr(q_vector);
3114 if (!test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state))
3115 ixgbe_irq_enable_queues(adapter, BIT_ULL(q_vector->v_idx));
3116
3117 return min(work_done, budget - 1);
3118}
3119
3120/**
3121 * ixgbe_request_msix_irqs - Initialize MSI-X interrupts
3122 * @adapter: board private structure
3123 *
3124 * ixgbe_request_msix_irqs allocates MSI-X vectors and requests
3125 * interrupts from the kernel.
3126 **/
3127static int ixgbe_request_msix_irqs(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3128{
3129 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
3130 unsigned int ri = 0, ti = 0;
3131 int vector, err;
3132
3133 for (vector = 0; vector < adapter->num_q_vectors; vector++) {
3134 struct ixgbe_q_vector *q_vector = adapter->q_vector[vector];
3135 struct msix_entry *entry = &adapter->msix_entries[vector];
3136
3137 if (q_vector->tx.ring && q_vector->rx.ring) {
3138 snprintf(q_vector->name, sizeof(q_vector->name),
3139 "%s-TxRx-%u", netdev->name, ri++);
3140 ti++;
3141 } else if (q_vector->rx.ring) {
3142 snprintf(q_vector->name, sizeof(q_vector->name),
3143 "%s-rx-%u", netdev->name, ri++);
3144 } else if (q_vector->tx.ring) {
3145 snprintf(q_vector->name, sizeof(q_vector->name),
3146 "%s-tx-%u", netdev->name, ti++);
3147 } else {
3148 /* skip this unused q_vector */
3149 continue;
3150 }
3151 err = request_irq(entry->vector, &ixgbe_msix_clean_rings, 0,
3152 q_vector->name, q_vector);
3153 if (err) {
3154 e_err(probe, "request_irq failed for MSIX interrupt "
3155 "Error: %d\n", err);
3156 goto free_queue_irqs;
3157 }
3158 /* If Flow Director is enabled, set interrupt affinity */
3159 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_HASH_CAPABLE) {
3160 /* assign the mask for this irq */
3161 irq_set_affinity_hint(entry->vector,
3162 &q_vector->affinity_mask);
3163 }
3164 }
3165
3166 err = request_irq(adapter->msix_entries[vector].vector,
3167 ixgbe_msix_other, 0, netdev->name, adapter);
3168 if (err) {
3169 e_err(probe, "request_irq for msix_other failed: %d\n", err);
3170 goto free_queue_irqs;
3171 }
3172
3173 return 0;
3174
3175free_queue_irqs:
3176 while (vector) {
3177 vector--;
3178 irq_set_affinity_hint(adapter->msix_entries[vector].vector,
3179 NULL);
3180 free_irq(adapter->msix_entries[vector].vector,
3181 adapter->q_vector[vector]);
3182 }
3183 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED;
3184 pci_disable_msix(adapter->pdev);
3185 kfree(adapter->msix_entries);
3186 adapter->msix_entries = NULL;
3187 return err;
3188}
3189
3190/**
3191 * ixgbe_intr - legacy mode Interrupt Handler
3192 * @irq: interrupt number
3193 * @data: pointer to a network interface device structure
3194 **/
3195static irqreturn_t ixgbe_intr(int irq, void *data)
3196{
3197 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = data;
3198 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3199 struct ixgbe_q_vector *q_vector = adapter->q_vector[0];
3200 u32 eicr;
3201
3202 /*
3203 * Workaround for silicon errata #26 on 82598. Mask the interrupt
3204 * before the read of EICR.
3205 */
3206 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIMC, IXGBE_IRQ_CLEAR_MASK);
3207
3208 /* for NAPI, using EIAM to auto-mask tx/rx interrupt bits on read
3209 * therefore no explicit interrupt disable is necessary */
3210 eicr = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_EICR);
3211 if (!eicr) {
3212 /*
3213 * shared interrupt alert!
3214 * make sure interrupts are enabled because the read will
3215 * have disabled interrupts due to EIAM
3216 * finish the workaround of silicon errata on 82598. Unmask
3217 * the interrupt that we masked before the EICR read.
3218 */
3219 if (!test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state))
3220 ixgbe_irq_enable(adapter, true, true);
3221 return IRQ_NONE; /* Not our interrupt */
3222 }
3223
3224 if (eicr & IXGBE_EICR_LSC)
3225 ixgbe_check_lsc(adapter);
3226
3227 switch (hw->mac.type) {
3228 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
3229 ixgbe_check_sfp_event(adapter, eicr);
3230 /* Fall through */
3231 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
3232 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
3233 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
3234 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
3235 if (eicr & IXGBE_EICR_ECC) {
3236 e_info(link, "Received ECC Err, initiating reset\n");
3237 set_bit(__IXGBE_RESET_REQUESTED, &adapter->state);
3238 ixgbe_service_event_schedule(adapter);
3239 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EICR, IXGBE_EICR_ECC);
3240 }
3241 ixgbe_check_overtemp_event(adapter, eicr);
3242 break;
3243 default:
3244 break;
3245 }
3246
3247 ixgbe_check_fan_failure(adapter, eicr);
3248 if (unlikely(eicr & IXGBE_EICR_TIMESYNC))
3249 ixgbe_ptp_check_pps_event(adapter);
3250
3251 /* would disable interrupts here but EIAM disabled it */
3252 napi_schedule_irqoff(&q_vector->napi);
3253
3254 /*
3255 * re-enable link(maybe) and non-queue interrupts, no flush.
3256 * ixgbe_poll will re-enable the queue interrupts
3257 */
3258 if (!test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state))
3259 ixgbe_irq_enable(adapter, false, false);
3260
3261 return IRQ_HANDLED;
3262}
3263
3264/**
3265 * ixgbe_request_irq - initialize interrupts
3266 * @adapter: board private structure
3267 *
3268 * Attempts to configure interrupts using the best available
3269 * capabilities of the hardware and kernel.
3270 **/
3271static int ixgbe_request_irq(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3272{
3273 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
3274 int err;
3275
3276 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED)
3277 err = ixgbe_request_msix_irqs(adapter);
3278 else if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_MSI_ENABLED)
3279 err = request_irq(adapter->pdev->irq, ixgbe_intr, 0,
3280 netdev->name, adapter);
3281 else
3282 err = request_irq(adapter->pdev->irq, ixgbe_intr, IRQF_SHARED,
3283 netdev->name, adapter);
3284
3285 if (err)
3286 e_err(probe, "request_irq failed, Error %d\n", err);
3287
3288 return err;
3289}
3290
3291static void ixgbe_free_irq(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3292{
3293 int vector;
3294
3295 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED)) {
3296 free_irq(adapter->pdev->irq, adapter);
3297 return;
3298 }
3299
3300 if (!adapter->msix_entries)
3301 return;
3302
3303 for (vector = 0; vector < adapter->num_q_vectors; vector++) {
3304 struct ixgbe_q_vector *q_vector = adapter->q_vector[vector];
3305 struct msix_entry *entry = &adapter->msix_entries[vector];
3306
3307 /* free only the irqs that were actually requested */
3308 if (!q_vector->rx.ring && !q_vector->tx.ring)
3309 continue;
3310
3311 /* clear the affinity_mask in the IRQ descriptor */
3312 irq_set_affinity_hint(entry->vector, NULL);
3313
3314 free_irq(entry->vector, q_vector);
3315 }
3316
3317 free_irq(adapter->msix_entries[vector].vector, adapter);
3318}
3319
3320/**
3321 * ixgbe_irq_disable - Mask off interrupt generation on the NIC
3322 * @adapter: board private structure
3323 **/
3324static inline void ixgbe_irq_disable(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3325{
3326 switch (adapter->hw.mac.type) {
3327 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
3328 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_EIMC, ~0);
3329 break;
3330 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
3331 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
3332 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
3333 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
3334 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
3335 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_EIMC, 0xFFFF0000);
3336 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_EIMC_EX(0), ~0);
3337 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_EIMC_EX(1), ~0);
3338 break;
3339 default:
3340 break;
3341 }
3342 IXGBE_WRITE_FLUSH(&adapter->hw);
3343 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED) {
3344 int vector;
3345
3346 for (vector = 0; vector < adapter->num_q_vectors; vector++)
3347 synchronize_irq(adapter->msix_entries[vector].vector);
3348
3349 synchronize_irq(adapter->msix_entries[vector++].vector);
3350 } else {
3351 synchronize_irq(adapter->pdev->irq);
3352 }
3353}

3355/**
3356 * ixgbe_configure_msi_and_legacy - Initialize PIN (INTA...) and MSI interrupts
3357 *
3358 **/
3359static void ixgbe_configure_msi_and_legacy(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3360{
3361 struct ixgbe_q_vector *q_vector = adapter->q_vector[0];
3362
3363 ixgbe_write_eitr(q_vector);
3364
3365 ixgbe_set_ivar(adapter, 0, 0, 0);
3366 ixgbe_set_ivar(adapter, 1, 0, 0);
3367
3368 e_info(hw, "Legacy interrupt IVAR setup done\n");
3369}
3370
3371/**
3372 * ixgbe_configure_tx_ring - Configure 8259x Tx ring after Reset
3373 * @adapter: board private structure
3374 * @ring: structure containing ring specific data
3375 *
3376 * Configure the Tx descriptor ring after a reset.
3377 **/
3378void ixgbe_configure_tx_ring(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
3379 struct ixgbe_ring *ring)
3380{
3381 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3382 u64 tdba = ring->dma;
3383 int wait_loop = 10;
3384 u32 txdctl = IXGBE_TXDCTL_ENABLE;
3385 u8 reg_idx = ring->reg_idx;
3386
3387 /* disable queue to avoid issues while updating state */
3388 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_TXDCTL(reg_idx), 0);
3389 IXGBE_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
3390
3391 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_TDBAL(reg_idx),
3392 (tdba & DMA_BIT_MASK(32)));
3393 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_TDBAH(reg_idx), (tdba >> 32));
3394 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_TDLEN(reg_idx),
3395 ring->count * sizeof(union ixgbe_adv_tx_desc));
3396 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_TDH(reg_idx), 0);
3397 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_TDT(reg_idx), 0);
3398 ring->tail = adapter->io_addr + IXGBE_TDT(reg_idx);
3399
3400 /*
3401 * set WTHRESH to encourage burst writeback, it should not be set
3402 * higher than 1 when:
3403 * - ITR is 0 as it could cause false TX hangs
3404 * - ITR is set to > 100k int/sec and BQL is enabled
3405 *
3406 * In order to avoid issues WTHRESH + PTHRESH should always be equal
3407 * to or less than the number of on chip descriptors, which is
3408 * currently 40.
3409 */
3410 if (!ring->q_vector || (ring->q_vector->itr < IXGBE_100K_ITR))
3411 txdctl |= 1u << 16; /* WTHRESH = 1 */
3412 else
3413 txdctl |= 8u << 16; /* WTHRESH = 8 */
3414
3415 /*
3416 * Setting PTHRESH to 32 both improves performance
3417 * and avoids a TX hang with DFP enabled
3418 */
3419 txdctl |= (1u << 8) | /* HTHRESH = 1 */
3420 32; /* PTHRESH = 32 */
3421
3422 /* reinitialize flowdirector state */
3423 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_HASH_CAPABLE) {
3424 ring->atr_sample_rate = adapter->atr_sample_rate;
3425 ring->atr_count = 0;
3426 set_bit(__IXGBE_TX_FDIR_INIT_DONE, &ring->state);
3427 } else {
3428 ring->atr_sample_rate = 0;
3429 }
3430
3431 /* initialize XPS */
3432 if (!test_and_set_bit(__IXGBE_TX_XPS_INIT_DONE, &ring->state)) {
3433 struct ixgbe_q_vector *q_vector = ring->q_vector;
3434
3435 if (q_vector)
3436 netif_set_xps_queue(ring->netdev,
3437 &q_vector->affinity_mask,
3438 ring->queue_index);
3439 }
3440
3441 clear_bit(__IXGBE_HANG_CHECK_ARMED, &ring->state);
3442
3443 /* reinitialize tx_buffer_info */
3444 memset(ring->tx_buffer_info, 0,
3445 sizeof(struct ixgbe_tx_buffer) * ring->count);
3446
3447 /* enable queue */
3448 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_TXDCTL(reg_idx), txdctl);
3449
3450 /* TXDCTL.EN will return 0 on 82598 if link is down, so skip it */
3451 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB &&
3452 !(IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_LINKS) & IXGBE_LINKS_UP))
3453 return;
3454
3455 /* poll to verify queue is enabled */
3456 do {
3457 usleep_range(1000, 2000);
3458 txdctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_TXDCTL(reg_idx));
3459 } while (--wait_loop && !(txdctl & IXGBE_TXDCTL_ENABLE));
3460 if (!wait_loop)
3461 hw_dbg(hw, "Could not enable Tx Queue %d\n", reg_idx);
3462}
3463
3464static void ixgbe_setup_mtqc(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3465{
3466 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3467 u32 rttdcs, mtqc;
3468 u8 tcs = netdev_get_num_tc(adapter->netdev);
3469
3470 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
3471 return;
3472
3473 /* disable the arbiter while setting MTQC */
3474 rttdcs = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RTTDCS);
3475 rttdcs |= IXGBE_RTTDCS_ARBDIS;
3476 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RTTDCS, rttdcs);
3477
3478 /* set transmit pool layout */
3479 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED) {
3480 mtqc = IXGBE_MTQC_VT_ENA;
3481 if (tcs > 4)
3482 mtqc |= IXGBE_MTQC_RT_ENA | IXGBE_MTQC_8TC_8TQ;
3483 else if (tcs > 1)
3484 mtqc |= IXGBE_MTQC_RT_ENA | IXGBE_MTQC_4TC_4TQ;
3485 else if (adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_VMDQ].mask ==
3486 IXGBE_82599_VMDQ_4Q_MASK)
3487 mtqc |= IXGBE_MTQC_32VF;
3488 else
3489 mtqc |= IXGBE_MTQC_64VF;
3490 } else {
3491 if (tcs > 4)
3492 mtqc = IXGBE_MTQC_RT_ENA | IXGBE_MTQC_8TC_8TQ;
3493 else if (tcs > 1)
3494 mtqc = IXGBE_MTQC_RT_ENA | IXGBE_MTQC_4TC_4TQ;
3495 else
3496 mtqc = IXGBE_MTQC_64Q_1PB;
3497 }
3498
3499 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_MTQC, mtqc);
3500
3501 /* Enable Security TX Buffer IFG for multiple pb */
3502 if (tcs) {
3503 u32 sectx = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_SECTXMINIFG);
3504 sectx |= IXGBE_SECTX_DCB;
3505 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_SECTXMINIFG, sectx);
3506 }
3507
3508 /* re-enable the arbiter */
3509 rttdcs &= ~IXGBE_RTTDCS_ARBDIS;
3510 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RTTDCS, rttdcs);
3511}
3512
3513/**
3514 * ixgbe_configure_tx - Configure 8259x Transmit Unit after Reset
3515 * @adapter: board private structure
3516 *
3517 * Configure the Tx unit of the MAC after a reset.
3518 **/
3519static void ixgbe_configure_tx(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3520{
3521 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3522 u32 dmatxctl;
3523 u32 i;
3524
3525 ixgbe_setup_mtqc(adapter);
3526
3527 if (hw->mac.type != ixgbe_mac_82598EB) {
3528 /* DMATXCTL.EN must be before Tx queues are enabled */
3529 dmatxctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_DMATXCTL);
3530 dmatxctl |= IXGBE_DMATXCTL_TE;
3531 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_DMATXCTL, dmatxctl);
3532 }
3533
3534 /* Setup the HW Tx Head and Tail descriptor pointers */
3535 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++)
3536 ixgbe_configure_tx_ring(adapter, adapter->tx_ring[i]);
3537 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_xdp_queues; i++)
3538 ixgbe_configure_tx_ring(adapter, adapter->xdp_ring[i]);
3539}
3540
3541static void ixgbe_enable_rx_drop(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
3542 struct ixgbe_ring *ring)
3543{
3544 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3545 u8 reg_idx = ring->reg_idx;
3546 u32 srrctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_SRRCTL(reg_idx));
3547
3548 srrctl |= IXGBE_SRRCTL_DROP_EN;
3549
3550 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_SRRCTL(reg_idx), srrctl);
3551}
3552
3553static void ixgbe_disable_rx_drop(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
3554 struct ixgbe_ring *ring)
3555{
3556 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3557 u8 reg_idx = ring->reg_idx;
3558 u32 srrctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_SRRCTL(reg_idx));
3559
3560 srrctl &= ~IXGBE_SRRCTL_DROP_EN;
3561
3562 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_SRRCTL(reg_idx), srrctl);
3563}
3564
3565#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
3566void ixgbe_set_rx_drop_en(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3567#else
3568static void ixgbe_set_rx_drop_en(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3569#endif
3570{
3571 int i;
3572 bool pfc_en = adapter->dcb_cfg.pfc_mode_enable;
3573
3574 if (adapter->ixgbe_ieee_pfc)
3575 pfc_en |= !!(adapter->ixgbe_ieee_pfc->pfc_en);
3576
3577 /*
3578 * We should set the drop enable bit if:
3579 * SR-IOV is enabled
3580 * or
3581 * Number of Rx queues > 1 and flow control is disabled
3582 *
3583 * This allows us to avoid head of line blocking for security
3584 * and performance reasons.
3585 */
3586 if (adapter->num_vfs || (adapter->num_rx_queues > 1 &&
3587 !(adapter->hw.fc.current_mode & ixgbe_fc_tx_pause) && !pfc_en)) {
3588 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++)
3589 ixgbe_enable_rx_drop(adapter, adapter->rx_ring[i]);
3590 } else {
3591 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++)
3592 ixgbe_disable_rx_drop(adapter, adapter->rx_ring[i]);
3593 }
3594}
3595
3596#define IXGBE_SRRCTL_BSIZEHDRSIZE_SHIFT 2
3597
3598static void ixgbe_configure_srrctl(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
3599 struct ixgbe_ring *rx_ring)
3600{
3601 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3602 u32 srrctl;
3603 u8 reg_idx = rx_ring->reg_idx;
3604
3605 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB) {
3606 u16 mask = adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_RSS].mask;
3607
3608 /*
3609 * if VMDq is not active we must program one srrctl register
3610 * per RSS queue since we have enabled RDRXCTL.MVMEN
3611 */
3612 reg_idx &= mask;
3613 }
3614
3615 /* configure header buffer length, needed for RSC */
3616 srrctl = IXGBE_RX_HDR_SIZE << IXGBE_SRRCTL_BSIZEHDRSIZE_SHIFT;
3617
3618 /* configure the packet buffer length */
3619 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_RX_3K_BUFFER, &rx_ring->state))
3620 srrctl |= IXGBE_RXBUFFER_3K >> IXGBE_SRRCTL_BSIZEPKT_SHIFT;
3621 else
3622 srrctl |= IXGBE_RXBUFFER_2K >> IXGBE_SRRCTL_BSIZEPKT_SHIFT;
3623
3624 /* configure descriptor type */
3625 srrctl |= IXGBE_SRRCTL_DESCTYPE_ADV_ONEBUF;
3626
3627 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_SRRCTL(reg_idx), srrctl);
3628}
3629
3630/**
3631 * ixgbe_rss_indir_tbl_entries - Return RSS indirection table entries
3632 * @adapter: device handle
3633 *
3634 * - 82598/82599/X540: 128
3635 * - X550(non-SRIOV mode): 512
3636 * - X550(SRIOV mode): 64
3637 */
3638u32 ixgbe_rss_indir_tbl_entries(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3639{
3640 if (adapter->hw.mac.type < ixgbe_mac_X550)
3641 return 128;
3642 else if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED)
3643 return 64;
3644 else
3645 return 512;
3646}
3647
3648/**
3649 * ixgbe_store_key - Write the RSS key to HW
3650 * @adapter: device handle
3651 *
3652 * Write the RSS key stored in adapter.rss_key to HW.
3653 */
3654void ixgbe_store_key(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3655{
3656 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3657 int i;
3658
3659 for (i = 0; i < 10; i++)
3660 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RSSRK(i), adapter->rss_key[i]);
3661}
3662
3663/**
3664 * ixgbe_init_rss_key - Initialize adapter RSS key
3665 * @adapter: device handle
3666 *
3667 * Allocates and initializes the RSS key if it is not allocated.
3668 **/
3669static inline int ixgbe_init_rss_key(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3670{
3671 u32 *rss_key;
3672
3673 if (!adapter->rss_key) {
3674 rss_key = kzalloc(IXGBE_RSS_KEY_SIZE, GFP_KERNEL);
3675 if (unlikely(!rss_key))
3676 return -ENOMEM;
3677
3678 netdev_rss_key_fill(rss_key, IXGBE_RSS_KEY_SIZE);
3679 adapter->rss_key = rss_key;
3680 }
3681
3682 return 0;
3683}
3684
3685/**
3686 * ixgbe_store_reta - Write the RETA table to HW
3687 * @adapter: device handle
3688 *
3689 * Write the RSS redirection table stored in adapter.rss_indir_tbl[] to HW.
3690 */
3691void ixgbe_store_reta(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3692{
3693 u32 i, reta_entries = ixgbe_rss_indir_tbl_entries(adapter);
3694 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3695 u32 reta = 0;
3696 u32 indices_multi;
3697 u8 *indir_tbl = adapter->rss_indir_tbl;
3698
3699 /* Fill out the redirection table as follows:
3700 * - 82598: 8 bit wide entries containing pair of 4 bit RSS
3701 * indices.
3702 * - 82599/X540: 8 bit wide entries containing 4 bit RSS index
3703 * - X550: 8 bit wide entries containing 6 bit RSS index
3704 */
3705 if (adapter->hw.mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
3706 indices_multi = 0x11;
3707 else
3708 indices_multi = 0x1;
3709
3710 /* Write redirection table to HW */
3711 for (i = 0; i < reta_entries; i++) {
3712 reta |= indices_multi * indir_tbl[i] << (i & 0x3) * 8;
3713 if ((i & 3) == 3) {
3714 if (i < 128)
3715 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RETA(i >> 2), reta);
3716 else
3717 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_ERETA((i >> 2) - 32),
3718 reta);
3719 reta = 0;
3720 }
3721 }
3722}
3723
3724/**
3725 * ixgbe_store_vfreta - Write the RETA table to HW (x550 devices in SRIOV mode)
3726 * @adapter: device handle
3727 *
3728 * Write the RSS redirection table stored in adapter.rss_indir_tbl[] to HW.
3729 */
3730static void ixgbe_store_vfreta(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3731{
3732 u32 i, reta_entries = ixgbe_rss_indir_tbl_entries(adapter);
3733 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3734 u32 vfreta = 0;
3735 unsigned int pf_pool = adapter->num_vfs;
3736
3737 /* Write redirection table to HW */
3738 for (i = 0; i < reta_entries; i++) {
3739 vfreta |= (u32)adapter->rss_indir_tbl[i] << (i & 0x3) * 8;
3740 if ((i & 3) == 3) {
3741 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_PFVFRETA(i >> 2, pf_pool),
3742 vfreta);
3743 vfreta = 0;
3744 }
3745 }
3746}
3747
3748static void ixgbe_setup_reta(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3749{
3750 u32 i, j;
3751 u32 reta_entries = ixgbe_rss_indir_tbl_entries(adapter);
3752 u16 rss_i = adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_RSS].indices;
3753
3754 /* Program table for at least 4 queues w/ SR-IOV so that VFs can
3755 * make full use of any rings they may have. We will use the
3756 * PSRTYPE register to control how many rings we use within the PF.
3757 */
3758 if ((adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED) && (rss_i < 4))
3759 rss_i = 4;
3760
3761 /* Fill out hash function seeds */
3762 ixgbe_store_key(adapter);
3763
3764 /* Fill out redirection table */
3765 memset(adapter->rss_indir_tbl, 0, sizeof(adapter->rss_indir_tbl));
3766
3767 for (i = 0, j = 0; i < reta_entries; i++, j++) {
3768 if (j == rss_i)
3769 j = 0;
3770
3771 adapter->rss_indir_tbl[i] = j;
3772 }
3773
3774 ixgbe_store_reta(adapter);
3775}
3776
3777static void ixgbe_setup_vfreta(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3778{
3779 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3780 u16 rss_i = adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_RSS].indices;
3781 unsigned int pf_pool = adapter->num_vfs;
3782 int i, j;
3783
3784 /* Fill out hash function seeds */
3785 for (i = 0; i < 10; i++)
3786 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_PFVFRSSRK(i, pf_pool),
3787 *(adapter->rss_key + i));
3788
3789 /* Fill out the redirection table */
3790 for (i = 0, j = 0; i < 64; i++, j++) {
3791 if (j == rss_i)
3792 j = 0;
3793
3794 adapter->rss_indir_tbl[i] = j;
3795 }
3796
3797 ixgbe_store_vfreta(adapter);
3798}
3799
3800static void ixgbe_setup_mrqc(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
3801{
3802 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3803 u32 mrqc = 0, rss_field = 0, vfmrqc = 0;
3804 u32 rxcsum;
3805
3806 /* Disable indicating checksum in descriptor, enables RSS hash */
3807 rxcsum = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXCSUM);
3808 rxcsum |= IXGBE_RXCSUM_PCSD;
3809 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXCSUM, rxcsum);
3810
3811 if (adapter->hw.mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB) {
3812 if (adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_RSS].mask)
3813 mrqc = IXGBE_MRQC_RSSEN;
3814 } else {
3815 u8 tcs = netdev_get_num_tc(adapter->netdev);
3816
3817 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED) {
3818 if (tcs > 4)
3819 mrqc = IXGBE_MRQC_VMDQRT8TCEN; /* 8 TCs */
3820 else if (tcs > 1)
3821 mrqc = IXGBE_MRQC_VMDQRT4TCEN; /* 4 TCs */
3822 else if (adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_VMDQ].mask ==
3823 IXGBE_82599_VMDQ_4Q_MASK)
3824 mrqc = IXGBE_MRQC_VMDQRSS32EN;
3825 else
3826 mrqc = IXGBE_MRQC_VMDQRSS64EN;
3827
3828 /* Enable L3/L4 for Tx Switched packets */
3829 mrqc |= IXGBE_MRQC_L3L4TXSWEN;
3830 } else {
3831 if (tcs > 4)
3832 mrqc = IXGBE_MRQC_RTRSS8TCEN;
3833 else if (tcs > 1)
3834 mrqc = IXGBE_MRQC_RTRSS4TCEN;
3835 else
3836 mrqc = IXGBE_MRQC_RSSEN;
3837 }
3838 }
3839
3840 /* Perform hash on these packet types */
3841 rss_field |= IXGBE_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV4 |
3842 IXGBE_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV4_TCP |
3843 IXGBE_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV6 |
3844 IXGBE_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV6_TCP;
3845
3846 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSS_FIELD_IPV4_UDP)
3847 rss_field |= IXGBE_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV4_UDP;
3848 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSS_FIELD_IPV6_UDP)
3849 rss_field |= IXGBE_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV6_UDP;
3850
3851 if ((hw->mac.type >= ixgbe_mac_X550) &&
3852 (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED)) {
3853 unsigned int pf_pool = adapter->num_vfs;
3854
3855 /* Enable VF RSS mode */
3856 mrqc |= IXGBE_MRQC_MULTIPLE_RSS;
3857 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_MRQC, mrqc);
3858
3859 /* Setup RSS through the VF registers */
3860 ixgbe_setup_vfreta(adapter);
3861 vfmrqc = IXGBE_MRQC_RSSEN;
3862 vfmrqc |= rss_field;
3863 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_PFVFMRQC(pf_pool), vfmrqc);
3864 } else {
3865 ixgbe_setup_reta(adapter);
3866 mrqc |= rss_field;
3867 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_MRQC, mrqc);
3868 }
3869}
3870
3871/**
3872 * ixgbe_configure_rscctl - enable RSC for the indicated ring
3873 * @adapter: address of board private structure
3874 * @index: index of ring to set
3875 **/
3876static void ixgbe_configure_rscctl(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
3877 struct ixgbe_ring *ring)
3878{
3879 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3880 u32 rscctrl;
3881 u8 reg_idx = ring->reg_idx;
3882
3883 if (!ring_is_rsc_enabled(ring))
3884 return;
3885
3886 rscctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RSCCTL(reg_idx));
3887 rscctrl |= IXGBE_RSCCTL_RSCEN;
3888 /*
3889 * we must limit the number of descriptors so that the
3890 * total size of max desc * buf_len is not greater
3891 * than 65536
3892 */
3893 rscctrl |= IXGBE_RSCCTL_MAXDESC_16;
3894 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RSCCTL(reg_idx), rscctrl);
3895}
3896
3897#define IXGBE_MAX_RX_DESC_POLL 10
3898static void ixgbe_rx_desc_queue_enable(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
3899 struct ixgbe_ring *ring)
3900{
3901 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3902 int wait_loop = IXGBE_MAX_RX_DESC_POLL;
3903 u32 rxdctl;
3904 u8 reg_idx = ring->reg_idx;
3905
3906 if (ixgbe_removed(hw->hw_addr))
3907 return;
3908 /* RXDCTL.EN will return 0 on 82598 if link is down, so skip it */
3909 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB &&
3910 !(IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_LINKS) & IXGBE_LINKS_UP))
3911 return;
3912
3913 do {
3914 usleep_range(1000, 2000);
3915 rxdctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXDCTL(reg_idx));
3916 } while (--wait_loop && !(rxdctl & IXGBE_RXDCTL_ENABLE));
3917
3918 if (!wait_loop) {
3919 e_err(drv, "RXDCTL.ENABLE on Rx queue %d not set within "
3920 "the polling period\n", reg_idx);
3921 }
3922}
3923
3924void ixgbe_disable_rx_queue(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
3925 struct ixgbe_ring *ring)
3926{
3927 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3928 int wait_loop = IXGBE_MAX_RX_DESC_POLL;
3929 u32 rxdctl;
3930 u8 reg_idx = ring->reg_idx;
3931
3932 if (ixgbe_removed(hw->hw_addr))
3933 return;
3934 rxdctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXDCTL(reg_idx));
3935 rxdctl &= ~IXGBE_RXDCTL_ENABLE;
3936
3937 /* write value back with RXDCTL.ENABLE bit cleared */
3938 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXDCTL(reg_idx), rxdctl);
3939
3940 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB &&
3941 !(IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_LINKS) & IXGBE_LINKS_UP))
3942 return;
3943
3944 /* the hardware may take up to 100us to really disable the rx queue */
3945 do {
3946 udelay(10);
3947 rxdctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXDCTL(reg_idx));
3948 } while (--wait_loop && (rxdctl & IXGBE_RXDCTL_ENABLE));
3949
3950 if (!wait_loop) {
3951 e_err(drv, "RXDCTL.ENABLE on Rx queue %d not cleared within "
3952 "the polling period\n", reg_idx);
3953 }
3954}
3955
3956void ixgbe_configure_rx_ring(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
3957 struct ixgbe_ring *ring)
3958{
3959 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3960 union ixgbe_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc;
3961 u64 rdba = ring->dma;
3962 u32 rxdctl;
3963 u8 reg_idx = ring->reg_idx;
3964
3965 /* disable queue to avoid issues while updating state */
3966 rxdctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXDCTL(reg_idx));
3967 ixgbe_disable_rx_queue(adapter, ring);
3968
3969 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RDBAL(reg_idx), (rdba & DMA_BIT_MASK(32)));
3970 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RDBAH(reg_idx), (rdba >> 32));
3971 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RDLEN(reg_idx),
3972 ring->count * sizeof(union ixgbe_adv_rx_desc));
3973 /* Force flushing of IXGBE_RDLEN to prevent MDD */
3974 IXGBE_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
3975
3976 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RDH(reg_idx), 0);
3977 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RDT(reg_idx), 0);
3978 ring->tail = adapter->io_addr + IXGBE_RDT(reg_idx);
3979
3980 ixgbe_configure_srrctl(adapter, ring);
3981 ixgbe_configure_rscctl(adapter, ring);
3982
3983 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB) {
3984 /*
3985 * enable cache line friendly hardware writes:
3986 * PTHRESH=32 descriptors (half the internal cache),
3987 * this also removes ugly rx_no_buffer_count increment
3988 * HTHRESH=4 descriptors (to minimize latency on fetch)
3989 * WTHRESH=8 burst writeback up to two cache lines
3990 */
3991 rxdctl &= ~0x3FFFFF;
3992 rxdctl |= 0x080420;
3993#if (PAGE_SIZE < 8192)
3994 /* RXDCTL.RLPML does not work on 82599 */
3995 } else if (hw->mac.type != ixgbe_mac_82599EB) {
3996 rxdctl &= ~(IXGBE_RXDCTL_RLPMLMASK |
3997 IXGBE_RXDCTL_RLPML_EN);
3998
3999 /* Limit the maximum frame size so we don't overrun the skb.
4000 * This can happen in SRIOV mode when the MTU of the VF is
4001 * higher than the MTU of the PF.
4002 */
4003 if (ring_uses_build_skb(ring) &&
4004 !test_bit(__IXGBE_RX_3K_BUFFER, &ring->state))
4005 rxdctl |= IXGBE_MAX_2K_FRAME_BUILD_SKB |
4006 IXGBE_RXDCTL_RLPML_EN;
4007#endif
4008 }
4009
4010 /* initialize rx_buffer_info */
4011 memset(ring->rx_buffer_info, 0,
4012 sizeof(struct ixgbe_rx_buffer) * ring->count);
4013
4014 /* initialize Rx descriptor 0 */
4015 rx_desc = IXGBE_RX_DESC(ring, 0);
4016 rx_desc->wb.upper.length = 0;
4017
4018 /* enable receive descriptor ring */
4019 rxdctl |= IXGBE_RXDCTL_ENABLE;
4020 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXDCTL(reg_idx), rxdctl);
4021
4022 ixgbe_rx_desc_queue_enable(adapter, ring);
4023 ixgbe_alloc_rx_buffers(ring, ixgbe_desc_unused(ring));
4024}
4025
4026static void ixgbe_setup_psrtype(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4027{
4028 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4029 int rss_i = adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_RSS].indices;
4030 u16 pool;
4031
4032 /* PSRTYPE must be initialized in non 82598 adapters */
4033 u32 psrtype = IXGBE_PSRTYPE_TCPHDR |
4034 IXGBE_PSRTYPE_UDPHDR |
4035 IXGBE_PSRTYPE_IPV4HDR |
4036 IXGBE_PSRTYPE_L2HDR |
4037 IXGBE_PSRTYPE_IPV6HDR;
4038
4039 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
4040 return;
4041
4042 if (rss_i > 3)
4043 psrtype |= 2u << 29;
4044 else if (rss_i > 1)
4045 psrtype |= 1u << 29;
4046
4047 for_each_set_bit(pool, &adapter->fwd_bitmask, 32)
4048 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_PSRTYPE(VMDQ_P(pool)), psrtype);
4049}
4050
4051static void ixgbe_configure_virtualization(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4052{
4053 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4054 u32 reg_offset, vf_shift;
4055 u32 gcr_ext, vmdctl;
4056 int i;
4057
4058 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED))
4059 return;
4060
4061 vmdctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VT_CTL);
4062 vmdctl |= IXGBE_VMD_CTL_VMDQ_EN;
4063 vmdctl &= ~IXGBE_VT_CTL_POOL_MASK;
4064 vmdctl |= VMDQ_P(0) << IXGBE_VT_CTL_POOL_SHIFT;
4065 vmdctl |= IXGBE_VT_CTL_REPLEN;
4066 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VT_CTL, vmdctl);
4067
4068 vf_shift = VMDQ_P(0) % 32;
4069 reg_offset = (VMDQ_P(0) >= 32) ? 1 : 0;
4070
4071 /* Enable only the PF's pool for Tx/Rx */
4072 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VFRE(reg_offset), GENMASK(31, vf_shift));
4073 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VFRE(reg_offset ^ 1), reg_offset - 1);
4074 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VFTE(reg_offset), GENMASK(31, vf_shift));
4075 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VFTE(reg_offset ^ 1), reg_offset - 1);
4076 if (adapter->bridge_mode == BRIDGE_MODE_VEB)
4077 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_PFDTXGSWC, IXGBE_PFDTXGSWC_VT_LBEN);
4078
4079 /* Map PF MAC address in RAR Entry 0 to first pool following VFs */
4080 hw->mac.ops.set_vmdq(hw, 0, VMDQ_P(0));
4081
4082 /* clear VLAN promisc flag so VFTA will be updated if necessary */
4083 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_VLAN_PROMISC;
4084
4085 /*
4086 * Set up VF register offsets for selected VT Mode,
4087 * i.e. 32 or 64 VFs for SR-IOV
4088 */
4089 switch (adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_VMDQ].mask) {
4090 case IXGBE_82599_VMDQ_8Q_MASK:
4091 gcr_ext = IXGBE_GCR_EXT_VT_MODE_16;
4092 break;
4093 case IXGBE_82599_VMDQ_4Q_MASK:
4094 gcr_ext = IXGBE_GCR_EXT_VT_MODE_32;
4095 break;
4096 default:
4097 gcr_ext = IXGBE_GCR_EXT_VT_MODE_64;
4098 break;
4099 }
4100
4101 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_GCR_EXT, gcr_ext);
4102
4103 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_vfs; i++) {
4104 /* configure spoof checking */
4105 ixgbe_ndo_set_vf_spoofchk(adapter->netdev, i,
4106 adapter->vfinfo[i].spoofchk_enabled);
4107
4108 /* Enable/Disable RSS query feature */
4109 ixgbe_ndo_set_vf_rss_query_en(adapter->netdev, i,
4110 adapter->vfinfo[i].rss_query_enabled);
4111 }
4112}
4113
4114static void ixgbe_set_rx_buffer_len(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4115{
4116 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4117 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
4118 int max_frame = netdev->mtu + ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN;
4119 struct ixgbe_ring *rx_ring;
4120 int i;
4121 u32 mhadd, hlreg0;
4122
4123#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
4124 /* adjust max frame to be able to do baby jumbo for FCoE */
4125 if ((adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FCOE_ENABLED) &&
4126 (max_frame < IXGBE_FCOE_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE))
4127 max_frame = IXGBE_FCOE_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE;
4128
4129#endif /* IXGBE_FCOE */
4130
4131 /* adjust max frame to be at least the size of a standard frame */
4132 if (max_frame < (ETH_FRAME_LEN + ETH_FCS_LEN))
4133 max_frame = (ETH_FRAME_LEN + ETH_FCS_LEN);
4134
4135 mhadd = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_MHADD);
4136 if (max_frame != (mhadd >> IXGBE_MHADD_MFS_SHIFT)) {
4137 mhadd &= ~IXGBE_MHADD_MFS_MASK;
4138 mhadd |= max_frame << IXGBE_MHADD_MFS_SHIFT;
4139
4140 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_MHADD, mhadd);
4141 }
4142
4143 hlreg0 = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_HLREG0);
4144 /* set jumbo enable since MHADD.MFS is keeping size locked at max_frame */
4145 hlreg0 |= IXGBE_HLREG0_JUMBOEN;
4146 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_HLREG0, hlreg0);
4147
4148 /*
4149 * Setup the HW Rx Head and Tail Descriptor Pointers and
4150 * the Base and Length of the Rx Descriptor Ring
4151 */
4152 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++) {
4153 rx_ring = adapter->rx_ring[i];
4154
4155 clear_ring_rsc_enabled(rx_ring);
4156 clear_bit(__IXGBE_RX_3K_BUFFER, &rx_ring->state);
4157 clear_bit(__IXGBE_RX_BUILD_SKB_ENABLED, &rx_ring->state);
4158
4159 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_ENABLED)
4160 set_ring_rsc_enabled(rx_ring);
4161
4162 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_RX_FCOE, &rx_ring->state))
4163 set_bit(__IXGBE_RX_3K_BUFFER, &rx_ring->state);
4164
4165 clear_bit(__IXGBE_RX_BUILD_SKB_ENABLED, &rx_ring->state);
4166 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RX_LEGACY)
4167 continue;
4168
4169 set_bit(__IXGBE_RX_BUILD_SKB_ENABLED, &rx_ring->state);
4170
4171#if (PAGE_SIZE < 8192)
4172 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_ENABLED)
4173 set_bit(__IXGBE_RX_3K_BUFFER, &rx_ring->state);
4174
4175 if (IXGBE_2K_TOO_SMALL_WITH_PADDING ||
4176 (max_frame > (ETH_FRAME_LEN + ETH_FCS_LEN)))
4177 set_bit(__IXGBE_RX_3K_BUFFER, &rx_ring->state);
4178#endif
4179 }
4180}
4181
4182static void ixgbe_setup_rdrxctl(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4183{
4184 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4185 u32 rdrxctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RDRXCTL);
4186
4187 switch (hw->mac.type) {
4188 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
4189 /*
4190 * For VMDq support of different descriptor types or
4191 * buffer sizes through the use of multiple SRRCTL
4192 * registers, RDRXCTL.MVMEN must be set to 1
4193 *
4194 * also, the manual doesn't mention it clearly but DCA hints
4195 * will only use queue 0's tags unless this bit is set. Side
4196 * effects of setting this bit are only that SRRCTL must be
4197 * fully programmed [0..15]
4198 */
4199 rdrxctl |= IXGBE_RDRXCTL_MVMEN;
4200 break;
4201 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
4202 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
4203 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
4204 if (adapter->num_vfs)
4205 rdrxctl |= IXGBE_RDRXCTL_PSP;
4206 /* fall through */
4207 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
4208 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
4209 /* Disable RSC for ACK packets */
4210 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RSCDBU,
4211 (IXGBE_RSCDBU_RSCACKDIS | IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RSCDBU)));
4212 rdrxctl &= ~IXGBE_RDRXCTL_RSCFRSTSIZE;
4213 /* hardware requires some bits to be set by default */
4214 rdrxctl |= (IXGBE_RDRXCTL_RSCACKC | IXGBE_RDRXCTL_FCOE_WRFIX);
4215 rdrxctl |= IXGBE_RDRXCTL_CRCSTRIP;
4216 break;
4217 default:
4218 /* We should do nothing since we don't know this hardware */
4219 return;
4220 }
4221
4222 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RDRXCTL, rdrxctl);
4223}
4224
4225/**
4226 * ixgbe_configure_rx - Configure 8259x Receive Unit after Reset
4227 * @adapter: board private structure
4228 *
4229 * Configure the Rx unit of the MAC after a reset.
4230 **/
4231static void ixgbe_configure_rx(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4232{
4233 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4234 int i;
4235 u32 rxctrl, rfctl;
4236
4237 /* disable receives while setting up the descriptors */
4238 hw->mac.ops.disable_rx(hw);
4239
4240 ixgbe_setup_psrtype(adapter);
4241 ixgbe_setup_rdrxctl(adapter);
4242
4243 /* RSC Setup */
4244 rfctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RFCTL);
4245 rfctl &= ~IXGBE_RFCTL_RSC_DIS;
4246 if (!(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_ENABLED))
4247 rfctl |= IXGBE_RFCTL_RSC_DIS;
4248
4249 /* disable NFS filtering */
4250 rfctl |= (IXGBE_RFCTL_NFSW_DIS | IXGBE_RFCTL_NFSR_DIS);
4251 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RFCTL, rfctl);
4252
4253 /* Program registers for the distribution of queues */
4254 ixgbe_setup_mrqc(adapter);
4255
4256 /* set_rx_buffer_len must be called before ring initialization */
4257 ixgbe_set_rx_buffer_len(adapter);
4258
4259 /*
4260 * Setup the HW Rx Head and Tail Descriptor Pointers and
4261 * the Base and Length of the Rx Descriptor Ring
4262 */
4263 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++)
4264 ixgbe_configure_rx_ring(adapter, adapter->rx_ring[i]);
4265
4266 rxctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXCTRL);
4267 /* disable drop enable for 82598 parts */
4268 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
4269 rxctrl |= IXGBE_RXCTRL_DMBYPS;
4270
4271 /* enable all receives */
4272 rxctrl |= IXGBE_RXCTRL_RXEN;
4273 hw->mac.ops.enable_rx_dma(hw, rxctrl);
4274}
4275
4276static int ixgbe_vlan_rx_add_vid(struct net_device *netdev,
4277 __be16 proto, u16 vid)
4278{
4279 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4280 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4281
4282 /* add VID to filter table */
4283 if (!vid || !(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_VLAN_PROMISC))
4284 hw->mac.ops.set_vfta(&adapter->hw, vid, VMDQ_P(0), true, !!vid);
4285
4286 set_bit(vid, adapter->active_vlans);
4287
4288 return 0;
4289}
4290
4291static int ixgbe_find_vlvf_entry(struct ixgbe_hw *hw, u32 vlan)
4292{
4293 u32 vlvf;
4294 int idx;
4295
4296 /* short cut the special case */
4297 if (vlan == 0)
4298 return 0;
4299
4300 /* Search for the vlan id in the VLVF entries */
4301 for (idx = IXGBE_VLVF_ENTRIES; --idx;) {
4302 vlvf = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLVF(idx));
4303 if ((vlvf & VLAN_VID_MASK) == vlan)
4304 break;
4305 }
4306
4307 return idx;
4308}
4309
4310void ixgbe_update_pf_promisc_vlvf(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter, u32 vid)
4311{
4312 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4313 u32 bits, word;
4314 int idx;
4315
4316 idx = ixgbe_find_vlvf_entry(hw, vid);
4317 if (!idx)
4318 return;
4319
4320 /* See if any other pools are set for this VLAN filter
4321 * entry other than the PF.
4322 */
4323 word = idx * 2 + (VMDQ_P(0) / 32);
4324 bits = ~BIT(VMDQ_P(0) % 32);
4325 bits &= IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLVFB(word));
4326
4327 /* Disable the filter so this falls into the default pool. */
4328 if (!bits && !IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLVFB(word ^ 1))) {
4329 if (!(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_VLAN_PROMISC))
4330 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLVFB(word), 0);
4331 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLVF(idx), 0);
4332 }
4333}
4334
4335static int ixgbe_vlan_rx_kill_vid(struct net_device *netdev,
4336 __be16 proto, u16 vid)
4337{
4338 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4339 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4340
4341 /* remove VID from filter table */
4342 if (vid && !(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_VLAN_PROMISC))
4343 hw->mac.ops.set_vfta(hw, vid, VMDQ_P(0), false, true);
4344
4345 clear_bit(vid, adapter->active_vlans);
4346
4347 return 0;
4348}
4349
4350/**
4351 * ixgbe_vlan_strip_disable - helper to disable hw vlan stripping
4352 * @adapter: driver data
4353 */
4354static void ixgbe_vlan_strip_disable(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4355{
4356 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4357 u32 vlnctrl;
4358 int i, j;
4359
4360 switch (hw->mac.type) {
4361 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
4362 vlnctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLNCTRL);
4363 vlnctrl &= ~IXGBE_VLNCTRL_VME;
4364 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLNCTRL, vlnctrl);
4365 break;
4366 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
4367 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
4368 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
4369 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
4370 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
4371 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++) {
4372 struct ixgbe_ring *ring = adapter->rx_ring[i];
4373
4374 if (ring->l2_accel_priv)
4375 continue;
4376 j = ring->reg_idx;
4377 vlnctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXDCTL(j));
4378 vlnctrl &= ~IXGBE_RXDCTL_VME;
4379 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXDCTL(j), vlnctrl);
4380 }
4381 break;
4382 default:
4383 break;
4384 }
4385}
4386
4387/**
4388 * ixgbe_vlan_strip_enable - helper to enable hw vlan stripping
4389 * @adapter: driver data
4390 */
4391static void ixgbe_vlan_strip_enable(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4392{
4393 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4394 u32 vlnctrl;
4395 int i, j;
4396
4397 switch (hw->mac.type) {
4398 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
4399 vlnctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLNCTRL);
4400 vlnctrl |= IXGBE_VLNCTRL_VME;
4401 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLNCTRL, vlnctrl);
4402 break;
4403 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
4404 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
4405 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
4406 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
4407 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
4408 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++) {
4409 struct ixgbe_ring *ring = adapter->rx_ring[i];
4410
4411 if (ring->l2_accel_priv)
4412 continue;
4413 j = ring->reg_idx;
4414 vlnctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXDCTL(j));
4415 vlnctrl |= IXGBE_RXDCTL_VME;
4416 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXDCTL(j), vlnctrl);
4417 }
4418 break;
4419 default:
4420 break;
4421 }
4422}
4423
4424static void ixgbe_vlan_promisc_enable(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4425{
4426 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4427 u32 vlnctrl, i;
4428
4429 vlnctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLNCTRL);
4430
4431 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED) {
4432 /* For VMDq and SR-IOV we must leave VLAN filtering enabled */
4433 vlnctrl |= IXGBE_VLNCTRL_VFE;
4434 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLNCTRL, vlnctrl);
4435 } else {
4436 vlnctrl &= ~IXGBE_VLNCTRL_VFE;
4437 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLNCTRL, vlnctrl);
4438 return;
4439 }
4440
4441 /* Nothing to do for 82598 */
4442 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
4443 return;
4444
4445 /* We are already in VLAN promisc, nothing to do */
4446 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_VLAN_PROMISC)
4447 return;
4448
4449 /* Set flag so we don't redo unnecessary work */
4450 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_VLAN_PROMISC;
4451
4452 /* Add PF to all active pools */
4453 for (i = IXGBE_VLVF_ENTRIES; --i;) {
4454 u32 reg_offset = IXGBE_VLVFB(i * 2 + VMDQ_P(0) / 32);
4455 u32 vlvfb = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, reg_offset);
4456
4457 vlvfb |= BIT(VMDQ_P(0) % 32);
4458 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, reg_offset, vlvfb);
4459 }
4460
4461 /* Set all bits in the VLAN filter table array */
4462 for (i = hw->mac.vft_size; i--;)
4463 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VFTA(i), ~0U);
4464}
4465
4466#define VFTA_BLOCK_SIZE 8
4467static void ixgbe_scrub_vfta(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter, u32 vfta_offset)
4468{
4469 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4470 u32 vfta[VFTA_BLOCK_SIZE] = { 0 };
4471 u32 vid_start = vfta_offset * 32;
4472 u32 vid_end = vid_start + (VFTA_BLOCK_SIZE * 32);
4473 u32 i, vid, word, bits;
4474
4475 for (i = IXGBE_VLVF_ENTRIES; --i;) {
4476 u32 vlvf = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLVF(i));
4477
4478 /* pull VLAN ID from VLVF */
4479 vid = vlvf & VLAN_VID_MASK;
4480
4481 /* only concern outselves with a certain range */
4482 if (vid < vid_start || vid >= vid_end)
4483 continue;
4484
4485 if (vlvf) {
4486 /* record VLAN ID in VFTA */
4487 vfta[(vid - vid_start) / 32] |= BIT(vid % 32);
4488
4489 /* if PF is part of this then continue */
4490 if (test_bit(vid, adapter->active_vlans))
4491 continue;
4492 }
4493
4494 /* remove PF from the pool */
4495 word = i * 2 + VMDQ_P(0) / 32;
4496 bits = ~BIT(VMDQ_P(0) % 32);
4497 bits &= IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLVFB(word));
4498 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLVFB(word), bits);
4499 }
4500
4501 /* extract values from active_vlans and write back to VFTA */
4502 for (i = VFTA_BLOCK_SIZE; i--;) {
4503 vid = (vfta_offset + i) * 32;
4504 word = vid / BITS_PER_LONG;
4505 bits = vid % BITS_PER_LONG;
4506
4507 vfta[i] |= adapter->active_vlans[word] >> bits;
4508
4509 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VFTA(vfta_offset + i), vfta[i]);
4510 }
4511}
4512
4513static void ixgbe_vlan_promisc_disable(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4514{
4515 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4516 u32 vlnctrl, i;
4517
4518 /* Set VLAN filtering to enabled */
4519 vlnctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLNCTRL);
4520 vlnctrl |= IXGBE_VLNCTRL_VFE;
4521 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VLNCTRL, vlnctrl);
4522
4523 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED) ||
4524 hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
4525 return;
4526
4527 /* We are not in VLAN promisc, nothing to do */
4528 if (!(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_VLAN_PROMISC))
4529 return;
4530
4531 /* Set flag so we don't redo unnecessary work */
4532 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_VLAN_PROMISC;
4533
4534 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.vft_size; i += VFTA_BLOCK_SIZE)
4535 ixgbe_scrub_vfta(adapter, i);
4536}
4537
4538static void ixgbe_restore_vlan(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4539{
4540 u16 vid = 1;
4541
4542 ixgbe_vlan_rx_add_vid(adapter->netdev, htons(ETH_P_8021Q), 0);
4543
4544 for_each_set_bit_from(vid, adapter->active_vlans, VLAN_N_VID)
4545 ixgbe_vlan_rx_add_vid(adapter->netdev, htons(ETH_P_8021Q), vid);
4546}
4547
4548/**
4549 * ixgbe_write_mc_addr_list - write multicast addresses to MTA
4550 * @netdev: network interface device structure
4551 *
4552 * Writes multicast address list to the MTA hash table.
4553 * Returns: -ENOMEM on failure
4554 * 0 on no addresses written
4555 * X on writing X addresses to MTA
4556 **/
4557static int ixgbe_write_mc_addr_list(struct net_device *netdev)
4558{
4559 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4560 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4561
4562 if (!netif_running(netdev))
4563 return 0;
4564
4565 if (hw->mac.ops.update_mc_addr_list)
4566 hw->mac.ops.update_mc_addr_list(hw, netdev);
4567 else
4568 return -ENOMEM;
4569
4570#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
4571 ixgbe_restore_vf_multicasts(adapter);
4572#endif
4573
4574 return netdev_mc_count(netdev);
4575}
4576
4577#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
4578void ixgbe_full_sync_mac_table(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4579{
4580 struct ixgbe_mac_addr *mac_table = &adapter->mac_table[0];
4581 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4582 int i;
4583
4584 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.num_rar_entries; i++, mac_table++) {
4585 mac_table->state &= ~IXGBE_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED;
4586
4587 if (mac_table->state & IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE)
4588 hw->mac.ops.set_rar(hw, i,
4589 mac_table->addr,
4590 mac_table->pool,
4591 IXGBE_RAH_AV);
4592 else
4593 hw->mac.ops.clear_rar(hw, i);
4594 }
4595}
4596
4597#endif
4598static void ixgbe_sync_mac_table(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4599{
4600 struct ixgbe_mac_addr *mac_table = &adapter->mac_table[0];
4601 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4602 int i;
4603
4604 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.num_rar_entries; i++, mac_table++) {
4605 if (!(mac_table->state & IXGBE_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED))
4606 continue;
4607
4608 mac_table->state &= ~IXGBE_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED;
4609
4610 if (mac_table->state & IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE)
4611 hw->mac.ops.set_rar(hw, i,
4612 mac_table->addr,
4613 mac_table->pool,
4614 IXGBE_RAH_AV);
4615 else
4616 hw->mac.ops.clear_rar(hw, i);
4617 }
4618}
4619
4620static void ixgbe_flush_sw_mac_table(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4621{
4622 struct ixgbe_mac_addr *mac_table = &adapter->mac_table[0];
4623 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4624 int i;
4625
4626 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.num_rar_entries; i++, mac_table++) {
4627 mac_table->state |= IXGBE_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED;
4628 mac_table->state &= ~IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE;
4629 }
4630
4631 ixgbe_sync_mac_table(adapter);
4632}
4633
4634static int ixgbe_available_rars(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter, u16 pool)
4635{
4636 struct ixgbe_mac_addr *mac_table = &adapter->mac_table[0];
4637 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4638 int i, count = 0;
4639
4640 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.num_rar_entries; i++, mac_table++) {
4641 /* do not count default RAR as available */
4642 if (mac_table->state & IXGBE_MAC_STATE_DEFAULT)
4643 continue;
4644
4645 /* only count unused and addresses that belong to us */
4646 if (mac_table->state & IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE) {
4647 if (mac_table->pool != pool)
4648 continue;
4649 }
4650
4651 count++;
4652 }
4653
4654 return count;
4655}
4656
4657/* this function destroys the first RAR entry */
4658static void ixgbe_mac_set_default_filter(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4659{
4660 struct ixgbe_mac_addr *mac_table = &adapter->mac_table[0];
4661 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4662
4663 memcpy(&mac_table->addr, hw->mac.addr, ETH_ALEN);
4664 mac_table->pool = VMDQ_P(0);
4665
4666 mac_table->state = IXGBE_MAC_STATE_DEFAULT | IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE;
4667
4668 hw->mac.ops.set_rar(hw, 0, mac_table->addr, mac_table->pool,
4669 IXGBE_RAH_AV);
4670}
4671
4672int ixgbe_add_mac_filter(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
4673 const u8 *addr, u16 pool)
4674{
4675 struct ixgbe_mac_addr *mac_table = &adapter->mac_table[0];
4676 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4677 int i;
4678
4679 if (is_zero_ether_addr(addr))
4680 return -EINVAL;
4681
4682 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.num_rar_entries; i++, mac_table++) {
4683 if (mac_table->state & IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE)
4684 continue;
4685
4686 ether_addr_copy(mac_table->addr, addr);
4687 mac_table->pool = pool;
4688
4689 mac_table->state |= IXGBE_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED |
4690 IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE;
4691
4692 ixgbe_sync_mac_table(adapter);
4693
4694 return i;
4695 }
4696
4697 return -ENOMEM;
4698}
4699
4700int ixgbe_del_mac_filter(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
4701 const u8 *addr, u16 pool)
4702{
4703 struct ixgbe_mac_addr *mac_table = &adapter->mac_table[0];
4704 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4705 int i;
4706
4707 if (is_zero_ether_addr(addr))
4708 return -EINVAL;
4709
4710 /* search table for addr, if found clear IN_USE flag and sync */
4711 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.num_rar_entries; i++, mac_table++) {
4712 /* we can only delete an entry if it is in use */
4713 if (!(mac_table->state & IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE))
4714 continue;
4715 /* we only care about entries that belong to the given pool */
4716 if (mac_table->pool != pool)
4717 continue;
4718 /* we only care about a specific MAC address */
4719 if (!ether_addr_equal(addr, mac_table->addr))
4720 continue;
4721
4722 mac_table->state |= IXGBE_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED;
4723 mac_table->state &= ~IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE;
4724
4725 ixgbe_sync_mac_table(adapter);
4726
4727 return 0;
4728 }
4729
4730 return -ENOMEM;
4731}
4732/**
4733 * ixgbe_write_uc_addr_list - write unicast addresses to RAR table
4734 * @netdev: network interface device structure
4735 *
4736 * Writes unicast address list to the RAR table.
4737 * Returns: -ENOMEM on failure/insufficient address space
4738 * 0 on no addresses written
4739 * X on writing X addresses to the RAR table
4740 **/
4741static int ixgbe_write_uc_addr_list(struct net_device *netdev, int vfn)
4742{
4743 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4744 int count = 0;
4745
4746 /* return ENOMEM indicating insufficient memory for addresses */
4747 if (netdev_uc_count(netdev) > ixgbe_available_rars(adapter, vfn))
4748 return -ENOMEM;
4749
4750 if (!netdev_uc_empty(netdev)) {
4751 struct netdev_hw_addr *ha;
4752 netdev_for_each_uc_addr(ha, netdev) {
4753 ixgbe_del_mac_filter(adapter, ha->addr, vfn);
4754 ixgbe_add_mac_filter(adapter, ha->addr, vfn);
4755 count++;
4756 }
4757 }
4758 return count;
4759}
4760
4761static int ixgbe_uc_sync(struct net_device *netdev, const unsigned char *addr)
4762{
4763 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4764 int ret;
4765
4766 ret = ixgbe_add_mac_filter(adapter, addr, VMDQ_P(0));
4767
4768 return min_t(int, ret, 0);
4769}
4770
4771static int ixgbe_uc_unsync(struct net_device *netdev, const unsigned char *addr)
4772{
4773 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4774
4775 ixgbe_del_mac_filter(adapter, addr, VMDQ_P(0));
4776
4777 return 0;
4778}
4779
4780/**
4781 * ixgbe_set_rx_mode - Unicast, Multicast and Promiscuous mode set
4782 * @netdev: network interface device structure
4783 *
4784 * The set_rx_method entry point is called whenever the unicast/multicast
4785 * address list or the network interface flags are updated. This routine is
4786 * responsible for configuring the hardware for proper unicast, multicast and
4787 * promiscuous mode.
4788 **/
4789void ixgbe_set_rx_mode(struct net_device *netdev)
4790{
4791 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4792 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4793 u32 fctrl, vmolr = IXGBE_VMOLR_BAM | IXGBE_VMOLR_AUPE;
4794 netdev_features_t features = netdev->features;
4795 int count;
4796
4797 /* Check for Promiscuous and All Multicast modes */
4798 fctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCTRL);
4799
4800 /* set all bits that we expect to always be set */
4801 fctrl &= ~IXGBE_FCTRL_SBP; /* disable store-bad-packets */
4802 fctrl |= IXGBE_FCTRL_BAM;
4803 fctrl |= IXGBE_FCTRL_DPF; /* discard pause frames when FC enabled */
4804 fctrl |= IXGBE_FCTRL_PMCF;
4805
4806 /* clear the bits we are changing the status of */
4807 fctrl &= ~(IXGBE_FCTRL_UPE | IXGBE_FCTRL_MPE);
4808 if (netdev->flags & IFF_PROMISC) {
4809 hw->addr_ctrl.user_set_promisc = true;
4810 fctrl |= (IXGBE_FCTRL_UPE | IXGBE_FCTRL_MPE);
4811 vmolr |= IXGBE_VMOLR_MPE;
4812 features &= ~NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER;
4813 } else {
4814 if (netdev->flags & IFF_ALLMULTI) {
4815 fctrl |= IXGBE_FCTRL_MPE;
4816 vmolr |= IXGBE_VMOLR_MPE;
4817 }
4818 hw->addr_ctrl.user_set_promisc = false;
4819 }
4820
4821 /*
4822 * Write addresses to available RAR registers, if there is not
4823 * sufficient space to store all the addresses then enable
4824 * unicast promiscuous mode
4825 */
4826 if (__dev_uc_sync(netdev, ixgbe_uc_sync, ixgbe_uc_unsync)) {
4827 fctrl |= IXGBE_FCTRL_UPE;
4828 vmolr |= IXGBE_VMOLR_ROPE;
4829 }
4830
4831 /* Write addresses to the MTA, if the attempt fails
4832 * then we should just turn on promiscuous mode so
4833 * that we can at least receive multicast traffic
4834 */
4835 count = ixgbe_write_mc_addr_list(netdev);
4836 if (count < 0) {
4837 fctrl |= IXGBE_FCTRL_MPE;
4838 vmolr |= IXGBE_VMOLR_MPE;
4839 } else if (count) {
4840 vmolr |= IXGBE_VMOLR_ROMPE;
4841 }
4842
4843 if (hw->mac.type != ixgbe_mac_82598EB) {
4844 vmolr |= IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VMOLR(VMDQ_P(0))) &
4845 ~(IXGBE_VMOLR_MPE | IXGBE_VMOLR_ROMPE |
4846 IXGBE_VMOLR_ROPE);
4847 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VMOLR(VMDQ_P(0)), vmolr);
4848 }
4849
4850 /* This is useful for sniffing bad packets. */
4851 if (features & NETIF_F_RXALL) {
4852 /* UPE and MPE will be handled by normal PROMISC logic
4853 * in e1000e_set_rx_mode */
4854 fctrl |= (IXGBE_FCTRL_SBP | /* Receive bad packets */
4855 IXGBE_FCTRL_BAM | /* RX All Bcast Pkts */
4856 IXGBE_FCTRL_PMCF); /* RX All MAC Ctrl Pkts */
4857
4858 fctrl &= ~(IXGBE_FCTRL_DPF);
4859 /* NOTE: VLAN filtering is disabled by setting PROMISC */
4860 }
4861
4862 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCTRL, fctrl);
4863
4864 if (features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX)
4865 ixgbe_vlan_strip_enable(adapter);
4866 else
4867 ixgbe_vlan_strip_disable(adapter);
4868
4869 if (features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER)
4870 ixgbe_vlan_promisc_disable(adapter);
4871 else
4872 ixgbe_vlan_promisc_enable(adapter);
4873}
4874
4875static void ixgbe_napi_enable_all(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4876{
4877 int q_idx;
4878
4879 for (q_idx = 0; q_idx < adapter->num_q_vectors; q_idx++)
4880 napi_enable(&adapter->q_vector[q_idx]->napi);
4881}

4883static void ixgbe_napi_disable_all(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4884{
4885 int q_idx;
4886
4887 for (q_idx = 0; q_idx < adapter->num_q_vectors; q_idx++)
4888 napi_disable(&adapter->q_vector[q_idx]->napi);
4889}

4891static void ixgbe_clear_udp_tunnel_port(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter, u32 mask)
4892{
4893 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4894 u32 vxlanctrl;
4895
4896 if (!(adapter->flags & (IXGBE_FLAG_VXLAN_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE |
4897 IXGBE_FLAG_GENEVE_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE)))
4898 return;
4899
4900 vxlanctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VXLANCTRL) & ~mask;
4901 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VXLANCTRL, vxlanctrl);
4902
4903 if (mask & IXGBE_VXLANCTRL_VXLAN_UDPPORT_MASK)
4904 adapter->vxlan_port = 0;
4905
4906 if (mask & IXGBE_VXLANCTRL_GENEVE_UDPPORT_MASK)
4907 adapter->geneve_port = 0;
4908}
