4910#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
4911/**
4912 * ixgbe_configure_dcb - Configure DCB hardware
4913 * @adapter: ixgbe adapter struct
4914 *
4915 * This is called by the driver on open to configure the DCB hardware.
4916 * This is also called by the gennetlink interface when reconfiguring
4917 * the DCB state.
4918 */
4919static void ixgbe_configure_dcb(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
4920{
4921 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4922 int max_frame = adapter->netdev->mtu + ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN;
4923
4924 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED)) {
4925 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
4926 netif_set_gso_max_size(adapter->netdev, 65536);
4927 return;
4928 }
4929
4930 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
4931 netif_set_gso_max_size(adapter->netdev, 32768);
4932
4933#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
4934 if (adapter->netdev->features & NETIF_F_FCOE_MTU)
4935 max_frame = max(max_frame, IXGBE_FCOE_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE);
4936#endif
4937
4938 /* reconfigure the hardware */
4939 if (adapter->dcbx_cap & DCB_CAP_DCBX_VER_CEE) {
4940 ixgbe_dcb_calculate_tc_credits(hw, &adapter->dcb_cfg, max_frame,
4941 DCB_TX_CONFIG);
4942 ixgbe_dcb_calculate_tc_credits(hw, &adapter->dcb_cfg, max_frame,
4943 DCB_RX_CONFIG);
4944 ixgbe_dcb_hw_config(hw, &adapter->dcb_cfg);
4945 } else if (adapter->ixgbe_ieee_ets && adapter->ixgbe_ieee_pfc) {
4946 ixgbe_dcb_hw_ets(&adapter->hw,
4947 adapter->ixgbe_ieee_ets,
4948 max_frame);
4949 ixgbe_dcb_hw_pfc_config(&adapter->hw,
4950 adapter->ixgbe_ieee_pfc->pfc_en,
4951 adapter->ixgbe_ieee_ets->prio_tc);
4952 }
4953
4954 /* Enable RSS Hash per TC */
4955 if (hw->mac.type != ixgbe_mac_82598EB) {
4956 u32 msb = 0;
4957 u16 rss_i = adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_RSS].indices - 1;
4958
4959 while (rss_i) {
4960 msb++;
4961 rss_i >>= 1;
4962 }
4963
4964 /* write msb to all 8 TCs in one write */
4965 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RQTC, msb * 0x11111111);
4966 }
4967}
4968#endif
4969
4970/* Additional bittime to account for IXGBE framing */
4971#define IXGBE_ETH_FRAMING 20
4972
4973/**
4974 * ixgbe_hpbthresh - calculate high water mark for flow control
4975 *
4976 * @adapter: board private structure to calculate for
4977 * @pb: packet buffer to calculate
4978 */
4979static int ixgbe_hpbthresh(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter, int pb)
4980{
4981 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4982 struct net_device *dev = adapter->netdev;
4983 int link, tc, kb, marker;
4984 u32 dv_id, rx_pba;
4985
4986 /* Calculate max LAN frame size */
4987 tc = link = dev->mtu + ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN + IXGBE_ETH_FRAMING;
4988
4989#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
4990 /* FCoE traffic class uses FCOE jumbo frames */
4991 if ((dev->features & NETIF_F_FCOE_MTU) &&
4992 (tc < IXGBE_FCOE_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE) &&
4993 (pb == ixgbe_fcoe_get_tc(adapter)))
4994 tc = IXGBE_FCOE_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE;
4995#endif
4996
4997 /* Calculate delay value for device */
4998 switch (hw->mac.type) {
4999 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
5000 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
5001 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
5002 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
5003 dv_id = IXGBE_DV_X540(link, tc);
5004 break;
5005 default:
5006 dv_id = IXGBE_DV(link, tc);
5007 break;
5008 }
5009
5010 /* Loopback switch introduces additional latency */
5011 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED)
5012 dv_id += IXGBE_B2BT(tc);
5013
5014 /* Delay value is calculated in bit times convert to KB */
5015 kb = IXGBE_BT2KB(dv_id);
5016 rx_pba = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RXPBSIZE(pb)) >> 10;
5017
5018 marker = rx_pba - kb;
5019
5020 /* It is possible that the packet buffer is not large enough
5021 * to provide required headroom. In this case throw an error
5022 * to user and a do the best we can.
5023 */
5024 if (marker < 0) {
5025 e_warn(drv, "Packet Buffer(%i) can not provide enough"
5026 "headroom to support flow control."
5027 "Decrease MTU or number of traffic classes\n", pb);
5028 marker = tc + 1;
5029 }
5030
5031 return marker;
5032}
5033
5034/**
5035 * ixgbe_lpbthresh - calculate low water mark for for flow control
5036 *
5037 * @adapter: board private structure to calculate for
5038 * @pb: packet buffer to calculate
5039 */
5040static int ixgbe_lpbthresh(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter, int pb)
5041{
5042 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5043 struct net_device *dev = adapter->netdev;
5044 int tc;
5045 u32 dv_id;
5046
5047 /* Calculate max LAN frame size */
5048 tc = dev->mtu + ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN;
5049
5050#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
5051 /* FCoE traffic class uses FCOE jumbo frames */
5052 if ((dev->features & NETIF_F_FCOE_MTU) &&
5053 (tc < IXGBE_FCOE_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE) &&
5054 (pb == netdev_get_prio_tc_map(dev, adapter->fcoe.up)))
5055 tc = IXGBE_FCOE_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE;
5056#endif
5057
5058 /* Calculate delay value for device */
5059 switch (hw->mac.type) {
5060 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
5061 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
5062 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
5063 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
5064 dv_id = IXGBE_LOW_DV_X540(tc);
5065 break;
5066 default:
5067 dv_id = IXGBE_LOW_DV(tc);
5068 break;
5069 }
5070
5071 /* Delay value is calculated in bit times convert to KB */
5072 return IXGBE_BT2KB(dv_id);
5073}
5074
5075/*
5076 * ixgbe_pbthresh_setup - calculate and setup high low water marks
5077 */
5078static void ixgbe_pbthresh_setup(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5079{
5080 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5081 int num_tc = netdev_get_num_tc(adapter->netdev);
5082 int i;
5083
5084 if (!num_tc)
5085 num_tc = 1;
5086
5087 for (i = 0; i < num_tc; i++) {
5088 hw->fc.high_water[i] = ixgbe_hpbthresh(adapter, i);
5089 hw->fc.low_water[i] = ixgbe_lpbthresh(adapter, i);
5090
5091 /* Low water marks must not be larger than high water marks */
5092 if (hw->fc.low_water[i] > hw->fc.high_water[i])
5093 hw->fc.low_water[i] = 0;
5094 }
5095
5096 for (; i < MAX_TRAFFIC_CLASS; i++)
5097 hw->fc.high_water[i] = 0;
5098}
5099
5100static void ixgbe_configure_pb(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5101{
5102 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5103 int hdrm;
5104 u8 tc = netdev_get_num_tc(adapter->netdev);
5105
5106 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_HASH_CAPABLE ||
5107 adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_PERFECT_CAPABLE)
5108 hdrm = 32 << adapter->fdir_pballoc;
5109 else
5110 hdrm = 0;
5111
5112 hw->mac.ops.set_rxpba(hw, tc, hdrm, PBA_STRATEGY_EQUAL);
5113 ixgbe_pbthresh_setup(adapter);
5114}
5115
5116static void ixgbe_fdir_filter_restore(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5117{
5118 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5119 struct hlist_node *node2;
5120 struct ixgbe_fdir_filter *filter;
5121
5122 spin_lock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
5123
5124 if (!hlist_empty(&adapter->fdir_filter_list))
5125 ixgbe_fdir_set_input_mask_82599(hw, &adapter->fdir_mask);
5126
5127 hlist_for_each_entry_safe(filter, node2,
5128 &adapter->fdir_filter_list, fdir_node) {
5129 ixgbe_fdir_write_perfect_filter_82599(hw,
5130 &filter->filter,
5131 filter->sw_idx,
5132 (filter->action == IXGBE_FDIR_DROP_QUEUE) ?
5133 IXGBE_FDIR_DROP_QUEUE :
5134 adapter->rx_ring[filter->action]->reg_idx);
5135 }
5136
5137 spin_unlock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
5138}
5139
5140static void ixgbe_macvlan_set_rx_mode(struct net_device *dev, unsigned int pool,
5141 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5142{
5143 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5144 u32 vmolr;
5145
5146 /* No unicast promiscuous support for VMDQ devices. */
5147 vmolr = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VMOLR(pool));
5148 vmolr |= (IXGBE_VMOLR_ROMPE | IXGBE_VMOLR_BAM | IXGBE_VMOLR_AUPE);
5149
5150 /* clear the affected bit */
5151 vmolr &= ~IXGBE_VMOLR_MPE;
5152
5153 if (dev->flags & IFF_ALLMULTI) {
5154 vmolr |= IXGBE_VMOLR_MPE;
5155 } else {
5156 vmolr |= IXGBE_VMOLR_ROMPE;
5157 hw->mac.ops.update_mc_addr_list(hw, dev);
5158 }
5159 ixgbe_write_uc_addr_list(adapter->netdev, pool);
5160 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VMOLR(pool), vmolr);
5161}
5162
5163static void ixgbe_fwd_psrtype(struct ixgbe_fwd_adapter *vadapter)
5164{
5165 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = vadapter->real_adapter;
5166 int rss_i = adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool;
5167 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5168 u16 pool = vadapter->pool;
5169 u32 psrtype = IXGBE_PSRTYPE_TCPHDR |
5170 IXGBE_PSRTYPE_UDPHDR |
5171 IXGBE_PSRTYPE_IPV4HDR |
5172 IXGBE_PSRTYPE_L2HDR |
5173 IXGBE_PSRTYPE_IPV6HDR;
5174
5175 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
5176 return;
5177
5178 if (rss_i > 3)
5179 psrtype |= 2u << 29;
5180 else if (rss_i > 1)
5181 psrtype |= 1u << 29;
5182
5183 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_PSRTYPE(VMDQ_P(pool)), psrtype);
5184}
5185
5186/**
5187 * ixgbe_clean_rx_ring - Free Rx Buffers per Queue
5188 * @rx_ring: ring to free buffers from
5189 **/
5190static void ixgbe_clean_rx_ring(struct ixgbe_ring *rx_ring)
5191{
5192 u16 i = rx_ring->next_to_clean;
5193 struct ixgbe_rx_buffer *rx_buffer = &rx_ring->rx_buffer_info[i];
5194
5195 /* Free all the Rx ring sk_buffs */
5196 while (i != rx_ring->next_to_alloc) {
5197 if (rx_buffer->skb) {
5198 struct sk_buff *skb = rx_buffer->skb;
5199 if (IXGBE_CB(skb)->page_released)
5200 dma_unmap_page_attrs(rx_ring->dev,
5201 IXGBE_CB(skb)->dma,
5202 ixgbe_rx_pg_size(rx_ring),
5203 DMA_FROM_DEVICE,
5204 IXGBE_RX_DMA_ATTR);
5205 dev_kfree_skb(skb);
5206 }
5207
5208 /* Invalidate cache lines that may have been written to by
5209 * device so that we avoid corrupting memory.
5210 */
5211 dma_sync_single_range_for_cpu(rx_ring->dev,
5212 rx_buffer->dma,
5213 rx_buffer->page_offset,
5214 ixgbe_rx_bufsz(rx_ring),
5215 DMA_FROM_DEVICE);
5216
5217 /* free resources associated with mapping */
5218 dma_unmap_page_attrs(rx_ring->dev, rx_buffer->dma,
5219 ixgbe_rx_pg_size(rx_ring),
5220 DMA_FROM_DEVICE,
5221 IXGBE_RX_DMA_ATTR);
5222 __page_frag_cache_drain(rx_buffer->page,
5223 rx_buffer->pagecnt_bias);
5224
5225 i++;
5226 rx_buffer++;
5227 if (i == rx_ring->count) {
5228 i = 0;
5229 rx_buffer = rx_ring->rx_buffer_info;
5230 }
5231 }
5232
5233 rx_ring->next_to_alloc = 0;
5234 rx_ring->next_to_clean = 0;
5235 rx_ring->next_to_use = 0;
5236}
5237
5238static void ixgbe_disable_fwd_ring(struct ixgbe_fwd_adapter *vadapter,
5239 struct ixgbe_ring *rx_ring)
5240{
5241 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = vadapter->real_adapter;
5242 int index = rx_ring->queue_index + vadapter->rx_base_queue;
5243
5244 /* shutdown specific queue receive and wait for dma to settle */
5245 ixgbe_disable_rx_queue(adapter, rx_ring);
5246 usleep_range(10000, 20000);
5247 ixgbe_irq_disable_queues(adapter, BIT_ULL(index));
5248 ixgbe_clean_rx_ring(rx_ring);
5249 rx_ring->l2_accel_priv = NULL;
5250}
5251
5252static int ixgbe_fwd_ring_down(struct net_device *vdev,
5253 struct ixgbe_fwd_adapter *accel)
5254{
5255 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = accel->real_adapter;
5256 unsigned int rxbase = accel->rx_base_queue;
5257 unsigned int txbase = accel->tx_base_queue;
5258 int i;
5259
5260 netif_tx_stop_all_queues(vdev);
5261
5262 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool; i++) {
5263 ixgbe_disable_fwd_ring(accel, adapter->rx_ring[rxbase + i]);
5264 adapter->rx_ring[rxbase + i]->netdev = adapter->netdev;
5265 }
5266
5267 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool; i++) {
5268 adapter->tx_ring[txbase + i]->l2_accel_priv = NULL;
5269 adapter->tx_ring[txbase + i]->netdev = adapter->netdev;
5270 }
5271
5272
5273 return 0;
5274}
5275
5276static int ixgbe_fwd_ring_up(struct net_device *vdev,
5277 struct ixgbe_fwd_adapter *accel)
5278{
5279 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = accel->real_adapter;
5280 unsigned int rxbase, txbase, queues;
5281 int i, baseq, err = 0;
5282
5283 if (!test_bit(accel->pool, &adapter->fwd_bitmask))
5284 return 0;
5285
5286 baseq = accel->pool * adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool;
5287 netdev_dbg(vdev, "pool %i:%i queues %i:%i VSI bitmask %lx\n",
5288 accel->pool, adapter->num_rx_pools,
5289 baseq, baseq + adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool,
5290 adapter->fwd_bitmask);
5291
5292 accel->netdev = vdev;
5293 accel->rx_base_queue = rxbase = baseq;
5294 accel->tx_base_queue = txbase = baseq;
5295
5296 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool; i++)
5297 ixgbe_disable_fwd_ring(accel, adapter->rx_ring[rxbase + i]);
5298
5299 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool; i++) {
5300 adapter->rx_ring[rxbase + i]->netdev = vdev;
5301 adapter->rx_ring[rxbase + i]->l2_accel_priv = accel;
5302 ixgbe_configure_rx_ring(adapter, adapter->rx_ring[rxbase + i]);
5303 }
5304
5305 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool; i++) {
5306 adapter->tx_ring[txbase + i]->netdev = vdev;
5307 adapter->tx_ring[txbase + i]->l2_accel_priv = accel;
5308 }
5309
5310 queues = min_t(unsigned int,
5311 adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool, vdev->num_tx_queues);
5312 err = netif_set_real_num_tx_queues(vdev, queues);
5313 if (err)
5314 goto fwd_queue_err;
5315
5316 err = netif_set_real_num_rx_queues(vdev, queues);
5317 if (err)
5318 goto fwd_queue_err;
5319
5320 if (is_valid_ether_addr(vdev->dev_addr))
5321 ixgbe_add_mac_filter(adapter, vdev->dev_addr, accel->pool);
5322
5323 ixgbe_fwd_psrtype(accel);
5324 ixgbe_macvlan_set_rx_mode(vdev, accel->pool, adapter);
5325 return err;
5326fwd_queue_err:
5327 ixgbe_fwd_ring_down(vdev, accel);
5328 return err;
5329}
5330
5331static int ixgbe_upper_dev_walk(struct net_device *upper, void *data)
5332{
5333 if (netif_is_macvlan(upper)) {
5334 struct macvlan_dev *dfwd = netdev_priv(upper);
5335 struct ixgbe_fwd_adapter *vadapter = dfwd->fwd_priv;
5336
5337 if (dfwd->fwd_priv)
5338 ixgbe_fwd_ring_up(upper, vadapter);
5339 }
5340
5341 return 0;
5342}
5343
5344static void ixgbe_configure_dfwd(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5345{
5346 netdev_walk_all_upper_dev_rcu(adapter->netdev,
5347 ixgbe_upper_dev_walk, NULL);
5348}
5349
5350static void ixgbe_configure(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5351{
5352 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5353
5354 ixgbe_configure_pb(adapter);
5355#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
5356 ixgbe_configure_dcb(adapter);
5357#endif
5358 /*
5359 * We must restore virtualization before VLANs or else
5360 * the VLVF registers will not be populated
5361 */
5362 ixgbe_configure_virtualization(adapter);
5363
5364 ixgbe_set_rx_mode(adapter->netdev);
5365 ixgbe_restore_vlan(adapter);
5366
5367 switch (hw->mac.type) {
5368 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
5369 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
5370 hw->mac.ops.disable_rx_buff(hw);
5371 break;
5372 default:
5373 break;
5374 }
5375
5376 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_HASH_CAPABLE) {
5377 ixgbe_init_fdir_signature_82599(&adapter->hw,
5378 adapter->fdir_pballoc);
5379 } else if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_PERFECT_CAPABLE) {
5380 ixgbe_init_fdir_perfect_82599(&adapter->hw,
5381 adapter->fdir_pballoc);
5382 ixgbe_fdir_filter_restore(adapter);
5383 }
5384
5385 switch (hw->mac.type) {
5386 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
5387 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
5388 hw->mac.ops.enable_rx_buff(hw);
5389 break;
5390 default:
5391 break;
5392 }
5393
5394#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA
5395 /* configure DCA */
5396 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_DCA_CAPABLE)
5397 ixgbe_setup_dca(adapter);
5398#endif /* CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA */
5399
5400#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
5401 /* configure FCoE L2 filters, redirection table, and Rx control */
5402 ixgbe_configure_fcoe(adapter);
5403
5404#endif /* IXGBE_FCOE */
5405 ixgbe_configure_tx(adapter);
5406 ixgbe_configure_rx(adapter);
5407 ixgbe_configure_dfwd(adapter);
5408}
5409
5410/**
5411 * ixgbe_sfp_link_config - set up SFP+ link
5412 * @adapter: pointer to private adapter struct
5413 **/
5414static void ixgbe_sfp_link_config(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5415{
5416 /*
5417 * We are assuming the worst case scenario here, and that
5418 * is that an SFP was inserted/removed after the reset
5419 * but before SFP detection was enabled. As such the best
5420 * solution is to just start searching as soon as we start
5421 */
5422 if (adapter->hw.mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
5423 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_SEARCH_FOR_SFP;
5424
5425 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_SFP_NEEDS_RESET;
5426 adapter->sfp_poll_time = 0;
5427}
5428
5429/**
5430 * ixgbe_non_sfp_link_config - set up non-SFP+ link
5431 * @hw: pointer to private hardware struct
5432 *
5433 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
5434 **/
5435static int ixgbe_non_sfp_link_config(struct ixgbe_hw *hw)
5436{
5437 u32 speed;
5438 bool autoneg, link_up = false;
5439 int ret = IXGBE_ERR_LINK_SETUP;
5440
5441 if (hw->mac.ops.check_link)
5442 ret = hw->mac.ops.check_link(hw, &speed, &link_up, false);
5443
5444 if (ret)
5445 return ret;
5446
5447 speed = hw->phy.autoneg_advertised;
5448 if ((!speed) && (hw->mac.ops.get_link_capabilities))
5449 ret = hw->mac.ops.get_link_capabilities(hw, &speed,
5450 &autoneg);
5451 if (ret)
5452 return ret;
5453
5454 if (hw->mac.ops.setup_link)
5455 ret = hw->mac.ops.setup_link(hw, speed, link_up);
5456
5457 return ret;
5458}
5459
5460static void ixgbe_setup_gpie(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5461{
5462 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5463 u32 gpie = 0;
5464
5465 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED) {
5466 gpie = IXGBE_GPIE_MSIX_MODE | IXGBE_GPIE_PBA_SUPPORT |
5467 IXGBE_GPIE_OCD;
5468 gpie |= IXGBE_GPIE_EIAME;
5469 /*
5470 * use EIAM to auto-mask when MSI-X interrupt is asserted
5471 * this saves a register write for every interrupt
5472 */
5473 switch (hw->mac.type) {
5474 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
5475 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIAM, IXGBE_EICS_RTX_QUEUE);
5476 break;
5477 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
5478 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
5479 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
5480 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
5481 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
5482 default:
5483 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIAM_EX(0), 0xFFFFFFFF);
5484 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIAM_EX(1), 0xFFFFFFFF);
5485 break;
5486 }
5487 } else {
5488 /* legacy interrupts, use EIAM to auto-mask when reading EICR,
5489 * specifically only auto mask tx and rx interrupts */
5490 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIAM, IXGBE_EICS_RTX_QUEUE);
5491 }
5492
5493 /* XXX: to interrupt immediately for EICS writes, enable this */
5494 /* gpie |= IXGBE_GPIE_EIMEN; */
5495
5496 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED) {
5497 gpie &= ~IXGBE_GPIE_VTMODE_MASK;
5498
5499 switch (adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_VMDQ].mask) {
5500 case IXGBE_82599_VMDQ_8Q_MASK:
5501 gpie |= IXGBE_GPIE_VTMODE_16;
5502 break;
5503 case IXGBE_82599_VMDQ_4Q_MASK:
5504 gpie |= IXGBE_GPIE_VTMODE_32;
5505 break;
5506 default:
5507 gpie |= IXGBE_GPIE_VTMODE_64;
5508 break;
5509 }
5510 }
5511
5512 /* Enable Thermal over heat sensor interrupt */
5513 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_TEMP_SENSOR_CAPABLE) {
5514 switch (adapter->hw.mac.type) {
5515 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
5516 gpie |= IXGBE_SDP0_GPIEN_8259X;
5517 break;
5518 default:
5519 break;
5520 }
5521 }
5522
5523 /* Enable fan failure interrupt */
5524 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FAN_FAIL_CAPABLE)
5525 gpie |= IXGBE_SDP1_GPIEN(hw);
5526
5527 switch (hw->mac.type) {
5528 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
5529 gpie |= IXGBE_SDP1_GPIEN_8259X | IXGBE_SDP2_GPIEN_8259X;
5530 break;
5531 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
5532 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
5533 gpie |= IXGBE_SDP0_GPIEN_X540;
5534 break;
5535 default:
5536 break;
5537 }
5538
5539 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_GPIE, gpie);
5540}
5541
5542static void ixgbe_up_complete(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5543{
5544 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5545 int err;
5546 u32 ctrl_ext;
5547
5548 ixgbe_get_hw_control(adapter);
5549 ixgbe_setup_gpie(adapter);
5550
5551 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED)
5552 ixgbe_configure_msix(adapter);
5553 else
5554 ixgbe_configure_msi_and_legacy(adapter);
5555
5556 /* enable the optics for 82599 SFP+ fiber */
5557 if (hw->mac.ops.enable_tx_laser)
5558 hw->mac.ops.enable_tx_laser(hw);
5559
5560 if (hw->phy.ops.set_phy_power)
5561 hw->phy.ops.set_phy_power(hw, true);
5562
5563 smp_mb__before_atomic();
5564 clear_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state);
5565 ixgbe_napi_enable_all(adapter);
5566
5567 if (ixgbe_is_sfp(hw)) {
5568 ixgbe_sfp_link_config(adapter);
5569 } else {
5570 err = ixgbe_non_sfp_link_config(hw);
5571 if (err)
5572 e_err(probe, "link_config FAILED %d\n", err);
5573 }
5574
5575 /* clear any pending interrupts, may auto mask */
5576 IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_EICR);
5577 ixgbe_irq_enable(adapter, true, true);
5578
5579 /*
5580 * If this adapter has a fan, check to see if we had a failure
5581 * before we enabled the interrupt.
5582 */
5583 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FAN_FAIL_CAPABLE) {
5584 u32 esdp = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_ESDP);
5585 if (esdp & IXGBE_ESDP_SDP1)
5586 e_crit(drv, "Fan has stopped, replace the adapter\n");
5587 }
5588
5589 /* bring the link up in the watchdog, this could race with our first
5590 * link up interrupt but shouldn't be a problem */
5591 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE;
5592 adapter->link_check_timeout = jiffies;
5593 mod_timer(&adapter->service_timer, jiffies);
5594
5595 /* Set PF Reset Done bit so PF/VF Mail Ops can work */
5596 ctrl_ext = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_CTRL_EXT);
5597 ctrl_ext |= IXGBE_CTRL_EXT_PFRSTD;
5598 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_CTRL_EXT, ctrl_ext);
5599}
5600
5601void ixgbe_reinit_locked(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5602{
5603 WARN_ON(in_interrupt());
5604 /* put off any impending NetWatchDogTimeout */
5605 netif_trans_update(adapter->netdev);
5606
5607 while (test_and_set_bit(__IXGBE_RESETTING, &adapter->state))
5608 usleep_range(1000, 2000);
5609 if (adapter->hw.phy.type == ixgbe_phy_fw)
5610 ixgbe_watchdog_link_is_down(adapter);
5611 ixgbe_down(adapter);
5612 /*
5613 * If SR-IOV enabled then wait a bit before bringing the adapter
5614 * back up to give the VFs time to respond to the reset. The
5615 * two second wait is based upon the watchdog timer cycle in
5616 * the VF driver.
5617 */
5618 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED)
5619 msleep(2000);
5620 ixgbe_up(adapter);
5621 clear_bit(__IXGBE_RESETTING, &adapter->state);
5622}
5623
5624void ixgbe_up(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5625{
5626 /* hardware has been reset, we need to reload some things */
5627 ixgbe_configure(adapter);
5628
5629 ixgbe_up_complete(adapter);
5630}
5631
5632void ixgbe_reset(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5633{
5634 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5635 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
5636 int err;
5637
5638 if (ixgbe_removed(hw->hw_addr))
5639 return;
5640 /* lock SFP init bit to prevent race conditions with the watchdog */
5641 while (test_and_set_bit(__IXGBE_IN_SFP_INIT, &adapter->state))
5642 usleep_range(1000, 2000);
5643
5644 /* clear all SFP and link config related flags while holding SFP_INIT */
5645 adapter->flags2 &= ~(IXGBE_FLAG2_SEARCH_FOR_SFP |
5646 IXGBE_FLAG2_SFP_NEEDS_RESET);
5647 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_CONFIG;
5648
5649 err = hw->mac.ops.init_hw(hw);
5650 switch (err) {
5651 case 0:
5652 case IXGBE_ERR_SFP_NOT_PRESENT:
5653 case IXGBE_ERR_SFP_NOT_SUPPORTED:
5654 break;
5655 case IXGBE_ERR_MASTER_REQUESTS_PENDING:
5656 e_dev_err("master disable timed out\n");
5657 break;
5658 case IXGBE_ERR_EEPROM_VERSION:
5659 /* We are running on a pre-production device, log a warning */
5660 e_dev_warn("This device is a pre-production adapter/LOM. "
5661 "Please be aware there may be issues associated with "
5662 "your hardware. If you are experiencing problems "
5663 "please contact your Intel or hardware "
5664 "representative who provided you with this "
5665 "hardware.\n");
5666 break;
5667 default:
5668 e_dev_err("Hardware Error: %d\n", err);
5669 }
5670
5671 clear_bit(__IXGBE_IN_SFP_INIT, &adapter->state);
5672
5673 /* flush entries out of MAC table */
5674 ixgbe_flush_sw_mac_table(adapter);
5675 __dev_uc_unsync(netdev, NULL);
5676
5677 /* do not flush user set addresses */
5678 ixgbe_mac_set_default_filter(adapter);
5679
5680 /* update SAN MAC vmdq pool selection */
5681 if (hw->mac.san_mac_rar_index)
5682 hw->mac.ops.set_vmdq_san_mac(hw, VMDQ_P(0));
5683
5684 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_PTP_RUNNING, &adapter->state))
5685 ixgbe_ptp_reset(adapter);
5686
5687 if (hw->phy.ops.set_phy_power) {
5688 if (!netif_running(adapter->netdev) && !adapter->wol)
5689 hw->phy.ops.set_phy_power(hw, false);
5690 else
5691 hw->phy.ops.set_phy_power(hw, true);
5692 }
5693}
5694
5695/**
5696 * ixgbe_clean_tx_ring - Free Tx Buffers
5697 * @tx_ring: ring to be cleaned
5698 **/
5699static void ixgbe_clean_tx_ring(struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring)
5700{
5701 u16 i = tx_ring->next_to_clean;
5702 struct ixgbe_tx_buffer *tx_buffer = &tx_ring->tx_buffer_info[i];
5703
5704 while (i != tx_ring->next_to_use) {
5705 union ixgbe_adv_tx_desc *eop_desc, *tx_desc;
5706
5707 /* Free all the Tx ring sk_buffs */
5708 if (ring_is_xdp(tx_ring))
5709 page_frag_free(tx_buffer->data);
5710 else
5711 dev_kfree_skb_any(tx_buffer->skb);
5712
5713 /* unmap skb header data */
5714 dma_unmap_single(tx_ring->dev,
5715 dma_unmap_addr(tx_buffer, dma),
5716 dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len),
5717 DMA_TO_DEVICE);
5718
5719 /* check for eop_desc to determine the end of the packet */
5720 eop_desc = tx_buffer->next_to_watch;
5721 tx_desc = IXGBE_TX_DESC(tx_ring, i);
5722
5723 /* unmap remaining buffers */
5724 while (tx_desc != eop_desc) {
5725 tx_buffer++;
5726 tx_desc++;
5727 i++;
5728 if (unlikely(i == tx_ring->count)) {
5729 i = 0;
5730 tx_buffer = tx_ring->tx_buffer_info;
5731 tx_desc = IXGBE_TX_DESC(tx_ring, 0);
5732 }
5733
5734 /* unmap any remaining paged data */
5735 if (dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len))
5736 dma_unmap_page(tx_ring->dev,
5737 dma_unmap_addr(tx_buffer, dma),
5738 dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len),
5739 DMA_TO_DEVICE);
5740 }
5741
5742 /* move us one more past the eop_desc for start of next pkt */
5743 tx_buffer++;
5744 i++;
5745 if (unlikely(i == tx_ring->count)) {
5746 i = 0;
5747 tx_buffer = tx_ring->tx_buffer_info;
5748 }
5749 }
5750
5751 /* reset BQL for queue */
5752 if (!ring_is_xdp(tx_ring))
5753 netdev_tx_reset_queue(txring_txq(tx_ring));
5754
5755 /* reset next_to_use and next_to_clean */
5756 tx_ring->next_to_use = 0;
5757 tx_ring->next_to_clean = 0;
5758}
5759
5760/**
5761 * ixgbe_clean_all_rx_rings - Free Rx Buffers for all queues
5762 * @adapter: board private structure
5763 **/
5764static void ixgbe_clean_all_rx_rings(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5765{
5766 int i;
5767
5768 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++)
5769 ixgbe_clean_rx_ring(adapter->rx_ring[i]);
5770}
5771
5772/**
5773 * ixgbe_clean_all_tx_rings - Free Tx Buffers for all queues
5774 * @adapter: board private structure
5775 **/
5776static void ixgbe_clean_all_tx_rings(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5777{
5778 int i;
5779
5780 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++)
5781 ixgbe_clean_tx_ring(adapter->tx_ring[i]);
5782 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_xdp_queues; i++)
5783 ixgbe_clean_tx_ring(adapter->xdp_ring[i]);
5784}
5785
5786static void ixgbe_fdir_filter_exit(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5787{
5788 struct hlist_node *node2;
5789 struct ixgbe_fdir_filter *filter;
5790
5791 spin_lock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
5792
5793 hlist_for_each_entry_safe(filter, node2,
5794 &adapter->fdir_filter_list, fdir_node) {
5795 hlist_del(&filter->fdir_node);
5796 kfree(filter);
5797 }
5798 adapter->fdir_filter_count = 0;
5799
5800 spin_unlock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
5801}
5802
5803static int ixgbe_disable_macvlan(struct net_device *upper, void *data)
5804{
5805 if (netif_is_macvlan(upper)) {
5806 struct macvlan_dev *vlan = netdev_priv(upper);
5807
5808 if (vlan->fwd_priv) {
5809 netif_tx_stop_all_queues(upper);
5810 netif_carrier_off(upper);
5811 netif_tx_disable(upper);
5812 }
5813 }
5814
5815 return 0;
5816}
5817
5818void ixgbe_down(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5819{
5820 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
5821 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5822 int i;
5823
5824 /* signal that we are down to the interrupt handler */
5825 if (test_and_set_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state))
5826 return; /* do nothing if already down */
5827
5828 /* disable receives */
5829 hw->mac.ops.disable_rx(hw);
5830
5831 /* disable all enabled rx queues */
5832 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++)
5833 /* this call also flushes the previous write */
5834 ixgbe_disable_rx_queue(adapter, adapter->rx_ring[i]);
5835
5836 usleep_range(10000, 20000);
5837
5838 /* synchronize_sched() needed for pending XDP buffers to drain */
5839 if (adapter->xdp_ring[0])
5840 synchronize_sched();
5841 netif_tx_stop_all_queues(netdev);
5842
5843 /* call carrier off first to avoid false dev_watchdog timeouts */
5844 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
5845 netif_tx_disable(netdev);
5846
5847 /* disable any upper devices */
5848 netdev_walk_all_upper_dev_rcu(adapter->netdev,
5849 ixgbe_disable_macvlan, NULL);
5850
5851 ixgbe_irq_disable(adapter);
5852
5853 ixgbe_napi_disable_all(adapter);
5854
5855 clear_bit(__IXGBE_RESET_REQUESTED, &adapter->state);
5856 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_FDIR_REQUIRES_REINIT;
5857 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE;
5858
5859 del_timer_sync(&adapter->service_timer);
5860
5861 if (adapter->num_vfs) {
5862 /* Clear EITR Select mapping */
5863 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_EITRSEL, 0);
5864
5865 /* Mark all the VFs as inactive */
5866 for (i = 0 ; i < adapter->num_vfs; i++)
5867 adapter->vfinfo[i].clear_to_send = false;
5868
5869 /* ping all the active vfs to let them know we are going down */
5870 ixgbe_ping_all_vfs(adapter);
5871
5872 /* Disable all VFTE/VFRE TX/RX */
5873 ixgbe_disable_tx_rx(adapter);
5874 }
5875
5876 /* disable transmits in the hardware now that interrupts are off */
5877 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++) {
5878 u8 reg_idx = adapter->tx_ring[i]->reg_idx;
5879 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_TXDCTL(reg_idx), IXGBE_TXDCTL_SWFLSH);
5880 }
5881 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_xdp_queues; i++) {
5882 u8 reg_idx = adapter->xdp_ring[i]->reg_idx;
5883
5884 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_TXDCTL(reg_idx), IXGBE_TXDCTL_SWFLSH);
5885 }
5886
5887 /* Disable the Tx DMA engine on 82599 and later MAC */
5888 switch (hw->mac.type) {
5889 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
5890 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
5891 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
5892 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
5893 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
5894 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_DMATXCTL,
5895 (IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_DMATXCTL) &
5896 ~IXGBE_DMATXCTL_TE));
5897 break;
5898 default:
5899 break;
5900 }
5901
5902 if (!pci_channel_offline(adapter->pdev))
5903 ixgbe_reset(adapter);
5904
5905 /* power down the optics for 82599 SFP+ fiber */
5906 if (hw->mac.ops.disable_tx_laser)
5907 hw->mac.ops.disable_tx_laser(hw);
5908
5909 ixgbe_clean_all_tx_rings(adapter);
5910 ixgbe_clean_all_rx_rings(adapter);
5911}
5912
5913/**
5914 * ixgbe_eee_capable - helper function to determine EEE support on X550
5915 * @adapter: board private structure
5916 */
5917static void ixgbe_set_eee_capable(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5918{
5919 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5920
5921 switch (hw->device_id) {
5922 case IXGBE_DEV_ID_X550EM_A_1G_T:
5923 case IXGBE_DEV_ID_X550EM_A_1G_T_L:
5924 if (!hw->phy.eee_speeds_supported)
5925 break;
5926 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_EEE_CAPABLE;
5927 if (!hw->phy.eee_speeds_advertised)
5928 break;
5929 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_EEE_ENABLED;
5930 break;
5931 default:
5932 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_EEE_CAPABLE;
5933 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_EEE_ENABLED;
5934 break;
5935 }
5936}

5938/**
5939 * ixgbe_tx_timeout - Respond to a Tx Hang
5940 * @netdev: network interface device structure
5941 **/
5942static void ixgbe_tx_timeout(struct net_device *netdev)
5943{
5944 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
5945
5946 /* Do the reset outside of interrupt context */
5947 ixgbe_tx_timeout_reset(adapter);
5948}
5949
5950#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
5951static void ixgbe_init_dcb(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
5952{
5953 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5954 struct tc_configuration *tc;
5955 int j;
5956
5957 switch (hw->mac.type) {
5958 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
5959 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
5960 adapter->dcb_cfg.num_tcs.pg_tcs = MAX_TRAFFIC_CLASS;
5961 adapter->dcb_cfg.num_tcs.pfc_tcs = MAX_TRAFFIC_CLASS;
5962 break;
5963 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
5964 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
5965 adapter->dcb_cfg.num_tcs.pg_tcs = X540_TRAFFIC_CLASS;
5966 adapter->dcb_cfg.num_tcs.pfc_tcs = X540_TRAFFIC_CLASS;
5967 break;
5968 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
5969 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
5970 default:
5971 adapter->dcb_cfg.num_tcs.pg_tcs = DEF_TRAFFIC_CLASS;
5972 adapter->dcb_cfg.num_tcs.pfc_tcs = DEF_TRAFFIC_CLASS;
5973 break;
5974 }
5975
5976 /* Configure DCB traffic classes */
5977 for (j = 0; j < MAX_TRAFFIC_CLASS; j++) {
5978 tc = &adapter->dcb_cfg.tc_config[j];
5979 tc->path[DCB_TX_CONFIG].bwg_id = 0;
5980 tc->path[DCB_TX_CONFIG].bwg_percent = 12 + (j & 1);
5981 tc->path[DCB_RX_CONFIG].bwg_id = 0;
5982 tc->path[DCB_RX_CONFIG].bwg_percent = 12 + (j & 1);
5983 tc->dcb_pfc = pfc_disabled;
5984 }
5985
5986 /* Initialize default user to priority mapping, UPx->TC0 */
5987 tc = &adapter->dcb_cfg.tc_config[0];
5988 tc->path[DCB_TX_CONFIG].up_to_tc_bitmap = 0xFF;
5989 tc->path[DCB_RX_CONFIG].up_to_tc_bitmap = 0xFF;
5990
5991 adapter->dcb_cfg.bw_percentage[DCB_TX_CONFIG][0] = 100;
5992 adapter->dcb_cfg.bw_percentage[DCB_RX_CONFIG][0] = 100;
5993 adapter->dcb_cfg.pfc_mode_enable = false;
5994 adapter->dcb_set_bitmap = 0x00;
5995 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE)
5996 adapter->dcbx_cap = DCB_CAP_DCBX_HOST | DCB_CAP_DCBX_VER_CEE;
5997 memcpy(&adapter->temp_dcb_cfg, &adapter->dcb_cfg,
5998 sizeof(adapter->temp_dcb_cfg));
5999}
6000#endif
6001
6002/**
6003 * ixgbe_sw_init - Initialize general software structures (struct ixgbe_adapter)
6004 * @adapter: board private structure to initialize
6005 *
6006 * ixgbe_sw_init initializes the Adapter private data structure.
6007 * Fields are initialized based on PCI device information and
6008 * OS network device settings (MTU size).
6009 **/
6010static int ixgbe_sw_init(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
6011 const struct ixgbe_info *ii)
6012{
6013 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6014 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
6015 unsigned int rss, fdir;
6016 u32 fwsm;
6017 int i;
6018
6019 /* PCI config space info */
6020
6021 hw->vendor_id = pdev->vendor;
6022 hw->device_id = pdev->device;
6023 hw->revision_id = pdev->revision;
6024 hw->subsystem_vendor_id = pdev->subsystem_vendor;
6025 hw->subsystem_device_id = pdev->subsystem_device;
6026
6027 /* get_invariants needs the device IDs */
6028 ii->get_invariants(hw);
6029
6030 /* Set common capability flags and settings */
6031 rss = min_t(int, ixgbe_max_rss_indices(adapter), num_online_cpus());
6032 adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_RSS].limit = rss;
6033 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_CAPABLE;
6034 adapter->max_q_vectors = MAX_Q_VECTORS_82599;
6035 adapter->atr_sample_rate = 20;
6036 fdir = min_t(int, IXGBE_MAX_FDIR_INDICES, num_online_cpus());
6037 adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_FDIR].limit = fdir;
6038 adapter->fdir_pballoc = IXGBE_FDIR_PBALLOC_64K;
6039#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA
6040 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_DCA_CAPABLE;
6041#endif
6042#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
6043 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE;
6044 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED;
6045#endif
6046#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
6047 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_FCOE_CAPABLE;
6048 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_FCOE_ENABLED;
6049#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
6050 /* Default traffic class to use for FCoE */
6051 adapter->fcoe.up = IXGBE_FCOE_DEFTC;
6052#endif /* CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB */
6053#endif /* IXGBE_FCOE */
6054
6055 /* initialize static ixgbe jump table entries */
6056 adapter->jump_tables[0] = kzalloc(sizeof(*adapter->jump_tables[0]),
6057 GFP_KERNEL);
6058 if (!adapter->jump_tables[0])
6059 return -ENOMEM;
6060 adapter->jump_tables[0]->mat = ixgbe_ipv4_fields;
6061
6062 for (i = 1; i < IXGBE_MAX_LINK_HANDLE; i++)
6063 adapter->jump_tables[i] = NULL;
6064
6065 adapter->mac_table = kzalloc(sizeof(struct ixgbe_mac_addr) *
6066 hw->mac.num_rar_entries,
6067 GFP_ATOMIC);
6068 if (!adapter->mac_table)
6069 return -ENOMEM;
6070
6071 if (ixgbe_init_rss_key(adapter))
6072 return -ENOMEM;
6073
6074 /* Set MAC specific capability flags and exceptions */
6075 switch (hw->mac.type) {
6076 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
6077 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_CAPABLE;
6078
6079 if (hw->device_id == IXGBE_DEV_ID_82598AT)
6080 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_FAN_FAIL_CAPABLE;
6081
6082 adapter->max_q_vectors = MAX_Q_VECTORS_82598;
6083 adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_FDIR].limit = 0;
6084 adapter->atr_sample_rate = 0;
6085 adapter->fdir_pballoc = 0;
6086#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
6087 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_FCOE_CAPABLE;
6088 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_FCOE_ENABLED;
6089#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
6090 adapter->fcoe.up = 0;
6091#endif /* IXGBE_DCB */
6092#endif /* IXGBE_FCOE */
6093 break;
6094 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
6095 if (hw->device_id == IXGBE_DEV_ID_82599_T3_LOM)
6096 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_TEMP_SENSOR_CAPABLE;
6097 break;
6098 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
6099 fwsm = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FWSM(hw));
6100 if (fwsm & IXGBE_FWSM_TS_ENABLED)
6101 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_TEMP_SENSOR_CAPABLE;
6102 break;
6103 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
6104 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_GENEVE_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE;
6105 switch (hw->device_id) {
6106 case IXGBE_DEV_ID_X550EM_A_1G_T:
6107 case IXGBE_DEV_ID_X550EM_A_1G_T_L:
6108 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_TEMP_SENSOR_CAPABLE;
6109 break;
6110 default:
6111 break;
6112 }
6113 /* fall through */
6114 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
6115#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
6116 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE;
6117#endif
6118#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
6119 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_FCOE_CAPABLE;
6120#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
6121 adapter->fcoe.up = 0;
6122#endif /* IXGBE_DCB */
6123#endif /* IXGBE_FCOE */
6124 /* Fall Through */
6125 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
6126 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_X550)
6127 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_TEMP_SENSOR_CAPABLE;
6128#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA
6129 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_DCA_CAPABLE;
6130#endif
6131 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_VXLAN_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE;
6132 break;
6133 default:
6134 break;
6135 }
6136
6137#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
6138 /* FCoE support exists, always init the FCoE lock */
6139 spin_lock_init(&adapter->fcoe.lock);
6140
6141#endif
6142 /* n-tuple support exists, always init our spinlock */
6143 spin_lock_init(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
6144
6145#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
6146 ixgbe_init_dcb(adapter);
6147#endif
6148
6149 /* default flow control settings */
6150 hw->fc.requested_mode = ixgbe_fc_full;
6151 hw->fc.current_mode = ixgbe_fc_full; /* init for ethtool output */
6152 ixgbe_pbthresh_setup(adapter);
6153 hw->fc.pause_time = IXGBE_DEFAULT_FCPAUSE;
6154 hw->fc.send_xon = true;
6155 hw->fc.disable_fc_autoneg = ixgbe_device_supports_autoneg_fc(hw);
6156
6157#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
6158 if (max_vfs > 0)
6159 e_dev_warn("Enabling SR-IOV VFs using the max_vfs module parameter is deprecated - please use the pci sysfs interface instead.\n");
6160
6161 /* assign number of SR-IOV VFs */
6162 if (hw->mac.type != ixgbe_mac_82598EB) {
6163 if (max_vfs > IXGBE_MAX_VFS_DRV_LIMIT) {
6164 max_vfs = 0;
6165 e_dev_warn("max_vfs parameter out of range. Not assigning any SR-IOV VFs\n");
6166 }
6167 }
6168#endif /* CONFIG_PCI_IOV */
6169
6170 /* enable itr by default in dynamic mode */
6171 adapter->rx_itr_setting = 1;
6172 adapter->tx_itr_setting = 1;
6173
6174 /* set default ring sizes */
6175 adapter->tx_ring_count = IXGBE_DEFAULT_TXD;
6176 adapter->rx_ring_count = IXGBE_DEFAULT_RXD;
6177
6178 /* set default work limits */
6179 adapter->tx_work_limit = IXGBE_DEFAULT_TX_WORK;
6180
6181 /* initialize eeprom parameters */
6182 if (ixgbe_init_eeprom_params_generic(hw)) {
6183 e_dev_err("EEPROM initialization failed\n");
6184 return -EIO;
6185 }
6186
6187 /* PF holds first pool slot */
6188 set_bit(0, &adapter->fwd_bitmask);
6189 set_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state);
6190
6191 return 0;
6192}
6193
6194/**
6195 * ixgbe_setup_tx_resources - allocate Tx resources (Descriptors)
6196 * @tx_ring: tx descriptor ring (for a specific queue) to setup
6197 *
6198 * Return 0 on success, negative on failure
6199 **/
6200int ixgbe_setup_tx_resources(struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring)
6201{
6202 struct device *dev = tx_ring->dev;
6203 int orig_node = dev_to_node(dev);
6204 int ring_node = -1;
6205 int size;
6206
6207 size = sizeof(struct ixgbe_tx_buffer) * tx_ring->count;
6208
6209 if (tx_ring->q_vector)
6210 ring_node = tx_ring->q_vector->numa_node;
6211
6212 tx_ring->tx_buffer_info = vmalloc_node(size, ring_node);
6213 if (!tx_ring->tx_buffer_info)
6214 tx_ring->tx_buffer_info = vmalloc(size);
6215 if (!tx_ring->tx_buffer_info)
6216 goto err;
6217
6218 /* round up to nearest 4K */
6219 tx_ring->size = tx_ring->count * sizeof(union ixgbe_adv_tx_desc);
6220 tx_ring->size = ALIGN(tx_ring->size, 4096);
6221
6222 set_dev_node(dev, ring_node);
6223 tx_ring->desc = dma_alloc_coherent(dev,
6224 tx_ring->size,
6225 &tx_ring->dma,
6226 GFP_KERNEL);
6227 set_dev_node(dev, orig_node);
6228 if (!tx_ring->desc)
6229 tx_ring->desc = dma_alloc_coherent(dev, tx_ring->size,
6230 &tx_ring->dma, GFP_KERNEL);
6231 if (!tx_ring->desc)
6232 goto err;
6233
6234 tx_ring->next_to_use = 0;
6235 tx_ring->next_to_clean = 0;
6236 return 0;
6237
6238err:
6239 vfree(tx_ring->tx_buffer_info);
6240 tx_ring->tx_buffer_info = NULL;
6241 dev_err(dev, "Unable to allocate memory for the Tx descriptor ring\n");
6242 return -ENOMEM;
6243}
6244
6245/**
6246 * ixgbe_setup_all_tx_resources - allocate all queues Tx resources
6247 * @adapter: board private structure
6248 *
6249 * If this function returns with an error, then it's possible one or
6250 * more of the rings is populated (while the rest are not). It is the
6251 * callers duty to clean those orphaned rings.
6252 *
6253 * Return 0 on success, negative on failure
6254 **/
6255static int ixgbe_setup_all_tx_resources(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
6256{
6257 int i, j = 0, err = 0;
6258
6259 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++) {
6260 err = ixgbe_setup_tx_resources(adapter->tx_ring[i]);
6261 if (!err)
6262 continue;
6263
6264 e_err(probe, "Allocation for Tx Queue %u failed\n", i);
6265 goto err_setup_tx;
6266 }
6267 for (j = 0; j < adapter->num_xdp_queues; j++) {
6268 err = ixgbe_setup_tx_resources(adapter->xdp_ring[j]);
6269 if (!err)
6270 continue;
6271
6272 e_err(probe, "Allocation for Tx Queue %u failed\n", j);
6273 goto err_setup_tx;
6274 }
6275
6276 return 0;
6277err_setup_tx:
6278 /* rewind the index freeing the rings as we go */
6279 while (j--)
6280 ixgbe_free_tx_resources(adapter->xdp_ring[j]);
6281 while (i--)
6282 ixgbe_free_tx_resources(adapter->tx_ring[i]);
6283 return err;
6284}
6285
6286/**
6287 * ixgbe_setup_rx_resources - allocate Rx resources (Descriptors)
6288 * @rx_ring: rx descriptor ring (for a specific queue) to setup
6289 *
6290 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
6291 **/
6292int ixgbe_setup_rx_resources(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
6293 struct ixgbe_ring *rx_ring)
6294{
6295 struct device *dev = rx_ring->dev;
6296 int orig_node = dev_to_node(dev);
6297 int ring_node = -1;
6298 int size;
6299
6300 size = sizeof(struct ixgbe_rx_buffer) * rx_ring->count;
6301
6302 if (rx_ring->q_vector)
6303 ring_node = rx_ring->q_vector->numa_node;
6304
6305 rx_ring->rx_buffer_info = vmalloc_node(size, ring_node);
6306 if (!rx_ring->rx_buffer_info)
6307 rx_ring->rx_buffer_info = vmalloc(size);
6308 if (!rx_ring->rx_buffer_info)
6309 goto err;
6310
6311 /* Round up to nearest 4K */
6312 rx_ring->size = rx_ring->count * sizeof(union ixgbe_adv_rx_desc);
6313 rx_ring->size = ALIGN(rx_ring->size, 4096);
6314
6315 set_dev_node(dev, ring_node);
6316 rx_ring->desc = dma_alloc_coherent(dev,
6317 rx_ring->size,
6318 &rx_ring->dma,
6319 GFP_KERNEL);
6320 set_dev_node(dev, orig_node);
6321 if (!rx_ring->desc)
6322 rx_ring->desc = dma_alloc_coherent(dev, rx_ring->size,
6323 &rx_ring->dma, GFP_KERNEL);
6324 if (!rx_ring->desc)
6325 goto err;
6326
6327 rx_ring->next_to_clean = 0;
6328 rx_ring->next_to_use = 0;
6329
6330 rx_ring->xdp_prog = adapter->xdp_prog;
6331
6332 return 0;
6333err:
6334 vfree(rx_ring->rx_buffer_info);
6335 rx_ring->rx_buffer_info = NULL;
6336 dev_err(dev, "Unable to allocate memory for the Rx descriptor ring\n");
6337 return -ENOMEM;
6338}
6339
6340/**
6341 * ixgbe_setup_all_rx_resources - allocate all queues Rx resources
6342 * @adapter: board private structure
6343 *
6344 * If this function returns with an error, then it's possible one or
6345 * more of the rings is populated (while the rest are not). It is the
6346 * callers duty to clean those orphaned rings.
6347 *
6348 * Return 0 on success, negative on failure
6349 **/
6350static int ixgbe_setup_all_rx_resources(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
6351{
6352 int i, err = 0;
6353
6354 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++) {
6355 err = ixgbe_setup_rx_resources(adapter, adapter->rx_ring[i]);
6356 if (!err)
6357 continue;
6358
6359 e_err(probe, "Allocation for Rx Queue %u failed\n", i);
6360 goto err_setup_rx;
6361 }
6362
6363#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
6364 err = ixgbe_setup_fcoe_ddp_resources(adapter);
6365 if (!err)
6366#endif
6367 return 0;
6368err_setup_rx:
6369 /* rewind the index freeing the rings as we go */
6370 while (i--)
6371 ixgbe_free_rx_resources(adapter->rx_ring[i]);
6372 return err;
6373}
6374
6375/**
6376 * ixgbe_free_tx_resources - Free Tx Resources per Queue
6377 * @tx_ring: Tx descriptor ring for a specific queue
6378 *
6379 * Free all transmit software resources
6380 **/
6381void ixgbe_free_tx_resources(struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring)
6382{
6383 ixgbe_clean_tx_ring(tx_ring);
6384
6385 vfree(tx_ring->tx_buffer_info);
6386 tx_ring->tx_buffer_info = NULL;
6387
6388 /* if not set, then don't free */
6389 if (!tx_ring->desc)
6390 return;
6391
6392 dma_free_coherent(tx_ring->dev, tx_ring->size,
6393 tx_ring->desc, tx_ring->dma);
6394
6395 tx_ring->desc = NULL;
6396}
6397
6398/**
6399 * ixgbe_free_all_tx_resources - Free Tx Resources for All Queues
6400 * @adapter: board private structure
6401 *
6402 * Free all transmit software resources
6403 **/
6404static void ixgbe_free_all_tx_resources(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
6405{
6406 int i;
6407
6408 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++)
6409 if (adapter->tx_ring[i]->desc)
6410 ixgbe_free_tx_resources(adapter->tx_ring[i]);
6411 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_xdp_queues; i++)
6412 if (adapter->xdp_ring[i]->desc)
6413 ixgbe_free_tx_resources(adapter->xdp_ring[i]);
6414}
6415
6416/**
6417 * ixgbe_free_rx_resources - Free Rx Resources
6418 * @rx_ring: ring to clean the resources from
6419 *
6420 * Free all receive software resources
6421 **/
6422void ixgbe_free_rx_resources(struct ixgbe_ring *rx_ring)
6423{
6424 ixgbe_clean_rx_ring(rx_ring);
6425
6426 rx_ring->xdp_prog = NULL;
6427 vfree(rx_ring->rx_buffer_info);
6428 rx_ring->rx_buffer_info = NULL;
6429
6430 /* if not set, then don't free */
6431 if (!rx_ring->desc)
6432 return;
6433
6434 dma_free_coherent(rx_ring->dev, rx_ring->size,
6435 rx_ring->desc, rx_ring->dma);
6436
6437 rx_ring->desc = NULL;
6438}
6439
6440/**
6441 * ixgbe_free_all_rx_resources - Free Rx Resources for All Queues
6442 * @adapter: board private structure
6443 *
6444 * Free all receive software resources
6445 **/
6446static void ixgbe_free_all_rx_resources(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
6447{
6448 int i;
6449
6450#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
6451 ixgbe_free_fcoe_ddp_resources(adapter);
6452
6453#endif
6454 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++)
6455 if (adapter->rx_ring[i]->desc)
6456 ixgbe_free_rx_resources(adapter->rx_ring[i]);
6457}
6458
6459/**
6460 * ixgbe_change_mtu - Change the Maximum Transfer Unit
6461 * @netdev: network interface device structure
6462 * @new_mtu: new value for maximum frame size
6463 *
6464 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
6465 **/
6466static int ixgbe_change_mtu(struct net_device *netdev, int new_mtu)
6467{
6468 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
6469
6470 /*
6471 * For 82599EB we cannot allow legacy VFs to enable their receive
6472 * paths when MTU greater than 1500 is configured. So display a
6473 * warning that legacy VFs will be disabled.
6474 */
6475 if ((adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED) &&
6476 (adapter->hw.mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82599EB) &&
6477 (new_mtu > ETH_DATA_LEN))
6478 e_warn(probe, "Setting MTU > 1500 will disable legacy VFs\n");
6479
6480 e_info(probe, "changing MTU from %d to %d\n", netdev->mtu, new_mtu);
6481
6482 /* must set new MTU before calling down or up */
6483 netdev->mtu = new_mtu;
6484
6485 if (netif_running(netdev))
6486 ixgbe_reinit_locked(adapter);
6487
6488 return 0;
6489}
6490
6491/**
6492 * ixgbe_open - Called when a network interface is made active
6493 * @netdev: network interface device structure
6494 *
6495 * Returns 0 on success, negative value on failure
6496 *
6497 * The open entry point is called when a network interface is made
6498 * active by the system (IFF_UP). At this point all resources needed
6499 * for transmit and receive operations are allocated, the interrupt
6500 * handler is registered with the OS, the watchdog timer is started,
6501 * and the stack is notified that the interface is ready.
6502 **/
6503int ixgbe_open(struct net_device *netdev)
6504{
6505 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
6506 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6507 int err, queues;
6508
6509 /* disallow open during test */
6510 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_TESTING, &adapter->state))
6511 return -EBUSY;
6512
6513 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
6514
6515 /* allocate transmit descriptors */
6516 err = ixgbe_setup_all_tx_resources(adapter);
6517 if (err)
6518 goto err_setup_tx;
6519
6520 /* allocate receive descriptors */
6521 err = ixgbe_setup_all_rx_resources(adapter);
6522 if (err)
6523 goto err_setup_rx;
6524
6525 ixgbe_configure(adapter);
6526
6527 err = ixgbe_request_irq(adapter);
6528 if (err)
6529 goto err_req_irq;
6530
6531 /* Notify the stack of the actual queue counts. */
6532 if (adapter->num_rx_pools > 1)
6533 queues = adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool;
6534 else
6535 queues = adapter->num_tx_queues;
6536
6537 err = netif_set_real_num_tx_queues(netdev, queues);
6538 if (err)
6539 goto err_set_queues;
6540
6541 if (adapter->num_rx_pools > 1 &&
6542 adapter->num_rx_queues > IXGBE_MAX_L2A_QUEUES)
6543 queues = IXGBE_MAX_L2A_QUEUES;
6544 else
6545 queues = adapter->num_rx_queues;
6546 err = netif_set_real_num_rx_queues(netdev, queues);
6547 if (err)
6548 goto err_set_queues;
6549
6550 ixgbe_ptp_init(adapter);
6551
6552 ixgbe_up_complete(adapter);
6553
6554 ixgbe_clear_udp_tunnel_port(adapter, IXGBE_VXLANCTRL_ALL_UDPPORT_MASK);
6555 udp_tunnel_get_rx_info(netdev);
6556
6557 return 0;
6558
6559err_set_queues:
6560 ixgbe_free_irq(adapter);
6561err_req_irq:
6562 ixgbe_free_all_rx_resources(adapter);
6563 if (hw->phy.ops.set_phy_power && !adapter->wol)
6564 hw->phy.ops.set_phy_power(&adapter->hw, false);
6565err_setup_rx:
6566 ixgbe_free_all_tx_resources(adapter);
6567err_setup_tx:
6568 ixgbe_reset(adapter);
6569
6570 return err;
6571}
6572
6573static void ixgbe_close_suspend(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
6574{
6575 ixgbe_ptp_suspend(adapter);
6576
6577 if (adapter->hw.phy.ops.enter_lplu) {
6578 adapter->hw.phy.reset_disable = true;
6579 ixgbe_down(adapter);
6580 adapter->hw.phy.ops.enter_lplu(&adapter->hw);
6581 adapter->hw.phy.reset_disable = false;
6582 } else {
6583 ixgbe_down(adapter);
6584 }
6585
6586 ixgbe_free_irq(adapter);
6587
6588 ixgbe_free_all_tx_resources(adapter);
6589 ixgbe_free_all_rx_resources(adapter);
6590}
6591
6592/**
6593 * ixgbe_close - Disables a network interface
6594 * @netdev: network interface device structure
6595 *
6596 * Returns 0, this is not allowed to fail
6597 *
6598 * The close entry point is called when an interface is de-activated
6599 * by the OS. The hardware is still under the drivers control, but
6600 * needs to be disabled. A global MAC reset is issued to stop the
6601 * hardware, and all transmit and receive resources are freed.
6602 **/
6603int ixgbe_close(struct net_device *netdev)
6604{
6605 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
6606
6607 ixgbe_ptp_stop(adapter);
6608
6609 if (netif_device_present(netdev))
6610 ixgbe_close_suspend(adapter);
6611
6612 ixgbe_fdir_filter_exit(adapter);
6613
6614 ixgbe_release_hw_control(adapter);
6615
6616 return 0;
6617}
6618
6619#ifdef CONFIG_PM
6620static int ixgbe_resume(struct pci_dev *pdev)
6621{
6622 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
6623 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
6624 u32 err;
6625
6626 adapter->hw.hw_addr = adapter->io_addr;
6627 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D0);
6628 pci_restore_state(pdev);
6629 /*
6630 * pci_restore_state clears dev->state_saved so call
6631 * pci_save_state to restore it.
6632 */
6633 pci_save_state(pdev);
6634
6635 err = pci_enable_device_mem(pdev);
6636 if (err) {
6637 e_dev_err("Cannot enable PCI device from suspend\n");
6638 return err;
6639 }
6640 smp_mb__before_atomic();
6641 clear_bit(__IXGBE_DISABLED, &adapter->state);
6642 pci_set_master(pdev);
6643
6644 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, false);
6645
6646 ixgbe_reset(adapter);
6647
6648 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_WUS, ~0);
6649
6650 rtnl_lock();
6651 err = ixgbe_init_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
6652 if (!err && netif_running(netdev))
6653 err = ixgbe_open(netdev);
6654
6655
6656 if (!err)
6657 netif_device_attach(netdev);
6658 rtnl_unlock();
6659
6660 return err;
6661}
6662#endif /* CONFIG_PM */
6663
6664static int __ixgbe_shutdown(struct pci_dev *pdev, bool *enable_wake)
6665{
6666 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
6667 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
6668 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6669 u32 ctrl, fctrl;
6670 u32 wufc = adapter->wol;
6671#ifdef CONFIG_PM
6672 int retval = 0;
6673#endif
6674
6675 rtnl_lock();
6676 netif_device_detach(netdev);
6677
6678 if (netif_running(netdev))
6679 ixgbe_close_suspend(adapter);
6680
6681 ixgbe_clear_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
6682 rtnl_unlock();
6683
6684#ifdef CONFIG_PM
6685 retval = pci_save_state(pdev);
6686 if (retval)
6687 return retval;
6688
6689#endif
6690 if (hw->mac.ops.stop_link_on_d3)
6691 hw->mac.ops.stop_link_on_d3(hw);
6692
6693 if (wufc) {
6694 ixgbe_set_rx_mode(netdev);
6695
6696 /* enable the optics for 82599 SFP+ fiber as we can WoL */
6697 if (hw->mac.ops.enable_tx_laser)
6698 hw->mac.ops.enable_tx_laser(hw);
6699
6700 /* turn on all-multi mode if wake on multicast is enabled */
6701 if (wufc & IXGBE_WUFC_MC) {
6702 fctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCTRL);
6703 fctrl |= IXGBE_FCTRL_MPE;
6704 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCTRL, fctrl);
6705 }
6706
6707 ctrl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_CTRL);
6708 ctrl |= IXGBE_CTRL_GIO_DIS;
6709 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_CTRL, ctrl);
6710
6711 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_WUFC, wufc);
6712 } else {
6713 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_WUC, 0);
6714 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_WUFC, 0);
6715 }
6716
6717 switch (hw->mac.type) {
6718 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
6719 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, false);
6720 break;
6721 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
6722 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
6723 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
6724 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
6725 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
6726 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, !!wufc);
6727 break;
6728 default:
6729 break;
6730 }
6731
6732 *enable_wake = !!wufc;
6733 if (hw->phy.ops.set_phy_power && !*enable_wake)
6734 hw->phy.ops.set_phy_power(hw, false);
6735
6736 ixgbe_release_hw_control(adapter);
6737
6738 if (!test_and_set_bit(__IXGBE_DISABLED, &adapter->state))
6739 pci_disable_device(pdev);
6740
6741 return 0;
6742}
6743
6744#ifdef CONFIG_PM
6745static int ixgbe_suspend(struct pci_dev *pdev, pm_message_t state)
6746{
6747 int retval;
6748 bool wake;
6749
6750 retval = __ixgbe_shutdown(pdev, &wake);
6751 if (retval)
6752 return retval;
6753
6754 if (wake) {
6755 pci_prepare_to_sleep(pdev);
6756 } else {
6757 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, false);
6758 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D3hot);
6759 }
6760
6761 return 0;
6762}
6763#endif /* CONFIG_PM */
6764
6765static void ixgbe_shutdown(struct pci_dev *pdev)
6766{
6767 bool wake;
6768
6769 __ixgbe_shutdown(pdev, &wake);
6770
6771 if (system_state == SYSTEM_POWER_OFF) {
6772 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, wake);
6773 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D3hot);
6774 }
6775}
6776
6777/**
6778 * ixgbe_update_stats - Update the board statistics counters.
6779 * @adapter: board private structure
6780 **/
6781void ixgbe_update_stats(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
6782{
6783 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
6784 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6785 struct ixgbe_hw_stats *hwstats = &adapter->stats;
6786 u64 total_mpc = 0;
6787 u32 i, missed_rx = 0, mpc, bprc, lxon, lxoff, xon_off_tot;
6788 u64 non_eop_descs = 0, restart_queue = 0, tx_busy = 0;
6789 u64 alloc_rx_page_failed = 0, alloc_rx_buff_failed = 0;
6790 u64 bytes = 0, packets = 0, hw_csum_rx_error = 0;
6791
6792 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state) ||
6793 test_bit(__IXGBE_RESETTING, &adapter->state))
6794 return;
6795
6796 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_ENABLED) {
6797 u64 rsc_count = 0;
6798 u64 rsc_flush = 0;
6799 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++) {
6800 rsc_count += adapter->rx_ring[i]->rx_stats.rsc_count;
6801 rsc_flush += adapter->rx_ring[i]->rx_stats.rsc_flush;
6802 }
6803 adapter->rsc_total_count = rsc_count;
6804 adapter->rsc_total_flush = rsc_flush;
6805 }
6806
6807 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++) {
6808 struct ixgbe_ring *rx_ring = adapter->rx_ring[i];
6809 non_eop_descs += rx_ring->rx_stats.non_eop_descs;
6810 alloc_rx_page_failed += rx_ring->rx_stats.alloc_rx_page_failed;
6811 alloc_rx_buff_failed += rx_ring->rx_stats.alloc_rx_buff_failed;
6812 hw_csum_rx_error += rx_ring->rx_stats.csum_err;
6813 bytes += rx_ring->stats.bytes;
6814 packets += rx_ring->stats.packets;
6815 }
6816 adapter->non_eop_descs = non_eop_descs;
6817 adapter->alloc_rx_page_failed = alloc_rx_page_failed;
6818 adapter->alloc_rx_buff_failed = alloc_rx_buff_failed;
6819 adapter->hw_csum_rx_error = hw_csum_rx_error;
6820 netdev->stats.rx_bytes = bytes;
6821 netdev->stats.rx_packets = packets;
6822
6823 bytes = 0;
6824 packets = 0;
6825 /* gather some stats to the adapter struct that are per queue */
6826 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++) {
6827 struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring = adapter->tx_ring[i];
6828 restart_queue += tx_ring->tx_stats.restart_queue;
6829 tx_busy += tx_ring->tx_stats.tx_busy;
6830 bytes += tx_ring->stats.bytes;
6831 packets += tx_ring->stats.packets;
6832 }
6833 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_xdp_queues; i++) {
6834 struct ixgbe_ring *xdp_ring = adapter->xdp_ring[i];
6835
6836 restart_queue += xdp_ring->tx_stats.restart_queue;
6837 tx_busy += xdp_ring->tx_stats.tx_busy;
6838 bytes += xdp_ring->stats.bytes;
6839 packets += xdp_ring->stats.packets;
6840 }
6841 adapter->restart_queue = restart_queue;
6842 adapter->tx_busy = tx_busy;
6843 netdev->stats.tx_bytes = bytes;
6844 netdev->stats.tx_packets = packets;
6845
6846 hwstats->crcerrs += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_CRCERRS);
6847
6848 /* 8 register reads */
6849 for (i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
6850 /* for packet buffers not used, the register should read 0 */
6851 mpc = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_MPC(i));
6852 missed_rx += mpc;
6853 hwstats->mpc[i] += mpc;
6854 total_mpc += hwstats->mpc[i];
6855 hwstats->pxontxc[i] += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PXONTXC(i));
6856 hwstats->pxofftxc[i] += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PXOFFTXC(i));
6857 switch (hw->mac.type) {
6858 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
6859 hwstats->rnbc[i] += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RNBC(i));
6860 hwstats->qbtc[i] += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_QBTC(i));
6861 hwstats->qbrc[i] += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_QBRC(i));
6862 hwstats->pxonrxc[i] +=
6863 IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PXONRXC(i));
6864 break;
6865 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
6866 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
6867 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
6868 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
6869 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
6870 hwstats->pxonrxc[i] +=
6871 IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PXONRXCNT(i));
6872 break;
6873 default:
6874 break;
6875 }
6876 }
6877
6878 /*16 register reads */
6879 for (i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
6880 hwstats->qptc[i] += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_QPTC(i));
6881 hwstats->qprc[i] += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_QPRC(i));
6882 if ((hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82599EB) ||
6883 (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_X540) ||
6884 (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_X550) ||
6885 (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x) ||
6886 (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_x550em_a)) {
6887 hwstats->qbtc[i] += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_QBTC_L(i));
6888 IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_QBTC_H(i)); /* to clear */
6889 hwstats->qbrc[i] += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_QBRC_L(i));
6890 IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_QBRC_H(i)); /* to clear */
6891 }
6892 }
6893
6894 hwstats->gprc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_GPRC);
6895 /* work around hardware counting issue */
6896 hwstats->gprc -= missed_rx;
6897
6898 ixgbe_update_xoff_received(adapter);
6899
6900 /* 82598 hardware only has a 32 bit counter in the high register */
6901 switch (hw->mac.type) {
6902 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
6903 hwstats->lxonrxc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_LXONRXC);
6904 hwstats->gorc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_GORCH);
6905 hwstats->gotc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_GOTCH);
6906 hwstats->tor += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_TORH);
6907 break;
6908 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
6909 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
6910 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
6911 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
6912 /* OS2BMC stats are X540 and later */
6913 hwstats->o2bgptc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_O2BGPTC);
6914 hwstats->o2bspc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_O2BSPC);
6915 hwstats->b2ospc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_B2OSPC);
6916 hwstats->b2ogprc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_B2OGPRC);
6917 /* fall through */
6918 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
6919 for (i = 0; i < 16; i++)
6920 adapter->hw_rx_no_dma_resources +=
6921 IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_QPRDC(i));
6922 hwstats->gorc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_GORCL);
6923 IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_GORCH); /* to clear */
6924 hwstats->gotc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_GOTCL);
6925 IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_GOTCH); /* to clear */
6926 hwstats->tor += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_TORL);
6927 IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_TORH); /* to clear */
6928 hwstats->lxonrxc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_LXONRXCNT);
6929 hwstats->fdirmatch += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FDIRMATCH);
6930 hwstats->fdirmiss += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FDIRMISS);
6931#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
6932 hwstats->fccrc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCCRC);
6933 hwstats->fcoerpdc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCOERPDC);
6934 hwstats->fcoeprc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCOEPRC);
6935 hwstats->fcoeptc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCOEPTC);
6936 hwstats->fcoedwrc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCOEDWRC);
6937 hwstats->fcoedwtc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCOEDWTC);
6938 /* Add up per cpu counters for total ddp aloc fail */
6939 if (adapter->fcoe.ddp_pool) {
6940 struct ixgbe_fcoe *fcoe = &adapter->fcoe;
6941 struct ixgbe_fcoe_ddp_pool *ddp_pool;
6942 unsigned int cpu;
6943 u64 noddp = 0, noddp_ext_buff = 0;
6944 for_each_possible_cpu(cpu) {
6945 ddp_pool = per_cpu_ptr(fcoe->ddp_pool, cpu);
6946 noddp += ddp_pool->noddp;
6947 noddp_ext_buff += ddp_pool->noddp_ext_buff;
6948 }
6949 hwstats->fcoe_noddp = noddp;
6950 hwstats->fcoe_noddp_ext_buff = noddp_ext_buff;
6951 }
6952#endif /* IXGBE_FCOE */
6953 break;
6954 default:
6955 break;
6956 }
6957 bprc = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_BPRC);
6958 hwstats->bprc += bprc;
6959 hwstats->mprc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_MPRC);
6960 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
6961 hwstats->mprc -= bprc;
6962 hwstats->roc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_ROC);
6963 hwstats->prc64 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PRC64);
6964 hwstats->prc127 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PRC127);
6965 hwstats->prc255 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PRC255);
6966 hwstats->prc511 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PRC511);
6967 hwstats->prc1023 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PRC1023);
6968 hwstats->prc1522 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PRC1522);
6969 hwstats->rlec += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RLEC);
6970 lxon = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_LXONTXC);
6971 hwstats->lxontxc += lxon;
6972 lxoff = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_LXOFFTXC);
6973 hwstats->lxofftxc += lxoff;
6974 hwstats->gptc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_GPTC);
6975 hwstats->mptc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_MPTC);
6976 /*
6977 * 82598 errata - tx of flow control packets is included in tx counters
6978 */
6979 xon_off_tot = lxon + lxoff;
6980 hwstats->gptc -= xon_off_tot;
6981 hwstats->mptc -= xon_off_tot;
6982 hwstats->gotc -= (xon_off_tot * (ETH_ZLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN));
6983 hwstats->ruc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RUC);
6984 hwstats->rfc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RFC);
6985 hwstats->rjc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RJC);
6986 hwstats->tpr += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_TPR);
6987 hwstats->ptc64 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PTC64);
6988 hwstats->ptc64 -= xon_off_tot;
6989 hwstats->ptc127 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PTC127);
6990 hwstats->ptc255 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PTC255);
6991 hwstats->ptc511 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PTC511);
6992 hwstats->ptc1023 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PTC1023);
6993 hwstats->ptc1522 += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PTC1522);
6994 hwstats->bptc += IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_BPTC);
6995
6996 /* Fill out the OS statistics structure */
6997 netdev->stats.multicast = hwstats->mprc;
6998
6999 /* Rx Errors */
7000 netdev->stats.rx_errors = hwstats->crcerrs + hwstats->rlec;
7001 netdev->stats.rx_dropped = 0;
7002 netdev->stats.rx_length_errors = hwstats->rlec;
7003 netdev->stats.rx_crc_errors = hwstats->crcerrs;
7004 netdev->stats.rx_missed_errors = total_mpc;
7005}
7006
7007/**
7008 * ixgbe_fdir_reinit_subtask - worker thread to reinit FDIR filter table
7009 * @adapter: pointer to the device adapter structure
7010 **/
7011static void ixgbe_fdir_reinit_subtask(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7012{
7013 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7014 int i;
7015
7016 if (!(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_FDIR_REQUIRES_REINIT))
7017 return;
7018
7019 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_FDIR_REQUIRES_REINIT;
7020
7021 /* if interface is down do nothing */
7022 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state))
7023 return;
7024
7025 /* do nothing if we are not using signature filters */
7026 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_HASH_CAPABLE))
7027 return;
7028
7029 adapter->fdir_overflow++;
7030
7031 if (ixgbe_reinit_fdir_tables_82599(hw) == 0) {
7032 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++)
7033 set_bit(__IXGBE_TX_FDIR_INIT_DONE,
7034 &(adapter->tx_ring[i]->state));
7035 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_xdp_queues; i++)
7036 set_bit(__IXGBE_TX_FDIR_INIT_DONE,
7037 &adapter->xdp_ring[i]->state);
7038 /* re-enable flow director interrupts */
7039 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIMS, IXGBE_EIMS_FLOW_DIR);
7040 } else {
7041 e_err(probe, "failed to finish FDIR re-initialization, "
7042 "ignored adding FDIR ATR filters\n");
7043 }
7044}
7045
7046/**
7047 * ixgbe_check_hang_subtask - check for hung queues and dropped interrupts
7048 * @adapter: pointer to the device adapter structure
7049 *
7050 * This function serves two purposes. First it strobes the interrupt lines
7051 * in order to make certain interrupts are occurring. Secondly it sets the
7052 * bits needed to check for TX hangs. As a result we should immediately
7053 * determine if a hang has occurred.
7054 */
7055static void ixgbe_check_hang_subtask(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7056{
7057 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7058 u64 eics = 0;
7059 int i;
7060
7061 /* If we're down, removing or resetting, just bail */
7062 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state) ||
7063 test_bit(__IXGBE_REMOVING, &adapter->state) ||
7064 test_bit(__IXGBE_RESETTING, &adapter->state))
7065 return;
7066
7067 /* Force detection of hung controller */
7068 if (netif_carrier_ok(adapter->netdev)) {
7069 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++)
7070 set_check_for_tx_hang(adapter->tx_ring[i]);
7071 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_xdp_queues; i++)
7072 set_check_for_tx_hang(adapter->xdp_ring[i]);
7073 }
7074
7075 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED)) {
7076 /*
7077 * for legacy and MSI interrupts don't set any bits
7078 * that are enabled for EIAM, because this operation
7079 * would set *both* EIMS and EICS for any bit in EIAM
7080 */
7081 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EICS,
7082 (IXGBE_EICS_TCP_TIMER | IXGBE_EICS_OTHER));
7083 } else {
7084 /* get one bit for every active tx/rx interrupt vector */
7085 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_q_vectors; i++) {
7086 struct ixgbe_q_vector *qv = adapter->q_vector[i];
7087 if (qv->rx.ring || qv->tx.ring)
7088 eics |= BIT_ULL(i);
7089 }
7090 }
7091
7092 /* Cause software interrupt to ensure rings are cleaned */
7093 ixgbe_irq_rearm_queues(adapter, eics);
7094}
7095
7096/**
7097 * ixgbe_watchdog_update_link - update the link status
7098 * @adapter: pointer to the device adapter structure
7099 * @link_speed: pointer to a u32 to store the link_speed
7100 **/
7101static void ixgbe_watchdog_update_link(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7102{
7103 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7104 u32 link_speed = adapter->link_speed;
7105 bool link_up = adapter->link_up;
7106 bool pfc_en = adapter->dcb_cfg.pfc_mode_enable;
7107
7108 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE))
7109 return;
7110
7111 if (hw->mac.ops.check_link) {
7112 hw->mac.ops.check_link(hw, &link_speed, &link_up, false);
7113 } else {
7114 /* always assume link is up, if no check link function */
7115 link_speed = IXGBE_LINK_SPEED_10GB_FULL;
7116 link_up = true;
7117 }
7118
7119 if (adapter->ixgbe_ieee_pfc)
7120 pfc_en |= !!(adapter->ixgbe_ieee_pfc->pfc_en);
7121
7122 if (link_up && !((adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED) && pfc_en)) {
7123 hw->mac.ops.fc_enable(hw);
7124 ixgbe_set_rx_drop_en(adapter);
7125 }
7126
7127 if (link_up ||
7128 time_after(jiffies, (adapter->link_check_timeout +
7129 IXGBE_TRY_LINK_TIMEOUT))) {
7130 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE;
7131 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_EIMS, IXGBE_EIMC_LSC);
7132 IXGBE_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
7133 }
7134
7135 adapter->link_up = link_up;
7136 adapter->link_speed = link_speed;
7137}
7138
7139static void ixgbe_update_default_up(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7140{
7141#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
7142 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
7143 struct dcb_app app = {
7144 .selector = IEEE_8021QAZ_APP_SEL_ETHERTYPE,
7145 .protocol = 0,
7146 };
7147 u8 up = 0;
7148
7149 if (adapter->dcbx_cap & DCB_CAP_DCBX_VER_IEEE)
7150 up = dcb_ieee_getapp_mask(netdev, &app);
7151
7152 adapter->default_up = (up > 1) ? (ffs(up) - 1) : 0;
7153#endif
7154}
7155
7156static int ixgbe_enable_macvlan(struct net_device *upper, void *data)
7157{
7158 if (netif_is_macvlan(upper)) {
7159 struct macvlan_dev *vlan = netdev_priv(upper);
7160
7161 if (vlan->fwd_priv)
7162 netif_tx_wake_all_queues(upper);
7163 }
7164
7165 return 0;
7166}
7167
7168/**
7169 * ixgbe_watchdog_link_is_up - update netif_carrier status and
7170 * print link up message
7171 * @adapter: pointer to the device adapter structure
7172 **/
7173static void ixgbe_watchdog_link_is_up(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7174{
7175 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
7176 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7177 u32 link_speed = adapter->link_speed;
7178 const char *speed_str;
7179 bool flow_rx, flow_tx;
7180
7181 /* only continue if link was previously down */
7182 if (netif_carrier_ok(netdev))
7183 return;
7184
7185 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_SEARCH_FOR_SFP;
7186
7187 switch (hw->mac.type) {
7188 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB: {
7189 u32 frctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCTRL);
7190 u32 rmcs = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RMCS);
7191 flow_rx = !!(frctl & IXGBE_FCTRL_RFCE);
7192 flow_tx = !!(rmcs & IXGBE_RMCS_TFCE_802_3X);
7193 }
7194 break;
7195 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
7196 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
7197 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
7198 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
7199 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB: {
7200 u32 mflcn = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_MFLCN);
7201 u32 fccfg = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_FCCFG);
7202 flow_rx = !!(mflcn & IXGBE_MFLCN_RFCE);
7203 flow_tx = !!(fccfg & IXGBE_FCCFG_TFCE_802_3X);
7204 }
7205 break;
7206 default:
7207 flow_tx = false;
7208 flow_rx = false;
7209 break;
7210 }
7211
7212 adapter->last_rx_ptp_check = jiffies;
7213
7214 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_PTP_RUNNING, &adapter->state))
7215 ixgbe_ptp_start_cyclecounter(adapter);
7216
7217 switch (link_speed) {
7218 case IXGBE_LINK_SPEED_10GB_FULL:
7219 speed_str = "10 Gbps";
7220 break;
7221 case IXGBE_LINK_SPEED_2_5GB_FULL:
7222 speed_str = "2.5 Gbps";
7223 break;
7224 case IXGBE_LINK_SPEED_1GB_FULL:
7225 speed_str = "1 Gbps";
7226 break;
7227 case IXGBE_LINK_SPEED_100_FULL:
7228 speed_str = "100 Mbps";
7229 break;
7230 case IXGBE_LINK_SPEED_10_FULL:
7231 speed_str = "10 Mbps";
7232 break;
7233 default:
7234 speed_str = "unknown speed";
7235 break;
7236 }
7237 e_info(drv, "NIC Link is Up %s, Flow Control: %s\n", speed_str,
7238 ((flow_rx && flow_tx) ? "RX/TX" :
7239 (flow_rx ? "RX" :
7240 (flow_tx ? "TX" : "None"))));
7241
7242 netif_carrier_on(netdev);
7243 ixgbe_check_vf_rate_limit(adapter);
7244
7245 /* enable transmits */
7246 netif_tx_wake_all_queues(adapter->netdev);
7247
7248 /* enable any upper devices */
7249 rtnl_lock();
7250 netdev_walk_all_upper_dev_rcu(adapter->netdev,
7251 ixgbe_enable_macvlan, NULL);
7252 rtnl_unlock();
7253
7254 /* update the default user priority for VFs */
7255 ixgbe_update_default_up(adapter);
7256
7257 /* ping all the active vfs to let them know link has changed */
7258 ixgbe_ping_all_vfs(adapter);
7259}
7260
7261/**
7262 * ixgbe_watchdog_link_is_down - update netif_carrier status and
7263 * print link down message
7264 * @adapter: pointer to the adapter structure
7265 **/
7266static void ixgbe_watchdog_link_is_down(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7267{
7268 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
7269 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7270
7271 adapter->link_up = false;
7272 adapter->link_speed = 0;
7273
7274 /* only continue if link was up previously */
7275 if (!netif_carrier_ok(netdev))
7276 return;
7277
7278 /* poll for SFP+ cable when link is down */
7279 if (ixgbe_is_sfp(hw) && hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
7280 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_SEARCH_FOR_SFP;
7281
7282 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_PTP_RUNNING, &adapter->state))
7283 ixgbe_ptp_start_cyclecounter(adapter);
7284
7285 e_info(drv, "NIC Link is Down\n");
7286 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
7287
7288 /* ping all the active vfs to let them know link has changed */
7289 ixgbe_ping_all_vfs(adapter);
7290}
7291
7292static bool ixgbe_ring_tx_pending(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7293{
7294 int i;
7295
7296 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++) {
7297 struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring = adapter->tx_ring[i];
7298
7299 if (tx_ring->next_to_use != tx_ring->next_to_clean)
7300 return true;
7301 }
7302
7303 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_xdp_queues; i++) {
7304 struct ixgbe_ring *ring = adapter->xdp_ring[i];
7305
7306 if (ring->next_to_use != ring->next_to_clean)
7307 return true;
7308 }
7309
7310 return false;
7311}
7312
7313static bool ixgbe_vf_tx_pending(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7314{
7315 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7316 struct ixgbe_ring_feature *vmdq = &adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_VMDQ];
7317 u32 q_per_pool = __ALIGN_MASK(1, ~vmdq->mask);
7318
7319 int i, j;
7320
7321 if (!adapter->num_vfs)
7322 return false;
7323
7324 /* resetting the PF is only needed for MAC before X550 */
7325 if (hw->mac.type >= ixgbe_mac_X550)
7326 return false;
7327
7328 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_vfs; i++) {
7329 for (j = 0; j < q_per_pool; j++) {
7330 u32 h, t;
7331
7332 h = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PVFTDHN(q_per_pool, i, j));
7333 t = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_PVFTDTN(q_per_pool, i, j));
7334
7335 if (h != t)
7336 return true;
7337 }
7338 }
7339
7340 return false;
7341}
7342
7343/**
7344 * ixgbe_watchdog_flush_tx - flush queues on link down
7345 * @adapter: pointer to the device adapter structure
7346 **/
7347static void ixgbe_watchdog_flush_tx(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7348{
7349 if (!netif_carrier_ok(adapter->netdev)) {
7350 if (ixgbe_ring_tx_pending(adapter) ||
7351 ixgbe_vf_tx_pending(adapter)) {
7352 /* We've lost link, so the controller stops DMA,
7353 * but we've got queued Tx work that's never going
7354 * to get done, so reset controller to flush Tx.
7355 * (Do the reset outside of interrupt context).
7356 */
7357 e_warn(drv, "initiating reset to clear Tx work after link loss\n");
7358 set_bit(__IXGBE_RESET_REQUESTED, &adapter->state);
7359 }
7360 }
7361}
7362
7363#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
7364static void ixgbe_check_for_bad_vf(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7365{
7366 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7367 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
7368 unsigned int vf;
7369 u32 gpc;
7370
7371 if (!(netif_carrier_ok(adapter->netdev)))
7372 return;
7373
7374 gpc = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_TXDGPC);
7375 if (gpc) /* If incrementing then no need for the check below */
7376 return;
7377 /* Check to see if a bad DMA write target from an errant or
7378 * malicious VF has caused a PCIe error. If so then we can
7379 * issue a VFLR to the offending VF(s) and then resume without
7380 * requesting a full slot reset.
7381 */
7382
7383 if (!pdev)
7384 return;
7385
7386 /* check status reg for all VFs owned by this PF */
7387 for (vf = 0; vf < adapter->num_vfs; ++vf) {
7388 struct pci_dev *vfdev = adapter->vfinfo[vf].vfdev;
7389 u16 status_reg;
7390
7391 if (!vfdev)
7392 continue;
7393 pci_read_config_word(vfdev, PCI_STATUS, &status_reg);
7394 if (status_reg != IXGBE_FAILED_READ_CFG_WORD &&
7395 status_reg & PCI_STATUS_REC_MASTER_ABORT)
7396 pcie_flr(vfdev);
7397 }
7398}
7399
7400static void ixgbe_spoof_check(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7401{
7402 u32 ssvpc;
7403
7404 /* Do not perform spoof check for 82598 or if not in IOV mode */
7405 if (adapter->hw.mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB ||
7406 adapter->num_vfs == 0)
7407 return;
7408
7409 ssvpc = IXGBE_READ_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_SSVPC);
7410
7411 /*
7412 * ssvpc register is cleared on read, if zero then no
7413 * spoofed packets in the last interval.
7414 */
7415 if (!ssvpc)
7416 return;
7417
7418 e_warn(drv, "%u Spoofed packets detected\n", ssvpc);
7419}
7420#else
7421static void ixgbe_spoof_check(struct ixgbe_adapter __always_unused *adapter)
7422{
7423}
7424
7425static void
7426ixgbe_check_for_bad_vf(struct ixgbe_adapter __always_unused *adapter)
7427{
7428}
7429#endif /* CONFIG_PCI_IOV */
7430
7431
7432/**
7433 * ixgbe_watchdog_subtask - check and bring link up
7434 * @adapter: pointer to the device adapter structure
7435 **/
7436static void ixgbe_watchdog_subtask(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7437{
7438 /* if interface is down, removing or resetting, do nothing */
7439 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state) ||
7440 test_bit(__IXGBE_REMOVING, &adapter->state) ||
7441 test_bit(__IXGBE_RESETTING, &adapter->state))
7442 return;
7443
7444 ixgbe_watchdog_update_link(adapter);
7445
7446 if (adapter->link_up)
7447 ixgbe_watchdog_link_is_up(adapter);
7448 else
7449 ixgbe_watchdog_link_is_down(adapter);
7450
7451 ixgbe_check_for_bad_vf(adapter);
7452 ixgbe_spoof_check(adapter);
7453 ixgbe_update_stats(adapter);
7454
7455 ixgbe_watchdog_flush_tx(adapter);
7456}
7457
7458/**
7459 * ixgbe_sfp_detection_subtask - poll for SFP+ cable
7460 * @adapter: the ixgbe adapter structure
7461 **/
7462static void ixgbe_sfp_detection_subtask(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7463{
7464 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7465 s32 err;
7466
7467 /* not searching for SFP so there is nothing to do here */
7468 if (!(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_SEARCH_FOR_SFP) &&
7469 !(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_SFP_NEEDS_RESET))
7470 return;
7471
7472 if (adapter->sfp_poll_time &&
7473 time_after(adapter->sfp_poll_time, jiffies))
7474 return; /* If not yet time to poll for SFP */
7475
7476 /* someone else is in init, wait until next service event */
7477 if (test_and_set_bit(__IXGBE_IN_SFP_INIT, &adapter->state))
7478 return;
7479
7480 adapter->sfp_poll_time = jiffies + IXGBE_SFP_POLL_JIFFIES - 1;
7481
7482 err = hw->phy.ops.identify_sfp(hw);
7483 if (err == IXGBE_ERR_SFP_NOT_SUPPORTED)
7484 goto sfp_out;
7485
7486 if (err == IXGBE_ERR_SFP_NOT_PRESENT) {
7487 /* If no cable is present, then we need to reset
7488 * the next time we find a good cable. */
7489 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_SFP_NEEDS_RESET;
7490 }
7491
7492 /* exit on error */
7493 if (err)
7494 goto sfp_out;
7495
7496 /* exit if reset not needed */
7497 if (!(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_SFP_NEEDS_RESET))
7498 goto sfp_out;
7499
7500 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_SFP_NEEDS_RESET;
7501
7502 /*
7503 * A module may be identified correctly, but the EEPROM may not have
7504 * support for that module. setup_sfp() will fail in that case, so
7505 * we should not allow that module to load.
7506 */
7507 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
