7508 err = hw->phy.ops.reset(hw);
7509 else
7510 err = hw->mac.ops.setup_sfp(hw);
7511
7512 if (err == IXGBE_ERR_SFP_NOT_SUPPORTED)
7513 goto sfp_out;
7514
7515 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_CONFIG;
7516 e_info(probe, "detected SFP+: %d\n", hw->phy.sfp_type);
7517
7518sfp_out:
7519 clear_bit(__IXGBE_IN_SFP_INIT, &adapter->state);
7520
7521 if ((err == IXGBE_ERR_SFP_NOT_SUPPORTED) &&
7522 (adapter->netdev->reg_state == NETREG_REGISTERED)) {
7523 e_dev_err("failed to initialize because an unsupported "
7524 "SFP+ module type was detected.\n");
7525 e_dev_err("Reload the driver after installing a "
7526 "supported module.\n");
7527 unregister_netdev(adapter->netdev);
7528 }
7529}
7530
7531/**
7532 * ixgbe_sfp_link_config_subtask - set up link SFP after module install
7533 * @adapter: the ixgbe adapter structure
7534 **/
7535static void ixgbe_sfp_link_config_subtask(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7536{
7537 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7538 u32 speed;
7539 bool autoneg = false;
7540
7541 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_CONFIG))
7542 return;
7543
7544 /* someone else is in init, wait until next service event */
7545 if (test_and_set_bit(__IXGBE_IN_SFP_INIT, &adapter->state))
7546 return;
7547
7548 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_CONFIG;
7549
7550 speed = hw->phy.autoneg_advertised;
7551 if ((!speed) && (hw->mac.ops.get_link_capabilities)) {
7552 hw->mac.ops.get_link_capabilities(hw, &speed, &autoneg);
7553
7554 /* setup the highest link when no autoneg */
7555 if (!autoneg) {
7556 if (speed & IXGBE_LINK_SPEED_10GB_FULL)
7557 speed = IXGBE_LINK_SPEED_10GB_FULL;
7558 }
7559 }
7560
7561 if (hw->mac.ops.setup_link)
7562 hw->mac.ops.setup_link(hw, speed, true);
7563
7564 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE;
7565 adapter->link_check_timeout = jiffies;
7566 clear_bit(__IXGBE_IN_SFP_INIT, &adapter->state);
7567}
7568
7569/**
7570 * ixgbe_service_timer - Timer Call-back
7571 * @data: pointer to adapter cast into an unsigned long
7572 **/
7573static void ixgbe_service_timer(unsigned long data)
7574{
7575 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = (struct ixgbe_adapter *)data;
7576 unsigned long next_event_offset;
7577
7578 /* poll faster when waiting for link */
7579 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE)
7580 next_event_offset = HZ / 10;
7581 else
7582 next_event_offset = HZ * 2;
7583
7584 /* Reset the timer */
7585 mod_timer(&adapter->service_timer, next_event_offset + jiffies);
7586
7587 ixgbe_service_event_schedule(adapter);
7588}
7589
7590static void ixgbe_phy_interrupt_subtask(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7591{
7592 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7593 u32 status;
7594
7595 if (!(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_PHY_INTERRUPT))
7596 return;
7597
7598 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_PHY_INTERRUPT;
7599
7600 if (!hw->phy.ops.handle_lasi)
7601 return;
7602
7603 status = hw->phy.ops.handle_lasi(&adapter->hw);
7604 if (status != IXGBE_ERR_OVERTEMP)
7605 return;
7606
7607 e_crit(drv, "%s\n", ixgbe_overheat_msg);
7608}
7609
7610static void ixgbe_reset_subtask(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
7611{
7612 if (!test_and_clear_bit(__IXGBE_RESET_REQUESTED, &adapter->state))
7613 return;
7614
7615 /* If we're already down, removing or resetting, just bail */
7616 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state) ||
7617 test_bit(__IXGBE_REMOVING, &adapter->state) ||
7618 test_bit(__IXGBE_RESETTING, &adapter->state))
7619 return;
7620
7621 ixgbe_dump(adapter);
7622 netdev_err(adapter->netdev, "Reset adapter\n");
7623 adapter->tx_timeout_count++;
7624
7625 rtnl_lock();
7626 ixgbe_reinit_locked(adapter);
7627 rtnl_unlock();
7628}
7629
7630/**
7631 * ixgbe_service_task - manages and runs subtasks
7632 * @work: pointer to work_struct containing our data
7633 **/
7634static void ixgbe_service_task(struct work_struct *work)
7635{
7636 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = container_of(work,
7637 struct ixgbe_adapter,
7638 service_task);
7639 if (ixgbe_removed(adapter->hw.hw_addr)) {
7640 if (!test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state)) {
7641 rtnl_lock();
7642 ixgbe_down(adapter);
7643 rtnl_unlock();
7644 }
7645 ixgbe_service_event_complete(adapter);
7646 return;
7647 }
7648 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_UDP_TUN_REREG_NEEDED) {
7649 rtnl_lock();
7650 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_UDP_TUN_REREG_NEEDED;
7651 udp_tunnel_get_rx_info(adapter->netdev);
7652 rtnl_unlock();
7653 }
7654 ixgbe_reset_subtask(adapter);
7655 ixgbe_phy_interrupt_subtask(adapter);
7656 ixgbe_sfp_detection_subtask(adapter);
7657 ixgbe_sfp_link_config_subtask(adapter);
7658 ixgbe_check_overtemp_subtask(adapter);
7659 ixgbe_watchdog_subtask(adapter);
7660 ixgbe_fdir_reinit_subtask(adapter);
7661 ixgbe_check_hang_subtask(adapter);
7662
7663 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_PTP_RUNNING, &adapter->state)) {
7664 ixgbe_ptp_overflow_check(adapter);
7665 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_RX_HWTSTAMP_IN_REGISTER)
7666 ixgbe_ptp_rx_hang(adapter);
7667 ixgbe_ptp_tx_hang(adapter);
7668 }
7669
7670 ixgbe_service_event_complete(adapter);
7671}
7672
7673static int ixgbe_tso(struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring,
7674 struct ixgbe_tx_buffer *first,
7675 u8 *hdr_len)
7676{
7677 u32 vlan_macip_lens, type_tucmd, mss_l4len_idx;
7678 struct sk_buff *skb = first->skb;
7679 union {
7680 struct iphdr *v4;
7681 struct ipv6hdr *v6;
7682 unsigned char *hdr;
7683 } ip;
7684 union {
7685 struct tcphdr *tcp;
7686 unsigned char *hdr;
7687 } l4;
7688 u32 paylen, l4_offset;
7689 int err;
7690
7691 if (skb->ip_summed != CHECKSUM_PARTIAL)
7692 return 0;
7693
7694 if (!skb_is_gso(skb))
7695 return 0;
7696
7697 err = skb_cow_head(skb, 0);
7698 if (err < 0)
7699 return err;
7700
7701 if (eth_p_mpls(first->protocol))
7702 ip.hdr = skb_inner_network_header(skb);
7703 else
7704 ip.hdr = skb_network_header(skb);
7705 l4.hdr = skb_checksum_start(skb);
7706
7707 /* ADV DTYP TUCMD MKRLOC/ISCSIHEDLEN */
7708 type_tucmd = IXGBE_ADVTXD_TUCMD_L4T_TCP;
7709
7710 /* initialize outer IP header fields */
7711 if (ip.v4->version == 4) {
7712 unsigned char *csum_start = skb_checksum_start(skb);
7713 unsigned char *trans_start = ip.hdr + (ip.v4->ihl * 4);
7714
7715 /* IP header will have to cancel out any data that
7716 * is not a part of the outer IP header
7717 */
7718 ip.v4->check = csum_fold(csum_partial(trans_start,
7719 csum_start - trans_start,
7720 0));
7721 type_tucmd |= IXGBE_ADVTXD_TUCMD_IPV4;
7722
7723 ip.v4->tot_len = 0;
7724 first->tx_flags |= IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_TSO |
7725 IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_CSUM |
7726 IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_IPV4;
7727 } else {
7728 ip.v6->payload_len = 0;
7729 first->tx_flags |= IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_TSO |
7730 IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_CSUM;
7731 }
7732
7733 /* determine offset of inner transport header */
7734 l4_offset = l4.hdr - skb->data;
7735
7736 /* compute length of segmentation header */
7737 *hdr_len = (l4.tcp->doff * 4) + l4_offset;
7738
7739 /* remove payload length from inner checksum */
7740 paylen = skb->len - l4_offset;
7741 csum_replace_by_diff(&l4.tcp->check, htonl(paylen));
7742
7743 /* update gso size and bytecount with header size */
7744 first->gso_segs = skb_shinfo(skb)->gso_segs;
7745 first->bytecount += (first->gso_segs - 1) * *hdr_len;
7746
7747 /* mss_l4len_id: use 0 as index for TSO */
7748 mss_l4len_idx = (*hdr_len - l4_offset) << IXGBE_ADVTXD_L4LEN_SHIFT;
7749 mss_l4len_idx |= skb_shinfo(skb)->gso_size << IXGBE_ADVTXD_MSS_SHIFT;
7750
7751 /* vlan_macip_lens: HEADLEN, MACLEN, VLAN tag */
7752 vlan_macip_lens = l4.hdr - ip.hdr;
7753 vlan_macip_lens |= (ip.hdr - skb->data) << IXGBE_ADVTXD_MACLEN_SHIFT;
7754 vlan_macip_lens |= first->tx_flags & IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_MASK;
7755
7756 ixgbe_tx_ctxtdesc(tx_ring, vlan_macip_lens, 0, type_tucmd,
7757 mss_l4len_idx);
7758
7759 return 1;
7760}
7761
7762static inline bool ixgbe_ipv6_csum_is_sctp(struct sk_buff *skb)
7763{
7764 unsigned int offset = 0;
7765
7766 ipv6_find_hdr(skb, &offset, IPPROTO_SCTP, NULL, NULL);
7767
7768 return offset == skb_checksum_start_offset(skb);
7769}
7770
7771static void ixgbe_tx_csum(struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring,
7772 struct ixgbe_tx_buffer *first)
7773{
7774 struct sk_buff *skb = first->skb;
7775 u32 vlan_macip_lens = 0;
7776 u32 type_tucmd = 0;
7777
7778 if (skb->ip_summed != CHECKSUM_PARTIAL) {
7779csum_failed:
7780 if (!(first->tx_flags & (IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_HW_VLAN |
7781 IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_CC)))
7782 return;
7783 goto no_csum;
7784 }
7785
7786 switch (skb->csum_offset) {
7787 case offsetof(struct tcphdr, check):
7788 type_tucmd = IXGBE_ADVTXD_TUCMD_L4T_TCP;
7789 /* fall through */
7790 case offsetof(struct udphdr, check):
7791 break;
7792 case offsetof(struct sctphdr, checksum):
7793 /* validate that this is actually an SCTP request */
7794 if (((first->protocol == htons(ETH_P_IP)) &&
7795 (ip_hdr(skb)->protocol == IPPROTO_SCTP)) ||
7796 ((first->protocol == htons(ETH_P_IPV6)) &&
7797 ixgbe_ipv6_csum_is_sctp(skb))) {
7798 type_tucmd = IXGBE_ADVTXD_TUCMD_L4T_SCTP;
7799 break;
7800 }
7801 /* fall through */
7802 default:
7803 skb_checksum_help(skb);
7804 goto csum_failed;
7805 }
7806
7807 /* update TX checksum flag */
7808 first->tx_flags |= IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_CSUM;
7809 vlan_macip_lens = skb_checksum_start_offset(skb) -
7810 skb_network_offset(skb);
7811no_csum:
7812 /* vlan_macip_lens: MACLEN, VLAN tag */
7813 vlan_macip_lens |= skb_network_offset(skb) << IXGBE_ADVTXD_MACLEN_SHIFT;
7814 vlan_macip_lens |= first->tx_flags & IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_MASK;
7815
7816 ixgbe_tx_ctxtdesc(tx_ring, vlan_macip_lens, 0, type_tucmd, 0);
7817}
7818
7819#define IXGBE_SET_FLAG(_input, _flag, _result) \
7820 ((_flag <= _result) ? \
7821 ((u32)(_input & _flag) * (_result / _flag)) : \
7822 ((u32)(_input & _flag) / (_flag / _result)))
7823
7824static u32 ixgbe_tx_cmd_type(struct sk_buff *skb, u32 tx_flags)
7825{
7826 /* set type for advanced descriptor with frame checksum insertion */
7827 u32 cmd_type = IXGBE_ADVTXD_DTYP_DATA |
7828 IXGBE_ADVTXD_DCMD_DEXT |
7829 IXGBE_ADVTXD_DCMD_IFCS;
7830
7831 /* set HW vlan bit if vlan is present */
7832 cmd_type |= IXGBE_SET_FLAG(tx_flags, IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_HW_VLAN,
7833 IXGBE_ADVTXD_DCMD_VLE);
7834
7835 /* set segmentation enable bits for TSO/FSO */
7836 cmd_type |= IXGBE_SET_FLAG(tx_flags, IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_TSO,
7837 IXGBE_ADVTXD_DCMD_TSE);
7838
7839 /* set timestamp bit if present */
7840 cmd_type |= IXGBE_SET_FLAG(tx_flags, IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_TSTAMP,
7841 IXGBE_ADVTXD_MAC_TSTAMP);
7842
7843 /* insert frame checksum */
7844 cmd_type ^= IXGBE_SET_FLAG(skb->no_fcs, 1, IXGBE_ADVTXD_DCMD_IFCS);
7845
7846 return cmd_type;
7847}
7848
7849static void ixgbe_tx_olinfo_status(union ixgbe_adv_tx_desc *tx_desc,
7850 u32 tx_flags, unsigned int paylen)
7851{
7852 u32 olinfo_status = paylen << IXGBE_ADVTXD_PAYLEN_SHIFT;
7853
7854 /* enable L4 checksum for TSO and TX checksum offload */
7855 olinfo_status |= IXGBE_SET_FLAG(tx_flags,
7856 IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_CSUM,
7857 IXGBE_ADVTXD_POPTS_TXSM);
7858
7859 /* enble IPv4 checksum for TSO */
7860 olinfo_status |= IXGBE_SET_FLAG(tx_flags,
7861 IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_IPV4,
7862 IXGBE_ADVTXD_POPTS_IXSM);
7863
7864 /*
7865 * Check Context must be set if Tx switch is enabled, which it
7866 * always is for case where virtual functions are running
7867 */
7868 olinfo_status |= IXGBE_SET_FLAG(tx_flags,
7869 IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_CC,
7870 IXGBE_ADVTXD_CC);
7871
7872 tx_desc->read.olinfo_status = cpu_to_le32(olinfo_status);
7873}
7874
7875static int __ixgbe_maybe_stop_tx(struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring, u16 size)
7876{
7877 netif_stop_subqueue(tx_ring->netdev, tx_ring->queue_index);
7878
7879 /* Herbert's original patch had:
7880 * smp_mb__after_netif_stop_queue();
7881 * but since that doesn't exist yet, just open code it.
7882 */
7883 smp_mb();
7884
7885 /* We need to check again in a case another CPU has just
7886 * made room available.
7887 */
7888 if (likely(ixgbe_desc_unused(tx_ring) < size))
7889 return -EBUSY;
7890
7891 /* A reprieve! - use start_queue because it doesn't call schedule */
7892 netif_start_subqueue(tx_ring->netdev, tx_ring->queue_index);
7893 ++tx_ring->tx_stats.restart_queue;
7894 return 0;
7895}
7896
7897static inline int ixgbe_maybe_stop_tx(struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring, u16 size)
7898{
7899 if (likely(ixgbe_desc_unused(tx_ring) >= size))
7900 return 0;
7901
7902 return __ixgbe_maybe_stop_tx(tx_ring, size);
7903}
7904
7905#define IXGBE_TXD_CMD (IXGBE_TXD_CMD_EOP | \
7906 IXGBE_TXD_CMD_RS)
7907
7908static int ixgbe_tx_map(struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring,
7909 struct ixgbe_tx_buffer *first,
7910 const u8 hdr_len)
7911{
7912 struct sk_buff *skb = first->skb;
7913 struct ixgbe_tx_buffer *tx_buffer;
7914 union ixgbe_adv_tx_desc *tx_desc;
7915 struct skb_frag_struct *frag;
7916 dma_addr_t dma;
7917 unsigned int data_len, size;
7918 u32 tx_flags = first->tx_flags;
7919 u32 cmd_type = ixgbe_tx_cmd_type(skb, tx_flags);
7920 u16 i = tx_ring->next_to_use;
7921
7922 tx_desc = IXGBE_TX_DESC(tx_ring, i);
7923
7924 ixgbe_tx_olinfo_status(tx_desc, tx_flags, skb->len - hdr_len);
7925
7926 size = skb_headlen(skb);
7927 data_len = skb->data_len;
7928
7929#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
7930 if (tx_flags & IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_FCOE) {
7931 if (data_len < sizeof(struct fcoe_crc_eof)) {
7932 size -= sizeof(struct fcoe_crc_eof) - data_len;
7933 data_len = 0;
7934 } else {
7935 data_len -= sizeof(struct fcoe_crc_eof);
7936 }
7937 }
7938
7939#endif
7940 dma = dma_map_single(tx_ring->dev, skb->data, size, DMA_TO_DEVICE);
7941
7942 tx_buffer = first;
7943
7944 for (frag = &skb_shinfo(skb)->frags[0];; frag++) {
7945 if (dma_mapping_error(tx_ring->dev, dma))
7946 goto dma_error;
7947
7948 /* record length, and DMA address */
7949 dma_unmap_len_set(tx_buffer, len, size);
7950 dma_unmap_addr_set(tx_buffer, dma, dma);
7951
7952 tx_desc->read.buffer_addr = cpu_to_le64(dma);
7953
7954 while (unlikely(size > IXGBE_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD)) {
7955 tx_desc->read.cmd_type_len =
7956 cpu_to_le32(cmd_type ^ IXGBE_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD);
7957
7958 i++;
7959 tx_desc++;
7960 if (i == tx_ring->count) {
7961 tx_desc = IXGBE_TX_DESC(tx_ring, 0);
7962 i = 0;
7963 }
7964 tx_desc->read.olinfo_status = 0;
7965
7966 dma += IXGBE_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD;
7967 size -= IXGBE_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD;
7968
7969 tx_desc->read.buffer_addr = cpu_to_le64(dma);
7970 }
7971
7972 if (likely(!data_len))
7973 break;
7974
7975 tx_desc->read.cmd_type_len = cpu_to_le32(cmd_type ^ size);
7976
7977 i++;
7978 tx_desc++;
7979 if (i == tx_ring->count) {
7980 tx_desc = IXGBE_TX_DESC(tx_ring, 0);
7981 i = 0;
7982 }
7983 tx_desc->read.olinfo_status = 0;
7984
7985#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
7986 size = min_t(unsigned int, data_len, skb_frag_size(frag));
7987#else
7988 size = skb_frag_size(frag);
7989#endif
7990 data_len -= size;
7991
7992 dma = skb_frag_dma_map(tx_ring->dev, frag, 0, size,
7993 DMA_TO_DEVICE);
7994
7995 tx_buffer = &tx_ring->tx_buffer_info[i];
7996 }
7997
7998 /* write last descriptor with RS and EOP bits */
7999 cmd_type |= size | IXGBE_TXD_CMD;
8000 tx_desc->read.cmd_type_len = cpu_to_le32(cmd_type);
8001
8002 netdev_tx_sent_queue(txring_txq(tx_ring), first->bytecount);
8003
8004 /* set the timestamp */
8005 first->time_stamp = jiffies;
8006
8007 /*
8008 * Force memory writes to complete before letting h/w know there
8009 * are new descriptors to fetch. (Only applicable for weak-ordered
8010 * memory model archs, such as IA-64).
8011 *
8012 * We also need this memory barrier to make certain all of the
8013 * status bits have been updated before next_to_watch is written.
8014 */
8015 wmb();
8016
8017 /* set next_to_watch value indicating a packet is present */
8018 first->next_to_watch = tx_desc;
8019
8020 i++;
8021 if (i == tx_ring->count)
8022 i = 0;
8023
8024 tx_ring->next_to_use = i;
8025
8026 ixgbe_maybe_stop_tx(tx_ring, DESC_NEEDED);
8027
8028 if (netif_xmit_stopped(txring_txq(tx_ring)) || !skb->xmit_more) {
8029 writel(i, tx_ring->tail);
8030
8031 /* we need this if more than one processor can write to our tail
8032 * at a time, it synchronizes IO on IA64/Altix systems
8033 */
8034 mmiowb();
8035 }
8036
8037 return 0;
8038dma_error:
8039 dev_err(tx_ring->dev, "TX DMA map failed\n");
8040
8041 /* clear dma mappings for failed tx_buffer_info map */
8042 for (;;) {
8043 tx_buffer = &tx_ring->tx_buffer_info[i];
8044 if (dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len))
8045 dma_unmap_page(tx_ring->dev,
8046 dma_unmap_addr(tx_buffer, dma),
8047 dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len),
8048 DMA_TO_DEVICE);
8049 dma_unmap_len_set(tx_buffer, len, 0);
8050 if (tx_buffer == first)
8051 break;
8052 if (i == 0)
8053 i += tx_ring->count;
8054 i--;
8055 }
8056
8057 dev_kfree_skb_any(first->skb);
8058 first->skb = NULL;
8059
8060 tx_ring->next_to_use = i;
8061
8062 return -1;
8063}
8064
8065static void ixgbe_atr(struct ixgbe_ring *ring,
8066 struct ixgbe_tx_buffer *first)
8067{
8068 struct ixgbe_q_vector *q_vector = ring->q_vector;
8069 union ixgbe_atr_hash_dword input = { .dword = 0 };
8070 union ixgbe_atr_hash_dword common = { .dword = 0 };
8071 union {
8072 unsigned char *network;
8073 struct iphdr *ipv4;
8074 struct ipv6hdr *ipv6;
8075 } hdr;
8076 struct tcphdr *th;
8077 unsigned int hlen;
8078 struct sk_buff *skb;
8079 __be16 vlan_id;
8080 int l4_proto;
8081
8082 /* if ring doesn't have a interrupt vector, cannot perform ATR */
8083 if (!q_vector)
8084 return;
8085
8086 /* do nothing if sampling is disabled */
8087 if (!ring->atr_sample_rate)
8088 return;
8089
8090 ring->atr_count++;
8091
8092 /* currently only IPv4/IPv6 with TCP is supported */
8093 if ((first->protocol != htons(ETH_P_IP)) &&
8094 (first->protocol != htons(ETH_P_IPV6)))
8095 return;
8096
8097 /* snag network header to get L4 type and address */
8098 skb = first->skb;
8099 hdr.network = skb_network_header(skb);
8100 if (unlikely(hdr.network <= skb->data))
8101 return;
8102 if (skb->encapsulation &&
8103 first->protocol == htons(ETH_P_IP) &&
8104 hdr.ipv4->protocol == IPPROTO_UDP) {
8105 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = q_vector->adapter;
8106
8107 if (unlikely(skb_tail_pointer(skb) < hdr.network +
8108 VXLAN_HEADROOM))
8109 return;
8110
8111 /* verify the port is recognized as VXLAN */
8112 if (adapter->vxlan_port &&
8113 udp_hdr(skb)->dest == adapter->vxlan_port)
8114 hdr.network = skb_inner_network_header(skb);
8115
8116 if (adapter->geneve_port &&
8117 udp_hdr(skb)->dest == adapter->geneve_port)
8118 hdr.network = skb_inner_network_header(skb);
8119 }
8120
8121 /* Make sure we have at least [minimum IPv4 header + TCP]
8122 * or [IPv6 header] bytes
8123 */
8124 if (unlikely(skb_tail_pointer(skb) < hdr.network + 40))
8125 return;
8126
8127 /* Currently only IPv4/IPv6 with TCP is supported */
8128 switch (hdr.ipv4->version) {
8129 case IPVERSION:
8130 /* access ihl as u8 to avoid unaligned access on ia64 */
8131 hlen = (hdr.network[0] & 0x0F) << 2;
8132 l4_proto = hdr.ipv4->protocol;
8133 break;
8134 case 6:
8135 hlen = hdr.network - skb->data;
8136 l4_proto = ipv6_find_hdr(skb, &hlen, IPPROTO_TCP, NULL, NULL);
8137 hlen -= hdr.network - skb->data;
8138 break;
8139 default:
8140 return;
8141 }
8142
8143 if (l4_proto != IPPROTO_TCP)
8144 return;
8145
8146 if (unlikely(skb_tail_pointer(skb) < hdr.network +
8147 hlen + sizeof(struct tcphdr)))
8148 return;
8149
8150 th = (struct tcphdr *)(hdr.network + hlen);
8151
8152 /* skip this packet since the socket is closing */
8153 if (th->fin)
8154 return;
8155
8156 /* sample on all syn packets or once every atr sample count */
8157 if (!th->syn && (ring->atr_count < ring->atr_sample_rate))
8158 return;
8159
8160 /* reset sample count */
8161 ring->atr_count = 0;
8162
8163 vlan_id = htons(first->tx_flags >> IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_SHIFT);
8164
8165 /*
8166 * src and dst are inverted, think how the receiver sees them
8167 *
8168 * The input is broken into two sections, a non-compressed section
8169 * containing vm_pool, vlan_id, and flow_type. The rest of the data
8170 * is XORed together and stored in the compressed dword.
8171 */
8172 input.formatted.vlan_id = vlan_id;
8173
8174 /*
8175 * since src port and flex bytes occupy the same word XOR them together
8176 * and write the value to source port portion of compressed dword
8177 */
8178 if (first->tx_flags & (IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_SW_VLAN | IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_HW_VLAN))
8179 common.port.src ^= th->dest ^ htons(ETH_P_8021Q);
8180 else
8181 common.port.src ^= th->dest ^ first->protocol;
8182 common.port.dst ^= th->source;
8183
8184 switch (hdr.ipv4->version) {
8185 case IPVERSION:
8186 input.formatted.flow_type = IXGBE_ATR_FLOW_TYPE_TCPV4;
8187 common.ip ^= hdr.ipv4->saddr ^ hdr.ipv4->daddr;
8188 break;
8189 case 6:
8190 input.formatted.flow_type = IXGBE_ATR_FLOW_TYPE_TCPV6;
8191 common.ip ^= hdr.ipv6->saddr.s6_addr32[0] ^
8192 hdr.ipv6->saddr.s6_addr32[1] ^
8193 hdr.ipv6->saddr.s6_addr32[2] ^
8194 hdr.ipv6->saddr.s6_addr32[3] ^
8195 hdr.ipv6->daddr.s6_addr32[0] ^
8196 hdr.ipv6->daddr.s6_addr32[1] ^
8197 hdr.ipv6->daddr.s6_addr32[2] ^
8198 hdr.ipv6->daddr.s6_addr32[3];
8199 break;
8200 default:
8201 break;
8202 }
8203
8204 if (hdr.network != skb_network_header(skb))
8205 input.formatted.flow_type |= IXGBE_ATR_L4TYPE_TUNNEL_MASK;
8206
8207 /* This assumes the Rx queue and Tx queue are bound to the same CPU */
8208 ixgbe_fdir_add_signature_filter_82599(&q_vector->adapter->hw,
8209 input, common, ring->queue_index);
8210}
8211
8212static u16 ixgbe_select_queue(struct net_device *dev, struct sk_buff *skb,
8213 void *accel_priv, select_queue_fallback_t fallback)
8214{
8215 struct ixgbe_fwd_adapter *fwd_adapter = accel_priv;
8216#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
8217 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter;
8218 struct ixgbe_ring_feature *f;
8219 int txq;
8220#endif
8221
8222 if (fwd_adapter)
8223 return skb->queue_mapping + fwd_adapter->tx_base_queue;
8224
8225#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
8226
8227 /*
8228 * only execute the code below if protocol is FCoE
8229 * or FIP and we have FCoE enabled on the adapter
8230 */
8231 switch (vlan_get_protocol(skb)) {
8232 case htons(ETH_P_FCOE):
8233 case htons(ETH_P_FIP):
8234 adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
8235
8236 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FCOE_ENABLED)
8237 break;
8238 /* fall through */
8239 default:
8240 return fallback(dev, skb);
8241 }
8242
8243 f = &adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_FCOE];
8244
8245 txq = skb_rx_queue_recorded(skb) ? skb_get_rx_queue(skb) :
8246 smp_processor_id();
8247
8248 while (txq >= f->indices)
8249 txq -= f->indices;
8250
8251 return txq + f->offset;
8252#else
8253 return fallback(dev, skb);
8254#endif
8255}
8256
8257static int ixgbe_xmit_xdp_ring(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
8258 struct xdp_buff *xdp)
8259{
8260 struct ixgbe_ring *ring = adapter->xdp_ring[smp_processor_id()];
8261 struct ixgbe_tx_buffer *tx_buffer;
8262 union ixgbe_adv_tx_desc *tx_desc;
8263 u32 len, cmd_type;
8264 dma_addr_t dma;
8265 u16 i;
8266
8267 len = xdp->data_end - xdp->data;
8268
8269 if (unlikely(!ixgbe_desc_unused(ring)))
8270 return IXGBE_XDP_CONSUMED;
8271
8272 dma = dma_map_single(ring->dev, xdp->data, len, DMA_TO_DEVICE);
8273 if (dma_mapping_error(ring->dev, dma))
8274 return IXGBE_XDP_CONSUMED;
8275
8276 /* record the location of the first descriptor for this packet */
8277 tx_buffer = &ring->tx_buffer_info[ring->next_to_use];
8278 tx_buffer->bytecount = len;
8279 tx_buffer->gso_segs = 1;
8280 tx_buffer->protocol = 0;
8281
8282 i = ring->next_to_use;
8283 tx_desc = IXGBE_TX_DESC(ring, i);
8284
8285 dma_unmap_len_set(tx_buffer, len, len);
8286 dma_unmap_addr_set(tx_buffer, dma, dma);
8287 tx_buffer->data = xdp->data;
8288 tx_desc->read.buffer_addr = cpu_to_le64(dma);
8289
8290 /* put descriptor type bits */
8291 cmd_type = IXGBE_ADVTXD_DTYP_DATA |
8292 IXGBE_ADVTXD_DCMD_DEXT |
8293 IXGBE_ADVTXD_DCMD_IFCS;
8294 cmd_type |= len | IXGBE_TXD_CMD;
8295 tx_desc->read.cmd_type_len = cpu_to_le32(cmd_type);
8296 tx_desc->read.olinfo_status =
8297 cpu_to_le32(len << IXGBE_ADVTXD_PAYLEN_SHIFT);
8298
8299 /* Avoid any potential race with xdp_xmit and cleanup */
8300 smp_wmb();
8301
8302 /* set next_to_watch value indicating a packet is present */
8303 i++;
8304 if (i == ring->count)
8305 i = 0;
8306
8307 tx_buffer->next_to_watch = tx_desc;
8308 ring->next_to_use = i;
8309
8310 return IXGBE_XDP_TX;
8311}
8312
8313netdev_tx_t ixgbe_xmit_frame_ring(struct sk_buff *skb,
8314 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
8315 struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring)
8316{
8317 struct ixgbe_tx_buffer *first;
8318 int tso;
8319 u32 tx_flags = 0;
8320 unsigned short f;
8321 u16 count = TXD_USE_COUNT(skb_headlen(skb));
8322 __be16 protocol = skb->protocol;
8323 u8 hdr_len = 0;
8324
8325 /*
8326 * need: 1 descriptor per page * PAGE_SIZE/IXGBE_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD,
8327 * + 1 desc for skb_headlen/IXGBE_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD,
8328 * + 2 desc gap to keep tail from touching head,
8329 * + 1 desc for context descriptor,
8330 * otherwise try next time
8331 */
8332 for (f = 0; f < skb_shinfo(skb)->nr_frags; f++)
8333 count += TXD_USE_COUNT(skb_shinfo(skb)->frags[f].size);
8334
8335 if (ixgbe_maybe_stop_tx(tx_ring, count + 3)) {
8336 tx_ring->tx_stats.tx_busy++;
8337 return NETDEV_TX_BUSY;
8338 }
8339
8340 /* record the location of the first descriptor for this packet */
8341 first = &tx_ring->tx_buffer_info[tx_ring->next_to_use];
8342 first->skb = skb;
8343 first->bytecount = skb->len;
8344 first->gso_segs = 1;
8345
8346 /* if we have a HW VLAN tag being added default to the HW one */
8347 if (skb_vlan_tag_present(skb)) {
8348 tx_flags |= skb_vlan_tag_get(skb) << IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_SHIFT;
8349 tx_flags |= IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_HW_VLAN;
8350 /* else if it is a SW VLAN check the next protocol and store the tag */
8351 } else if (protocol == htons(ETH_P_8021Q)) {
8352 struct vlan_hdr *vhdr, _vhdr;
8353 vhdr = skb_header_pointer(skb, ETH_HLEN, sizeof(_vhdr), &_vhdr);
8354 if (!vhdr)
8355 goto out_drop;
8356
8357 tx_flags |= ntohs(vhdr->h_vlan_TCI) <<
8358 IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_SHIFT;
8359 tx_flags |= IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_SW_VLAN;
8360 }
8361 protocol = vlan_get_protocol(skb);
8362
8363 if (unlikely(skb_shinfo(skb)->tx_flags & SKBTX_HW_TSTAMP) &&
8364 adapter->ptp_clock) {
8365 if (!test_and_set_bit_lock(__IXGBE_PTP_TX_IN_PROGRESS,
8366 &adapter->state)) {
8367 skb_shinfo(skb)->tx_flags |= SKBTX_IN_PROGRESS;
8368 tx_flags |= IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_TSTAMP;
8369
8370 /* schedule check for Tx timestamp */
8371 adapter->ptp_tx_skb = skb_get(skb);
8372 adapter->ptp_tx_start = jiffies;
8373 schedule_work(&adapter->ptp_tx_work);
8374 } else {
8375 adapter->tx_hwtstamp_skipped++;
8376 }
8377 }
8378
8379 skb_tx_timestamp(skb);
8380
8381#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
8382 /*
8383 * Use the l2switch_enable flag - would be false if the DMA
8384 * Tx switch had been disabled.
8385 */
8386 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED)
8387 tx_flags |= IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_CC;
8388
8389#endif
8390 /* DCB maps skb priorities 0-7 onto 3 bit PCP of VLAN tag. */
8391 if ((adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED) &&
8392 ((tx_flags & (IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_HW_VLAN | IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_SW_VLAN)) ||
8393 (skb->priority != TC_PRIO_CONTROL))) {
8394 tx_flags &= ~IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_PRIO_MASK;
8395 tx_flags |= (skb->priority & 0x7) <<
8396 IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_PRIO_SHIFT;
8397 if (tx_flags & IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_SW_VLAN) {
8398 struct vlan_ethhdr *vhdr;
8399
8400 if (skb_cow_head(skb, 0))
8401 goto out_drop;
8402 vhdr = (struct vlan_ethhdr *)skb->data;
8403 vhdr->h_vlan_TCI = htons(tx_flags >>
8404 IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_SHIFT);
8405 } else {
8406 tx_flags |= IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_HW_VLAN;
8407 }
8408 }
8409
8410 /* record initial flags and protocol */
8411 first->tx_flags = tx_flags;
8412 first->protocol = protocol;
8413
8414#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
8415 /* setup tx offload for FCoE */
8416 if ((protocol == htons(ETH_P_FCOE)) &&
8417 (tx_ring->netdev->features & (NETIF_F_FSO | NETIF_F_FCOE_CRC))) {
8418 tso = ixgbe_fso(tx_ring, first, &hdr_len);
8419 if (tso < 0)
8420 goto out_drop;
8421
8422 goto xmit_fcoe;
8423 }
8424
8425#endif /* IXGBE_FCOE */
8426 tso = ixgbe_tso(tx_ring, first, &hdr_len);
8427 if (tso < 0)
8428 goto out_drop;
8429 else if (!tso)
8430 ixgbe_tx_csum(tx_ring, first);
8431
8432 /* add the ATR filter if ATR is on */
8433 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_TX_FDIR_INIT_DONE, &tx_ring->state))
8434 ixgbe_atr(tx_ring, first);
8435
8436#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
8437xmit_fcoe:
8438#endif /* IXGBE_FCOE */
8439 if (ixgbe_tx_map(tx_ring, first, hdr_len))
8440 goto cleanup_tx_timestamp;
8441
8442 return NETDEV_TX_OK;
8443
8444out_drop:
8445 dev_kfree_skb_any(first->skb);
8446 first->skb = NULL;
8447cleanup_tx_timestamp:
8448 if (unlikely(tx_flags & IXGBE_TX_FLAGS_TSTAMP)) {
8449 dev_kfree_skb_any(adapter->ptp_tx_skb);
8450 adapter->ptp_tx_skb = NULL;
8451 cancel_work_sync(&adapter->ptp_tx_work);
8452 clear_bit_unlock(__IXGBE_PTP_TX_IN_PROGRESS, &adapter->state);
8453 }
8454
8455 return NETDEV_TX_OK;
8456}
8457
8458static netdev_tx_t __ixgbe_xmit_frame(struct sk_buff *skb,
8459 struct net_device *netdev,
8460 struct ixgbe_ring *ring)
8461{
8462 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8463 struct ixgbe_ring *tx_ring;
8464
8465 /*
8466 * The minimum packet size for olinfo paylen is 17 so pad the skb
8467 * in order to meet this minimum size requirement.
8468 */
8469 if (skb_put_padto(skb, 17))
8470 return NETDEV_TX_OK;
8471
8472 tx_ring = ring ? ring : adapter->tx_ring[skb->queue_mapping];
8473
8474 return ixgbe_xmit_frame_ring(skb, adapter, tx_ring);
8475}
8476
8477static netdev_tx_t ixgbe_xmit_frame(struct sk_buff *skb,
8478 struct net_device *netdev)
8479{
8480 return __ixgbe_xmit_frame(skb, netdev, NULL);
8481}
8482
8483/**
8484 * ixgbe_set_mac - Change the Ethernet Address of the NIC
8485 * @netdev: network interface device structure
8486 * @p: pointer to an address structure
8487 *
8488 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
8489 **/
8490static int ixgbe_set_mac(struct net_device *netdev, void *p)
8491{
8492 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8493 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8494 struct sockaddr *addr = p;
8495
8496 if (!is_valid_ether_addr(addr->sa_data))
8497 return -EADDRNOTAVAIL;
8498
8499 memcpy(netdev->dev_addr, addr->sa_data, netdev->addr_len);
8500 memcpy(hw->mac.addr, addr->sa_data, netdev->addr_len);
8501
8502 ixgbe_mac_set_default_filter(adapter);
8503
8504 return 0;
8505}
8506
8507static int
8508ixgbe_mdio_read(struct net_device *netdev, int prtad, int devad, u16 addr)
8509{
8510 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8511 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8512 u16 value;
8513 int rc;
8514
8515 if (prtad != hw->phy.mdio.prtad)
8516 return -EINVAL;
8517 rc = hw->phy.ops.read_reg(hw, addr, devad, &value);
8518 if (!rc)
8519 rc = value;
8520 return rc;
8521}
8522
8523static int ixgbe_mdio_write(struct net_device *netdev, int prtad, int devad,
8524 u16 addr, u16 value)
8525{
8526 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8527 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8528
8529 if (prtad != hw->phy.mdio.prtad)
8530 return -EINVAL;
8531 return hw->phy.ops.write_reg(hw, addr, devad, value);
8532}
8533
8534static int ixgbe_ioctl(struct net_device *netdev, struct ifreq *req, int cmd)
8535{
8536 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8537
8538 switch (cmd) {
8539 case SIOCSHWTSTAMP:
8540 return ixgbe_ptp_set_ts_config(adapter, req);
8541 case SIOCGHWTSTAMP:
8542 return ixgbe_ptp_get_ts_config(adapter, req);
8543 case SIOCGMIIPHY:
8544 if (!adapter->hw.phy.ops.read_reg)
8545 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
8546 /* fall through */
8547 default:
8548 return mdio_mii_ioctl(&adapter->hw.phy.mdio, if_mii(req), cmd);
8549 }
8550}
8551
8552/**
8553 * ixgbe_add_sanmac_netdev - Add the SAN MAC address to the corresponding
8554 * netdev->dev_addrs
8555 * @netdev: network interface device structure
8556 *
8557 * Returns non-zero on failure
8558 **/
8559static int ixgbe_add_sanmac_netdev(struct net_device *dev)
8560{
8561 int err = 0;
8562 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
8563 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8564
8565 if (is_valid_ether_addr(hw->mac.san_addr)) {
8566 rtnl_lock();
8567 err = dev_addr_add(dev, hw->mac.san_addr, NETDEV_HW_ADDR_T_SAN);
8568 rtnl_unlock();
8569
8570 /* update SAN MAC vmdq pool selection */
8571 hw->mac.ops.set_vmdq_san_mac(hw, VMDQ_P(0));
8572 }
8573 return err;
8574}
8575
8576/**
8577 * ixgbe_del_sanmac_netdev - Removes the SAN MAC address to the corresponding
8578 * netdev->dev_addrs
8579 * @netdev: network interface device structure
8580 *
8581 * Returns non-zero on failure
8582 **/
8583static int ixgbe_del_sanmac_netdev(struct net_device *dev)
8584{
8585 int err = 0;
8586 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
8587 struct ixgbe_mac_info *mac = &adapter->hw.mac;
8588
8589 if (is_valid_ether_addr(mac->san_addr)) {
8590 rtnl_lock();
8591 err = dev_addr_del(dev, mac->san_addr, NETDEV_HW_ADDR_T_SAN);
8592 rtnl_unlock();
8593 }
8594 return err;
8595}

8597#ifdef CONFIG_NET_POLL_CONTROLLER
8598/*
8599 * Polling 'interrupt' - used by things like netconsole to send skbs
8600 * without having to re-enable interrupts. It's not called while
8601 * the interrupt routine is executing.
8602 */
8603static void ixgbe_netpoll(struct net_device *netdev)
8604{
8605 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8606 int i;
8607
8608 /* if interface is down do nothing */
8609 if (test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state))
8610 return;
8611
8612 /* loop through and schedule all active queues */
8613 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_q_vectors; i++)
8614 ixgbe_msix_clean_rings(0, adapter->q_vector[i]);
8615}
8616
8617#endif
8618
8619static void ixgbe_get_ring_stats64(struct rtnl_link_stats64 *stats,
8620 struct ixgbe_ring *ring)
8621{
8622 u64 bytes, packets;
8623 unsigned int start;
8624
8625 if (ring) {
8626 do {
8627 start = u64_stats_fetch_begin_irq(&ring->syncp);
8628 packets = ring->stats.packets;
8629 bytes = ring->stats.bytes;
8630 } while (u64_stats_fetch_retry_irq(&ring->syncp, start));
8631 stats->tx_packets += packets;
8632 stats->tx_bytes += bytes;
8633 }
8634}
8635
8636static void ixgbe_get_stats64(struct net_device *netdev,
8637 struct rtnl_link_stats64 *stats)
8638{
8639 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8640 int i;
8641
8642 rcu_read_lock();
8643 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++) {
8644 struct ixgbe_ring *ring = ACCESS_ONCE(adapter->rx_ring[i]);
8645 u64 bytes, packets;
8646 unsigned int start;
8647
8648 if (ring) {
8649 do {
8650 start = u64_stats_fetch_begin_irq(&ring->syncp);
8651 packets = ring->stats.packets;
8652 bytes = ring->stats.bytes;
8653 } while (u64_stats_fetch_retry_irq(&ring->syncp, start));
8654 stats->rx_packets += packets;
8655 stats->rx_bytes += bytes;
8656 }
8657 }
8658
8659 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++) {
8660 struct ixgbe_ring *ring = ACCESS_ONCE(adapter->tx_ring[i]);
8661
8662 ixgbe_get_ring_stats64(stats, ring);
8663 }
8664 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_xdp_queues; i++) {
8665 struct ixgbe_ring *ring = ACCESS_ONCE(adapter->xdp_ring[i]);
8666
8667 ixgbe_get_ring_stats64(stats, ring);
8668 }
8669 rcu_read_unlock();
8670
8671 /* following stats updated by ixgbe_watchdog_task() */
8672 stats->multicast = netdev->stats.multicast;
8673 stats->rx_errors = netdev->stats.rx_errors;
8674 stats->rx_length_errors = netdev->stats.rx_length_errors;
8675 stats->rx_crc_errors = netdev->stats.rx_crc_errors;
8676 stats->rx_missed_errors = netdev->stats.rx_missed_errors;
8677}
8678
8679#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
8680/**
8681 * ixgbe_validate_rtr - verify 802.1Qp to Rx packet buffer mapping is valid.
8682 * @adapter: pointer to ixgbe_adapter
8683 * @tc: number of traffic classes currently enabled
8684 *
8685 * Configure a valid 802.1Qp to Rx packet buffer mapping ie confirm
8686 * 802.1Q priority maps to a packet buffer that exists.
8687 */
8688static void ixgbe_validate_rtr(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter, u8 tc)
8689{
8690 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8691 u32 reg, rsave;
8692 int i;
8693
8694 /* 82598 have a static priority to TC mapping that can not
8695 * be changed so no validation is needed.
8696 */
8697 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
8698 return;
8699
8700 reg = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_RTRUP2TC);
8701 rsave = reg;
8702
8703 for (i = 0; i < MAX_TRAFFIC_CLASS; i++) {
8704 u8 up2tc = reg >> (i * IXGBE_RTRUP2TC_UP_SHIFT);
8705
8706 /* If up2tc is out of bounds default to zero */
8707 if (up2tc > tc)
8708 reg &= ~(0x7 << IXGBE_RTRUP2TC_UP_SHIFT);
8709 }
8710
8711 if (reg != rsave)
8712 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_RTRUP2TC, reg);
8713
8714 return;
8715}
8716
8717/**
8718 * ixgbe_set_prio_tc_map - Configure netdev prio tc map
8719 * @adapter: Pointer to adapter struct
8720 *
8721 * Populate the netdev user priority to tc map
8722 */
8723static void ixgbe_set_prio_tc_map(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
8724{
8725 struct net_device *dev = adapter->netdev;
8726 struct ixgbe_dcb_config *dcb_cfg = &adapter->dcb_cfg;
8727 struct ieee_ets *ets = adapter->ixgbe_ieee_ets;
8728 u8 prio;
8729
8730 for (prio = 0; prio < MAX_USER_PRIORITY; prio++) {
8731 u8 tc = 0;
8732
8733 if (adapter->dcbx_cap & DCB_CAP_DCBX_VER_CEE)
8734 tc = ixgbe_dcb_get_tc_from_up(dcb_cfg, 0, prio);
8735 else if (ets)
8736 tc = ets->prio_tc[prio];
8737
8738 netdev_set_prio_tc_map(dev, prio, tc);
8739 }
8740}
8741
8742#endif /* CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB */
8743/**
8744 * ixgbe_setup_tc - configure net_device for multiple traffic classes
8745 *
8746 * @netdev: net device to configure
8747 * @tc: number of traffic classes to enable
8748 */
8749int ixgbe_setup_tc(struct net_device *dev, u8 tc)
8750{
8751 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
8752 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8753 bool pools;
8754
8755 /* Hardware supports up to 8 traffic classes */
8756 if (tc > adapter->dcb_cfg.num_tcs.pg_tcs)
8757 return -EINVAL;
8758
8759 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB && tc && tc < MAX_TRAFFIC_CLASS)
8760 return -EINVAL;
8761
8762 pools = (find_first_zero_bit(&adapter->fwd_bitmask, 32) > 1);
8763 if (tc && pools && adapter->num_rx_pools > IXGBE_MAX_DCBMACVLANS)
8764 return -EBUSY;
8765
8766 /* Hardware has to reinitialize queues and interrupts to
8767 * match packet buffer alignment. Unfortunately, the
8768 * hardware is not flexible enough to do this dynamically.
8769 */
8770 if (netif_running(dev))
8771 ixgbe_close(dev);
8772 else
8773 ixgbe_reset(adapter);
8774
8775 ixgbe_clear_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
8776
8777#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
8778 if (tc) {
8779 netdev_set_num_tc(dev, tc);
8780 ixgbe_set_prio_tc_map(adapter);
8781
8782 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED;
8783
8784 if (adapter->hw.mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB) {
8785 adapter->last_lfc_mode = adapter->hw.fc.requested_mode;
8786 adapter->hw.fc.requested_mode = ixgbe_fc_none;
8787 }
8788 } else {
8789 netdev_reset_tc(dev);
8790
8791 if (adapter->hw.mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
8792 adapter->hw.fc.requested_mode = adapter->last_lfc_mode;
8793
8794 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED;
8795
8796 adapter->temp_dcb_cfg.pfc_mode_enable = false;
8797 adapter->dcb_cfg.pfc_mode_enable = false;
8798 }
8799
8800 ixgbe_validate_rtr(adapter, tc);
8801
8802#endif /* CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB */
8803 ixgbe_init_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
8804
8805 if (netif_running(dev))
8806 return ixgbe_open(dev);
8807
8808 return 0;
8809}
8810
8811static int ixgbe_delete_clsu32(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
8812 struct tc_cls_u32_offload *cls)
8813{
8814 u32 hdl = cls->knode.handle;
8815 u32 uhtid = TC_U32_USERHTID(cls->knode.handle);
8816 u32 loc = cls->knode.handle & 0xfffff;
8817 int err = 0, i, j;
8818 struct ixgbe_jump_table *jump = NULL;
8819
8820 if (loc > IXGBE_MAX_HW_ENTRIES)
8821 return -EINVAL;
8822
8823 if ((uhtid != 0x800) && (uhtid >= IXGBE_MAX_LINK_HANDLE))
8824 return -EINVAL;
8825
8826 /* Clear this filter in the link data it is associated with */
8827 if (uhtid != 0x800) {
8828 jump = adapter->jump_tables[uhtid];
8829 if (!jump)
8830 return -EINVAL;
8831 if (!test_bit(loc - 1, jump->child_loc_map))
8832 return -EINVAL;
8833 clear_bit(loc - 1, jump->child_loc_map);
8834 }
8835
8836 /* Check if the filter being deleted is a link */
8837 for (i = 1; i < IXGBE_MAX_LINK_HANDLE; i++) {
8838 jump = adapter->jump_tables[i];
8839 if (jump && jump->link_hdl == hdl) {
8840 /* Delete filters in the hardware in the child hash
8841 * table associated with this link
8842 */
8843 for (j = 0; j < IXGBE_MAX_HW_ENTRIES; j++) {
8844 if (!test_bit(j, jump->child_loc_map))
8845 continue;
8846 spin_lock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
8847 err = ixgbe_update_ethtool_fdir_entry(adapter,
8848 NULL,
8849 j + 1);
8850 spin_unlock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
8851 clear_bit(j, jump->child_loc_map);
8852 }
8853 /* Remove resources for this link */
8854 kfree(jump->input);
8855 kfree(jump->mask);
8856 kfree(jump);
8857 adapter->jump_tables[i] = NULL;
8858 return err;
8859 }
8860 }
8861
8862 spin_lock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
8863 err = ixgbe_update_ethtool_fdir_entry(adapter, NULL, loc);
8864 spin_unlock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
8865 return err;
8866}
8867
8868static int ixgbe_configure_clsu32_add_hnode(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
8869 struct tc_cls_u32_offload *cls)
8870{
8871 u32 uhtid = TC_U32_USERHTID(cls->hnode.handle);
8872
8873 if (uhtid >= IXGBE_MAX_LINK_HANDLE)
8874 return -EINVAL;
8875
8876 /* This ixgbe devices do not support hash tables at the moment
8877 * so abort when given hash tables.
8878 */
8879 if (cls->hnode.divisor > 0)
8880 return -EINVAL;
8881
8882 set_bit(uhtid - 1, &adapter->tables);
8883 return 0;
8884}
8885
8886static int ixgbe_configure_clsu32_del_hnode(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
8887 struct tc_cls_u32_offload *cls)
8888{
8889 u32 uhtid = TC_U32_USERHTID(cls->hnode.handle);
8890
8891 if (uhtid >= IXGBE_MAX_LINK_HANDLE)
8892 return -EINVAL;
8893
8894 clear_bit(uhtid - 1, &adapter->tables);
8895 return 0;
8896}
8897
8898#ifdef CONFIG_NET_CLS_ACT
8899struct upper_walk_data {
8900 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter;
8901 u64 action;
8902 int ifindex;
8903 u8 queue;
8904};
8905
8906static int get_macvlan_queue(struct net_device *upper, void *_data)
8907{
8908 if (netif_is_macvlan(upper)) {
8909 struct macvlan_dev *dfwd = netdev_priv(upper);
8910 struct ixgbe_fwd_adapter *vadapter = dfwd->fwd_priv;
8911 struct upper_walk_data *data = _data;
8912 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = data->adapter;
8913 int ifindex = data->ifindex;
8914
8915 if (vadapter && vadapter->netdev->ifindex == ifindex) {
8916 data->queue = adapter->rx_ring[vadapter->rx_base_queue]->reg_idx;
8917 data->action = data->queue;
8918 return 1;
8919 }
8920 }
8921
8922 return 0;
8923}
8924
8925static int handle_redirect_action(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter, int ifindex,
8926 u8 *queue, u64 *action)
8927{
8928 unsigned int num_vfs = adapter->num_vfs, vf;
8929 struct upper_walk_data data;
8930 struct net_device *upper;
8931
8932 /* redirect to a SRIOV VF */
8933 for (vf = 0; vf < num_vfs; ++vf) {
8934 upper = pci_get_drvdata(adapter->vfinfo[vf].vfdev);
8935 if (upper->ifindex == ifindex) {
8936 if (adapter->num_rx_pools > 1)
8937 *queue = vf * 2;
8938 else
8939 *queue = vf * adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool;
8940
8941 *action = vf + 1;
8942 *action <<= ETHTOOL_RX_FLOW_SPEC_RING_VF_OFF;
8943 return 0;
8944 }
8945 }
8946
8947 /* redirect to a offloaded macvlan netdev */
8948 data.adapter = adapter;
8949 data.ifindex = ifindex;
8950 data.action = 0;
8951 data.queue = 0;
8952 if (netdev_walk_all_upper_dev_rcu(adapter->netdev,
8953 get_macvlan_queue, &data)) {
8954 *action = data.action;
8955 *queue = data.queue;
8956
8957 return 0;
8958 }
8959
8960 return -EINVAL;
8961}
8962
8963static int parse_tc_actions(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
8964 struct tcf_exts *exts, u64 *action, u8 *queue)
8965{
8966 const struct tc_action *a;
8967 LIST_HEAD(actions);
8968 int err;
8969
8970 if (!tcf_exts_has_actions(exts))
8971 return -EINVAL;
8972
8973 tcf_exts_to_list(exts, &actions);
8974 list_for_each_entry(a, &actions, list) {
8975
8976 /* Drop action */
8977 if (is_tcf_gact_shot(a)) {
8978 *action = IXGBE_FDIR_DROP_QUEUE;
8979 *queue = IXGBE_FDIR_DROP_QUEUE;
8980 return 0;
8981 }
8982
8983 /* Redirect to a VF or a offloaded macvlan */
8984 if (is_tcf_mirred_egress_redirect(a)) {
8985 int ifindex = tcf_mirred_ifindex(a);
8986
8987 err = handle_redirect_action(adapter, ifindex, queue,
8988 action);
8989 if (err == 0)
8990 return err;
8991 }
8992 }
8993
8994 return -EINVAL;
8995}
8996#else
8997static int parse_tc_actions(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
8998 struct tcf_exts *exts, u64 *action, u8 *queue)
8999{
9000 return -EINVAL;
9001}
9002#endif /* CONFIG_NET_CLS_ACT */
9003
9004static int ixgbe_clsu32_build_input(struct ixgbe_fdir_filter *input,
9005 union ixgbe_atr_input *mask,
9006 struct tc_cls_u32_offload *cls,
9007 struct ixgbe_mat_field *field_ptr,
9008 struct ixgbe_nexthdr *nexthdr)
9009{
9010 int i, j, off;
9011 __be32 val, m;
9012 bool found_entry = false, found_jump_field = false;
9013
9014 for (i = 0; i < cls->knode.sel->nkeys; i++) {
9015 off = cls->knode.sel->keys[i].off;
9016 val = cls->knode.sel->keys[i].val;
9017 m = cls->knode.sel->keys[i].mask;
9018
9019 for (j = 0; field_ptr[j].val; j++) {
9020 if (field_ptr[j].off == off) {
9021 field_ptr[j].val(input, mask, val, m);
9022 input->filter.formatted.flow_type |=
9023 field_ptr[j].type;
9024 found_entry = true;
9025 break;
9026 }
9027 }
9028 if (nexthdr) {
9029 if (nexthdr->off == cls->knode.sel->keys[i].off &&
9030 nexthdr->val == cls->knode.sel->keys[i].val &&
9031 nexthdr->mask == cls->knode.sel->keys[i].mask)
9032 found_jump_field = true;
9033 else
9034 continue;
9035 }
9036 }
9037
9038 if (nexthdr && !found_jump_field)
9039 return -EINVAL;
9040
9041 if (!found_entry)
9042 return 0;
9043
9044 mask->formatted.flow_type = IXGBE_ATR_L4TYPE_IPV6_MASK |
9045 IXGBE_ATR_L4TYPE_MASK;
9046
9047 if (input->filter.formatted.flow_type == IXGBE_ATR_FLOW_TYPE_IPV4)
9048 mask->formatted.flow_type &= IXGBE_ATR_L4TYPE_IPV6_MASK;
9049
9050 return 0;
9051}
9052
9053static int ixgbe_configure_clsu32(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
9054 struct tc_cls_u32_offload *cls)
9055{
9056 __be16 protocol = cls->common.protocol;
9057 u32 loc = cls->knode.handle & 0xfffff;
9058 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9059 struct ixgbe_mat_field *field_ptr;
9060 struct ixgbe_fdir_filter *input = NULL;
9061 union ixgbe_atr_input *mask = NULL;
9062 struct ixgbe_jump_table *jump = NULL;
9063 int i, err = -EINVAL;
9064 u8 queue;
9065 u32 uhtid, link_uhtid;
9066
9067 uhtid = TC_U32_USERHTID(cls->knode.handle);
9068 link_uhtid = TC_U32_USERHTID(cls->knode.link_handle);
9069
9070 /* At the moment cls_u32 jumps to network layer and skips past
9071 * L2 headers. The canonical method to match L2 frames is to use
9072 * negative values. However this is error prone at best but really
9073 * just broken because there is no way to "know" what sort of hdr
9074 * is in front of the network layer. Fix cls_u32 to support L2
9075 * headers when needed.
9076 */
9077 if (protocol != htons(ETH_P_IP))
9078 return err;
9079
9080 if (loc >= ((1024 << adapter->fdir_pballoc) - 2)) {
9081 e_err(drv, "Location out of range\n");
9082 return err;
9083 }
9084
9085 /* cls u32 is a graph starting at root node 0x800. The driver tracks
9086 * links and also the fields used to advance the parser across each
9087 * link (e.g. nexthdr/eat parameters from 'tc'). This way we can map
9088 * the u32 graph onto the hardware parse graph denoted in ixgbe_model.h
9089 * To add support for new nodes update ixgbe_model.h parse structures
9090 * this function _should_ be generic try not to hardcode values here.
9091 */
9092 if (uhtid == 0x800) {
9093 field_ptr = (adapter->jump_tables[0])->mat;
9094 } else {
9095 if (uhtid >= IXGBE_MAX_LINK_HANDLE)
9096 return err;
9097 if (!adapter->jump_tables[uhtid])
9098 return err;
9099 field_ptr = (adapter->jump_tables[uhtid])->mat;
9100 }
9101
9102 if (!field_ptr)
9103 return err;
9104
9105 /* At this point we know the field_ptr is valid and need to either
9106 * build cls_u32 link or attach filter. Because adding a link to
9107 * a handle that does not exist is invalid and the same for adding
9108 * rules to handles that don't exist.
9109 */
9110
9111 if (link_uhtid) {
9112 struct ixgbe_nexthdr *nexthdr = ixgbe_ipv4_jumps;
9113
9114 if (link_uhtid >= IXGBE_MAX_LINK_HANDLE)
9115 return err;
9116
9117 if (!test_bit(link_uhtid - 1, &adapter->tables))
9118 return err;
9119
9120 /* Multiple filters as links to the same hash table are not
9121 * supported. To add a new filter with the same next header
9122 * but different match/jump conditions, create a new hash table
9123 * and link to it.
9124 */
9125 if (adapter->jump_tables[link_uhtid] &&
9126 (adapter->jump_tables[link_uhtid])->link_hdl) {
9127 e_err(drv, "Link filter exists for link: %x\n",
9128 link_uhtid);
9129 return err;
9130 }
9131
9132 for (i = 0; nexthdr[i].jump; i++) {
9133 if (nexthdr[i].o != cls->knode.sel->offoff ||
9134 nexthdr[i].s != cls->knode.sel->offshift ||
9135 nexthdr[i].m != cls->knode.sel->offmask)
9136 return err;
9137
9138 jump = kzalloc(sizeof(*jump), GFP_KERNEL);
9139 if (!jump)
9140 return -ENOMEM;
9141 input = kzalloc(sizeof(*input), GFP_KERNEL);
9142 if (!input) {
9143 err = -ENOMEM;
9144 goto free_jump;
9145 }
9146 mask = kzalloc(sizeof(*mask), GFP_KERNEL);
9147 if (!mask) {
9148 err = -ENOMEM;
9149 goto free_input;
9150 }
9151 jump->input = input;
9152 jump->mask = mask;
9153 jump->link_hdl = cls->knode.handle;
9154
9155 err = ixgbe_clsu32_build_input(input, mask, cls,
9156 field_ptr, &nexthdr[i]);
9157 if (!err) {
9158 jump->mat = nexthdr[i].jump;
9159 adapter->jump_tables[link_uhtid] = jump;
9160 break;
9161 }
9162 }
9163 return 0;
9164 }
9165
9166 input = kzalloc(sizeof(*input), GFP_KERNEL);
9167 if (!input)
9168 return -ENOMEM;
9169 mask = kzalloc(sizeof(*mask), GFP_KERNEL);
9170 if (!mask) {
9171 err = -ENOMEM;
9172 goto free_input;
9173 }
9174
9175 if ((uhtid != 0x800) && (adapter->jump_tables[uhtid])) {
9176 if ((adapter->jump_tables[uhtid])->input)
9177 memcpy(input, (adapter->jump_tables[uhtid])->input,
9178 sizeof(*input));
9179 if ((adapter->jump_tables[uhtid])->mask)
9180 memcpy(mask, (adapter->jump_tables[uhtid])->mask,
9181 sizeof(*mask));
9182
9183 /* Lookup in all child hash tables if this location is already
9184 * filled with a filter
9185 */
9186 for (i = 1; i < IXGBE_MAX_LINK_HANDLE; i++) {
9187 struct ixgbe_jump_table *link = adapter->jump_tables[i];
9188
9189 if (link && (test_bit(loc - 1, link->child_loc_map))) {
9190 e_err(drv, "Filter exists in location: %x\n",
9191 loc);
9192 err = -EINVAL;
9193 goto err_out;
9194 }
9195 }
9196 }
9197 err = ixgbe_clsu32_build_input(input, mask, cls, field_ptr, NULL);
9198 if (err)
9199 goto err_out;
9200
9201 err = parse_tc_actions(adapter, cls->knode.exts, &input->action,
9202 &queue);
9203 if (err < 0)
9204 goto err_out;
9205
9206 input->sw_idx = loc;
9207
9208 spin_lock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
9209
9210 if (hlist_empty(&adapter->fdir_filter_list)) {
9211 memcpy(&adapter->fdir_mask, mask, sizeof(*mask));
9212 err = ixgbe_fdir_set_input_mask_82599(hw, mask);
9213 if (err)
9214 goto err_out_w_lock;
9215 } else if (memcmp(&adapter->fdir_mask, mask, sizeof(*mask))) {
9216 err = -EINVAL;
9217 goto err_out_w_lock;
9218 }
9219
9220 ixgbe_atr_compute_perfect_hash_82599(&input->filter, mask);
9221 err = ixgbe_fdir_write_perfect_filter_82599(hw, &input->filter,
9222 input->sw_idx, queue);
9223 if (!err)
9224 ixgbe_update_ethtool_fdir_entry(adapter, input, input->sw_idx);
9225 spin_unlock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
9226
9227 if ((uhtid != 0x800) && (adapter->jump_tables[uhtid]))
9228 set_bit(loc - 1, (adapter->jump_tables[uhtid])->child_loc_map);
9229
9230 kfree(mask);
9231 return err;
9232err_out_w_lock:
9233 spin_unlock(&adapter->fdir_perfect_lock);
9234err_out:
9235 kfree(mask);
9236free_input:
9237 kfree(input);
9238free_jump:
9239 kfree(jump);
9240 return err;
9241}
9242
9243static int ixgbe_setup_tc_cls_u32(struct net_device *dev,
9244 struct tc_cls_u32_offload *cls_u32)
9245{
9246 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
9247
9248 if (!is_classid_clsact_ingress(cls_u32->common.classid) ||
9249 cls_u32->common.chain_index)
9250 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
9251
9252 switch (cls_u32->command) {
9253 case TC_CLSU32_NEW_KNODE:
9254 case TC_CLSU32_REPLACE_KNODE:
9255 return ixgbe_configure_clsu32(adapter, cls_u32);
9256 case TC_CLSU32_DELETE_KNODE:
9257 return ixgbe_delete_clsu32(adapter, cls_u32);
9258 case TC_CLSU32_NEW_HNODE:
9259 case TC_CLSU32_REPLACE_HNODE:
9260 return ixgbe_configure_clsu32_add_hnode(adapter, cls_u32);
9261 case TC_CLSU32_DELETE_HNODE:
9262 return ixgbe_configure_clsu32_del_hnode(adapter, cls_u32);
9263 default:
9264 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
9265 }
9266}

9269 struct tc_mqprio_qopt *mqprio)
9270{
9271 mqprio->hw = TC_MQPRIO_HW_OFFLOAD_TCS;
9272 return ixgbe_setup_tc(dev, mqprio->num_tc);
9273}

9275static int __ixgbe_setup_tc(struct net_device *dev, enum tc_setup_type type,
9276 void *type_data)

9280 return ixgbe_setup_tc_cls_u32(dev, type_data);
9281 case TC_SETUP_MQPRIO:
9282 return ixgbe_setup_tc_mqprio(dev, type_data);
9283 default:
9284 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
9285 }
9286}

9299void ixgbe_do_reset(struct net_device *netdev)
9300{

9302
9303 if (netif_running(netdev))
9304 ixgbe_reinit_locked(adapter);
9305 else
9306 ixgbe_reset(adapter);
9307}
9308
9309static netdev_features_t ixgbe_fix_features(struct net_device *netdev,
9310 netdev_features_t features)
9311{
9312 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9313
9314 /* If Rx checksum is disabled, then RSC/LRO should also be disabled */
9315 if (!(features & NETIF_F_RXCSUM))
9316 features &= ~NETIF_F_LRO;
9317
9318 /* Turn off LRO if not RSC capable */
9319 if (!(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_CAPABLE))
9320 features &= ~NETIF_F_LRO;
9321
9322 return features;
9323}
9324
9325static int ixgbe_set_features(struct net_device *netdev,
9326 netdev_features_t features)
9327{
9328 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9329 netdev_features_t changed = netdev->features ^ features;
9330 bool need_reset = false;
9331
9332 /* Make sure RSC matches LRO, reset if change */
9333 if (!(features & NETIF_F_LRO)) {
9334 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_ENABLED)
9335 need_reset = true;
9336 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_ENABLED;
9337 } else if ((adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_CAPABLE) &&
9338 !(adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_ENABLED)) {
9339 if (adapter->rx_itr_setting == 1 ||
9340 adapter->rx_itr_setting > IXGBE_MIN_RSC_ITR) {
9341 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_ENABLED;
9342 need_reset = true;
9343 } else if ((changed ^ features) & NETIF_F_LRO) {
9344 e_info(probe, "rx-usecs set too low, "
9345 "disabling RSC\n");
9346 }
9347 }
9348
9349 /*
9350 * Check if Flow Director n-tuple support or hw_tc support was
9351 * enabled or disabled. If the state changed, we need to reset.
9352 */
9353 if ((features & NETIF_F_NTUPLE) || (features & NETIF_F_HW_TC)) {
9354 /* turn off ATR, enable perfect filters and reset */
9355 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_PERFECT_CAPABLE))
9356 need_reset = true;
9357
9358 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_HASH_CAPABLE;
9359 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_PERFECT_CAPABLE;
9360 } else {
9361 /* turn off perfect filters, enable ATR and reset */
9362 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_PERFECT_CAPABLE)
9363 need_reset = true;
9364
9365 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_PERFECT_CAPABLE;
9366
9367 /* We cannot enable ATR if SR-IOV is enabled */
9368 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED ||
9369 /* We cannot enable ATR if we have 2 or more tcs */
9370 (netdev_get_num_tc(netdev) > 1) ||
9371 /* We cannot enable ATR if RSS is disabled */
9372 (adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_RSS].limit <= 1) ||
9373 /* A sample rate of 0 indicates ATR disabled */
9374 (!adapter->atr_sample_rate))
9375 ; /* do nothing not supported */
9376 else /* otherwise supported and set the flag */
9377 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_FDIR_HASH_CAPABLE;
9378 }
9379
9380 if (changed & NETIF_F_RXALL)
9381 need_reset = true;
9382
9383 netdev->features = features;
9384
9385 if ((adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_VXLAN_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE)) {
9386 if (features & NETIF_F_RXCSUM) {
9387 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_UDP_TUN_REREG_NEEDED;
9388 } else {
9389 u32 port_mask = IXGBE_VXLANCTRL_VXLAN_UDPPORT_MASK;
9390
9391 ixgbe_clear_udp_tunnel_port(adapter, port_mask);
9392 }
9393 }
9394
9395 if ((adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_GENEVE_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE)) {
9396 if (features & NETIF_F_RXCSUM) {
9397 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_UDP_TUN_REREG_NEEDED;
9398 } else {
9399 u32 port_mask = IXGBE_VXLANCTRL_GENEVE_UDPPORT_MASK;
9400
9401 ixgbe_clear_udp_tunnel_port(adapter, port_mask);
9402 }
9403 }
9404
9405 if (need_reset)
9406 ixgbe_do_reset(netdev);
9407 else if (changed & (NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX |
9408 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER))
9409 ixgbe_set_rx_mode(netdev);
9410
9411 return 0;
9412}
9413
9414/**
9415 * ixgbe_add_udp_tunnel_port - Get notifications about adding UDP tunnel ports
9416 * @dev: The port's netdev
9417 * @ti: Tunnel endpoint information
9418 **/
9419static void ixgbe_add_udp_tunnel_port(struct net_device *dev,
9420 struct udp_tunnel_info *ti)
9421{
9422 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
9423 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9424 __be16 port = ti->port;
9425 u32 port_shift = 0;
9426 u32 reg;
9427
9428 if (ti->sa_family != AF_INET)
9429 return;
9430
9431 switch (ti->type) {
9432 case UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_VXLAN:
9433 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_VXLAN_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE))
9434 return;
9435
9436 if (adapter->vxlan_port == port)
9437 return;
9438
9439 if (adapter->vxlan_port) {
9440 netdev_info(dev,
9441 "VXLAN port %d set, not adding port %d\n",
9442 ntohs(adapter->vxlan_port),
9443 ntohs(port));
9444 return;
9445 }
9446
9447 adapter->vxlan_port = port;
9448 break;
9449 case UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_GENEVE:
9450 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_GENEVE_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE))
9451 return;
9452
9453 if (adapter->geneve_port == port)
9454 return;
9455
9456 if (adapter->geneve_port) {
9457 netdev_info(dev,
9458 "GENEVE port %d set, not adding port %d\n",
9459 ntohs(adapter->geneve_port),
9460 ntohs(port));
9461 return;
9462 }
9463
9464 port_shift = IXGBE_VXLANCTRL_GENEVE_UDPPORT_SHIFT;
9465 adapter->geneve_port = port;
9466 break;
9467 default:
9468 return;
9469 }
9470
9471 reg = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VXLANCTRL) | ntohs(port) << port_shift;
9472 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VXLANCTRL, reg);
9473}
9474
9475/**
9476 * ixgbe_del_udp_tunnel_port - Get notifications about removing UDP tunnel ports
9477 * @dev: The port's netdev
9478 * @ti: Tunnel endpoint information
9479 **/
9480static void ixgbe_del_udp_tunnel_port(struct net_device *dev,
9481 struct udp_tunnel_info *ti)
9482{
9483 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
9484 u32 port_mask;
9485
9486 if (ti->type != UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_VXLAN &&
9487 ti->type != UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_GENEVE)
9488 return;
9489
9490 if (ti->sa_family != AF_INET)
9491 return;
9492
9493 switch (ti->type) {
9494 case UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_VXLAN:
9495 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_VXLAN_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE))
9496 return;
9497
9498 if (adapter->vxlan_port != ti->port) {
9499 netdev_info(dev, "VXLAN port %d not found\n",
9500 ntohs(ti->port));
9501 return;
9502 }
9503
9504 port_mask = IXGBE_VXLANCTRL_VXLAN_UDPPORT_MASK;
9505 break;
9506 case UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_GENEVE:
9507 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_GENEVE_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE))
9508 return;
9509
9510 if (adapter->geneve_port != ti->port) {
9511 netdev_info(dev, "GENEVE port %d not found\n",
9512 ntohs(ti->port));
9513 return;
9514 }
9515
9516 port_mask = IXGBE_VXLANCTRL_GENEVE_UDPPORT_MASK;
9517 break;
9518 default:
9519 return;
9520 }
9521
9522 ixgbe_clear_udp_tunnel_port(adapter, port_mask);
9523 adapter->flags2 |= IXGBE_FLAG2_UDP_TUN_REREG_NEEDED;
9524}
9525
9526static int ixgbe_ndo_fdb_add(struct ndmsg *ndm, struct nlattr *tb[],
9527 struct net_device *dev,
9528 const unsigned char *addr, u16 vid,
9529 u16 flags)
9530{
9531 /* guarantee we can provide a unique filter for the unicast address */
9532 if (is_unicast_ether_addr(addr) || is_link_local_ether_addr(addr)) {
9533 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
9534 u16 pool = VMDQ_P(0);
9535
9536 if (netdev_uc_count(dev) >= ixgbe_available_rars(adapter, pool))
9537 return -ENOMEM;
9538 }
9539
9540 return ndo_dflt_fdb_add(ndm, tb, dev, addr, vid, flags);
9541}
9542
9543/**
9544 * ixgbe_configure_bridge_mode - set various bridge modes
9545 * @adapter - the private structure
9546 * @mode - requested bridge mode
9547 *
9548 * Configure some settings require for various bridge modes.
9549 **/
9550static int ixgbe_configure_bridge_mode(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter,
9551 __u16 mode)
9552{
9553 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9554 unsigned int p, num_pools;
9555 u32 vmdctl;
9556
9557 switch (mode) {
9558 case BRIDGE_MODE_VEPA:
9559 /* disable Tx loopback, rely on switch hairpin mode */
9560 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_PFDTXGSWC, 0);
9561
9562 /* must enable Rx switching replication to allow multicast
9563 * packet reception on all VFs, and to enable source address
9564 * pruning.
9565 */
9566 vmdctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VMD_CTL);
9567 vmdctl |= IXGBE_VT_CTL_REPLEN;
9568 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VMD_CTL, vmdctl);
9569
9570 /* enable Rx source address pruning. Note, this requires
9571 * replication to be enabled or else it does nothing.
9572 */
9573 num_pools = adapter->num_vfs + adapter->num_rx_pools;
9574 for (p = 0; p < num_pools; p++) {
9575 if (hw->mac.ops.set_source_address_pruning)
9576 hw->mac.ops.set_source_address_pruning(hw,
9577 true,
9578 p);
9579 }
9580 break;
9581 case BRIDGE_MODE_VEB:
9582 /* enable Tx loopback for internal VF/PF communication */
9583 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_PFDTXGSWC,
9584 IXGBE_PFDTXGSWC_VT_LBEN);
9585
9586 /* disable Rx switching replication unless we have SR-IOV
9587 * virtual functions
9588 */
9589 vmdctl = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_VMD_CTL);
9590 if (!adapter->num_vfs)
9591 vmdctl &= ~IXGBE_VT_CTL_REPLEN;
9592 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(hw, IXGBE_VMD_CTL, vmdctl);
9593
9594 /* disable Rx source address pruning, since we don't expect to
9595 * be receiving external loopback of our transmitted frames.
9596 */
9597 num_pools = adapter->num_vfs + adapter->num_rx_pools;
9598 for (p = 0; p < num_pools; p++) {
9599 if (hw->mac.ops.set_source_address_pruning)
9600 hw->mac.ops.set_source_address_pruning(hw,
9601 false,
9602 p);
9603 }
9604 break;
9605 default:
9606 return -EINVAL;
9607 }
9608
9609 adapter->bridge_mode = mode;
9610
9611 e_info(drv, "enabling bridge mode: %s\n",
9612 mode == BRIDGE_MODE_VEPA ? "VEPA" : "VEB");
9613
9614 return 0;
9615}
9616
9617static int ixgbe_ndo_bridge_setlink(struct net_device *dev,
9618 struct nlmsghdr *nlh, u16 flags)
9619{
9620 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
9621 struct nlattr *attr, *br_spec;
9622 int rem;
9623
9624 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED))
9625 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
9626
9627 br_spec = nlmsg_find_attr(nlh, sizeof(struct ifinfomsg), IFLA_AF_SPEC);
9628 if (!br_spec)
9629 return -EINVAL;
9630
9631 nla_for_each_nested(attr, br_spec, rem) {
9632 int status;
9633 __u16 mode;
9634
9635 if (nla_type(attr) != IFLA_BRIDGE_MODE)
9636 continue;
9637
9638 if (nla_len(attr) < sizeof(mode))
9639 return -EINVAL;
9640
9641 mode = nla_get_u16(attr);
9642 status = ixgbe_configure_bridge_mode(adapter, mode);
9643 if (status)
9644 return status;
9645
9646 break;
9647 }
9648
9649 return 0;
9650}
9651
9652static int ixgbe_ndo_bridge_getlink(struct sk_buff *skb, u32 pid, u32 seq,
9653 struct net_device *dev,
9654 u32 filter_mask, int nlflags)
9655{
9656 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
9657
9658 if (!(adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED))
9659 return 0;
9660
9661 return ndo_dflt_bridge_getlink(skb, pid, seq, dev,
9662 adapter->bridge_mode, 0, 0, nlflags,
9663 filter_mask, NULL);
9664}
9665
9666static void *ixgbe_fwd_add(struct net_device *pdev, struct net_device *vdev)
9667{
9668 struct ixgbe_fwd_adapter *fwd_adapter = NULL;
9669 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(pdev);
9670 int used_pools = adapter->num_vfs + adapter->num_rx_pools;
9671 unsigned int limit;
9672 int pool, err;
9673
9674 /* Hardware has a limited number of available pools. Each VF, and the
9675 * PF require a pool. Check to ensure we don't attempt to use more
9676 * then the available number of pools.
9677 */
9678 if (used_pools >= IXGBE_MAX_VF_FUNCTIONS)
9679 return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
9680
9681#ifdef CONFIG_RPS
9682 if (vdev->num_rx_queues != vdev->num_tx_queues) {
9683 netdev_info(pdev, "%s: Only supports a single queue count for TX and RX\n",
9684 vdev->name);
9685 return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
9686 }
9687#endif
9688 /* Check for hardware restriction on number of rx/tx queues */
9689 if (vdev->num_tx_queues > IXGBE_MAX_L2A_QUEUES ||
9690 vdev->num_tx_queues == IXGBE_BAD_L2A_QUEUE) {
9691 netdev_info(pdev,
9692 "%s: Supports RX/TX Queue counts 1,2, and 4\n",
9693 pdev->name);
9694 return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
9695 }
9696
9697 if (((adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED) &&
9698 adapter->num_rx_pools > IXGBE_MAX_DCBMACVLANS - 1) ||
9699 (adapter->num_rx_pools > IXGBE_MAX_MACVLANS))
9700 return ERR_PTR(-EBUSY);
9701
9702 fwd_adapter = kzalloc(sizeof(*fwd_adapter), GFP_KERNEL);
9703 if (!fwd_adapter)
9704 return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
9705
9706 pool = find_first_zero_bit(&adapter->fwd_bitmask, 32);
9707 adapter->num_rx_pools++;
9708 set_bit(pool, &adapter->fwd_bitmask);
9709 limit = find_last_bit(&adapter->fwd_bitmask, 32);
9710
9711 /* Enable VMDq flag so device will be set in VM mode */
9712 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED | IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED;
9713 adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_VMDQ].limit = limit + 1;
9714 adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_RSS].limit = vdev->num_tx_queues;
9715
9716 /* Force reinit of ring allocation with VMDQ enabled */
9717 err = ixgbe_setup_tc(pdev, netdev_get_num_tc(pdev));
9718 if (err)
9719 goto fwd_add_err;
9720 fwd_adapter->pool = pool;
9721 fwd_adapter->real_adapter = adapter;
9722
9723 if (netif_running(pdev)) {
9724 err = ixgbe_fwd_ring_up(vdev, fwd_adapter);
9725 if (err)
9726 goto fwd_add_err;
9727 netif_tx_start_all_queues(vdev);
9728 }
9729
9730 return fwd_adapter;
9731fwd_add_err:
9732 /* unwind counter and free adapter struct */
9733 netdev_info(pdev,
9734 "%s: dfwd hardware acceleration failed\n", vdev->name);
9735 clear_bit(pool, &adapter->fwd_bitmask);
9736 adapter->num_rx_pools--;
9737 kfree(fwd_adapter);
9738 return ERR_PTR(err);
9739}
9740
9741static void ixgbe_fwd_del(struct net_device *pdev, void *priv)
9742{
9743 struct ixgbe_fwd_adapter *fwd_adapter = priv;
9744 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = fwd_adapter->real_adapter;
9745 unsigned int limit;
9746
9747 clear_bit(fwd_adapter->pool, &adapter->fwd_bitmask);
9748 adapter->num_rx_pools--;
9749
9750 limit = find_last_bit(&adapter->fwd_bitmask, 32);
9751 adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_VMDQ].limit = limit + 1;
9752 ixgbe_fwd_ring_down(fwd_adapter->netdev, fwd_adapter);
9753 ixgbe_setup_tc(pdev, netdev_get_num_tc(pdev));
9754 netdev_dbg(pdev, "pool %i:%i queues %i:%i VSI bitmask %lx\n",
9755 fwd_adapter->pool, adapter->num_rx_pools,
9756 fwd_adapter->rx_base_queue,
9757 fwd_adapter->rx_base_queue + adapter->num_rx_queues_per_pool,
9758 adapter->fwd_bitmask);
9759 kfree(fwd_adapter);
9760}
9761
9762#define IXGBE_MAX_MAC_HDR_LEN 127
9763#define IXGBE_MAX_NETWORK_HDR_LEN 511
9764
9765static netdev_features_t
9766ixgbe_features_check(struct sk_buff *skb, struct net_device *dev,
9767 netdev_features_t features)
9768{
9769 unsigned int network_hdr_len, mac_hdr_len;
9770
9771 /* Make certain the headers can be described by a context descriptor */
9772 mac_hdr_len = skb_network_header(skb) - skb->data;
9773 if (unlikely(mac_hdr_len > IXGBE_MAX_MAC_HDR_LEN))
9774 return features & ~(NETIF_F_HW_CSUM |
9775 NETIF_F_SCTP_CRC |
9776 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_TX |
9777 NETIF_F_TSO |
9778 NETIF_F_TSO6);
9779
9780 network_hdr_len = skb_checksum_start(skb) - skb_network_header(skb);
9781 if (unlikely(network_hdr_len > IXGBE_MAX_NETWORK_HDR_LEN))
9782 return features & ~(NETIF_F_HW_CSUM |
9783 NETIF_F_SCTP_CRC |
9784 NETIF_F_TSO |
9785 NETIF_F_TSO6);
9786
9787 /* We can only support IPV4 TSO in tunnels if we can mangle the
9788 * inner IP ID field, so strip TSO if MANGLEID is not supported.
9789 */
9790 if (skb->encapsulation && !(features & NETIF_F_TSO_MANGLEID))
9791 features &= ~NETIF_F_TSO;
9792
9793 return features;
9794}
9795
9796static int ixgbe_xdp_setup(struct net_device *dev, struct bpf_prog *prog)
9797{
9798 int i, frame_size = dev->mtu + ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN + VLAN_HLEN;
9799 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
9800 struct bpf_prog *old_prog;
9801
9802 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED)
9803 return -EINVAL;
9804
9805 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED)
9806 return -EINVAL;
9807
9808 /* verify ixgbe ring attributes are sufficient for XDP */
9809 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++) {
9810 struct ixgbe_ring *ring = adapter->rx_ring[i];
9811
9812 if (ring_is_rsc_enabled(ring))
9813 return -EINVAL;
9814
9815 if (frame_size > ixgbe_rx_bufsz(ring))
9816 return -EINVAL;
9817 }
9818
9819 if (nr_cpu_ids > MAX_XDP_QUEUES)
9820 return -ENOMEM;
9821
9822 old_prog = xchg(&adapter->xdp_prog, prog);
9823
9824 /* If transitioning XDP modes reconfigure rings */
9825 if (!!prog != !!old_prog) {
9826 int err = ixgbe_setup_tc(dev, netdev_get_num_tc(dev));
9827
9828 if (err) {
9829 rcu_assign_pointer(adapter->xdp_prog, old_prog);
9830 return -EINVAL;
9831 }
9832 } else {
9833 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++)
9834 xchg(&adapter->rx_ring[i]->xdp_prog, adapter->xdp_prog);
9835 }
9836
9837 if (old_prog)
9838 bpf_prog_put(old_prog);
9839
9840 return 0;
9841}
9842
9843static int ixgbe_xdp(struct net_device *dev, struct netdev_xdp *xdp)
9844{
9845 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
9846
9847 switch (xdp->command) {
9848 case XDP_SETUP_PROG:
9849 return ixgbe_xdp_setup(dev, xdp->prog);
9850 case XDP_QUERY_PROG:
9851 xdp->prog_attached = !!(adapter->xdp_prog);
9852 xdp->prog_id = adapter->xdp_prog ?
9853 adapter->xdp_prog->aux->id : 0;
9854 return 0;
9855 default:
9856 return -EINVAL;
9857 }
9858}
9859
9860static int ixgbe_xdp_xmit(struct net_device *dev, struct xdp_buff *xdp)
9861{
9862 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
9863 struct ixgbe_ring *ring;
9864 int err;
9865
9866 if (unlikely(test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state)))
9867 return -ENETDOWN;
9868
9869 /* During program transitions its possible adapter->xdp_prog is assigned
9870 * but ring has not been configured yet. In this case simply abort xmit.
9871 */
9872 ring = adapter->xdp_prog ? adapter->xdp_ring[smp_processor_id()] : NULL;
9873 if (unlikely(!ring))
9874 return -ENXIO;
9875
9876 err = ixgbe_xmit_xdp_ring(adapter, xdp);
9877 if (err != IXGBE_XDP_TX)
9878 return -ENOSPC;
9879
9880 return 0;
9881}
9882
9883static void ixgbe_xdp_flush(struct net_device *dev)
9884{
9885 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(dev);
9886 struct ixgbe_ring *ring;
9887
9888 /* Its possible the device went down between xdp xmit and flush so
9889 * we need to ensure device is still up.
9890 */
9891 if (unlikely(test_bit(__IXGBE_DOWN, &adapter->state)))
9892 return;
9893
9894 ring = adapter->xdp_prog ? adapter->xdp_ring[smp_processor_id()] : NULL;
9895 if (unlikely(!ring))
9896 return;
9897
9898 /* Force memory writes to complete before letting h/w know there
9899 * are new descriptors to fetch.
9900 */
9901 wmb();
9902 writel(ring->next_to_use, ring->tail);
9903
9904 return;
9905}
