9957/**
9958 * ixgbe_enumerate_functions - Get the number of ports this device has
9959 * @adapter: adapter structure
9960 *
9961 * This function enumerates the phsyical functions co-located on a single slot,
9962 * in order to determine how many ports a device has. This is most useful in
9963 * determining the required GT/s of PCIe bandwidth necessary for optimal
9964 * performance.
9965 **/
9966static inline int ixgbe_enumerate_functions(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter)
9967{
9968 struct pci_dev *entry, *pdev = adapter->pdev;
9969 int physfns = 0;
9970
9971 /* Some cards can not use the generic count PCIe functions method,
9972 * because they are behind a parent switch, so we hardcode these with
9973 * the correct number of functions.
9974 */
9975 if (ixgbe_pcie_from_parent(&adapter->hw))
9976 physfns = 4;
9977
9978 list_for_each_entry(entry, &adapter->pdev->bus->devices, bus_list) {
9979 /* don't count virtual functions */
9980 if (entry->is_virtfn)
9981 continue;
9982
9983 /* When the devices on the bus don't all match our device ID,
9984 * we can't reliably determine the correct number of
9985 * functions. This can occur if a function has been direct
9986 * attached to a virtual machine using VT-d, for example. In
9987 * this case, simply return -1 to indicate this.
9988 */
9989 if ((entry->vendor != pdev->vendor) ||
9990 (entry->device != pdev->device))
9991 return -1;
9992
9993 physfns++;
9994 }
9995
9996 return physfns;
9997}
9998
9999/**
10000 * ixgbe_wol_supported - Check whether device supports WoL
10001 * @adapter: the adapter private structure
10002 * @device_id: the device ID
10003 * @subdev_id: the subsystem device ID
10004 *
10005 * This function is used by probe and ethtool to determine
10006 * which devices have WoL support
10007 *
10008 **/
10009bool ixgbe_wol_supported(struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter, u16 device_id,
10010 u16 subdevice_id)
10011{
10012 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
10013 u16 wol_cap = adapter->eeprom_cap & IXGBE_DEVICE_CAPS_WOL_MASK;
10014
10015 /* WOL not supported on 82598 */
10016 if (hw->mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
10017 return false;
10018
10019 /* check eeprom to see if WOL is enabled for X540 and newer */
10020 if (hw->mac.type >= ixgbe_mac_X540) {
10021 if ((wol_cap == IXGBE_DEVICE_CAPS_WOL_PORT0_1) ||
10022 ((wol_cap == IXGBE_DEVICE_CAPS_WOL_PORT0) &&
10023 (hw->bus.func == 0)))
10024 return true;
10025 }
10026
10027 /* WOL is determined based on device IDs for 82599 MACs */
10028 switch (device_id) {
10029 case IXGBE_DEV_ID_82599_SFP:
10030 /* Only these subdevices could supports WOL */
10031 switch (subdevice_id) {
10032 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_560FLR:
10033 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_LOM_SNAP6:
10034 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_SFP_WOL0:
10035 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_SFP_2OCP:
10036 /* only support first port */
10037 if (hw->bus.func != 0)
10038 break;
10039 /* fall through */
10040 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_SP_560FLR:
10041 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_SFP:
10042 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_RNDC:
10043 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_ECNA_DP:
10044 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_SFP_1OCP:
10045 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_SFP_LOM_OEM1:
10046 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_SFP_LOM_OEM2:
10047 return true;
10048 }
10049 break;
10050 case IXGBE_DEV_ID_82599EN_SFP:
10051 /* Only these subdevices support WOL */
10052 switch (subdevice_id) {
10053 case IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599EN_SFP_OCP1:
10054 return true;
10055 }
10056 break;
10057 case IXGBE_DEV_ID_82599_COMBO_BACKPLANE:
10058 /* All except this subdevice support WOL */
10059 if (subdevice_id != IXGBE_SUBDEV_ID_82599_KX4_KR_MEZZ)
10060 return true;
10061 break;
10062 case IXGBE_DEV_ID_82599_KX4:
10063 return true;
10064 default:
10065 break;
10066 }
10067
10068 return false;
10069}
10070
10071/**
10072 * ixgbe_probe - Device Initialization Routine
10073 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
10074 * @ent: entry in ixgbe_pci_tbl
10075 *
10076 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
10077 *
10078 * ixgbe_probe initializes an adapter identified by a pci_dev structure.
10079 * The OS initialization, configuring of the adapter private structure,
10080 * and a hardware reset occur.
10081 **/
10082static int ixgbe_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev, const struct pci_device_id *ent)
10083{
10084 struct net_device *netdev;
10085 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = NULL;
10086 struct ixgbe_hw *hw;
10087 const struct ixgbe_info *ii = ixgbe_info_tbl[ent->driver_data];
10088 int i, err, pci_using_dac, expected_gts;
10089 unsigned int indices = MAX_TX_QUEUES;
10090 u8 part_str[IXGBE_PBANUM_LENGTH];
10091 bool disable_dev = false;
10092#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
10093 u16 device_caps;
10094#endif
10095 u32 eec;
10096
10097 /* Catch broken hardware that put the wrong VF device ID in
10098 * the PCIe SR-IOV capability.
10099 */
10100 if (pdev->is_virtfn) {
10101 WARN(1, KERN_ERR "%s (%hx:%hx) should not be a VF!\n",
10102 pci_name(pdev), pdev->vendor, pdev->device);
10103 return -EINVAL;
10104 }
10105
10106 err = pci_enable_device_mem(pdev);
10107 if (err)
10108 return err;
10109
10110 if (!dma_set_mask_and_coherent(&pdev->dev, DMA_BIT_MASK(64))) {
10111 pci_using_dac = 1;
10112 } else {
10113 err = dma_set_mask_and_coherent(&pdev->dev, DMA_BIT_MASK(32));
10114 if (err) {
10115 dev_err(&pdev->dev,
10116 "No usable DMA configuration, aborting\n");
10117 goto err_dma;
10118 }
10119 pci_using_dac = 0;
10120 }
10121
10122 err = pci_request_mem_regions(pdev, ixgbe_driver_name);
10123 if (err) {
10124 dev_err(&pdev->dev,
10125 "pci_request_selected_regions failed 0x%x\n", err);
10126 goto err_pci_reg;
10127 }
10128
10129 pci_enable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
10130
10131 pci_set_master(pdev);
10132 pci_save_state(pdev);
10133
10134 if (ii->mac == ixgbe_mac_82598EB) {
10135#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
10136 /* 8 TC w/ 4 queues per TC */
10137 indices = 4 * MAX_TRAFFIC_CLASS;
10138#else
10139 indices = IXGBE_MAX_RSS_INDICES;
10140#endif
10141 }
10142
10143 netdev = alloc_etherdev_mq(sizeof(struct ixgbe_adapter), indices);
10144 if (!netdev) {
10145 err = -ENOMEM;
10146 goto err_alloc_etherdev;
10147 }
10148
10149 SET_NETDEV_DEV(netdev, &pdev->dev);
10150
10151 adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
10152
10153 adapter->netdev = netdev;
10154 adapter->pdev = pdev;
10155 hw = &adapter->hw;
10156 hw->back = adapter;
10157 adapter->msg_enable = netif_msg_init(debug, DEFAULT_MSG_ENABLE);
10158
10159 hw->hw_addr = ioremap(pci_resource_start(pdev, 0),
10160 pci_resource_len(pdev, 0));
10161 adapter->io_addr = hw->hw_addr;
10162 if (!hw->hw_addr) {
10163 err = -EIO;
10164 goto err_ioremap;
10165 }
10166
10167 netdev->netdev_ops = &ixgbe_netdev_ops;
10168 ixgbe_set_ethtool_ops(netdev);
10169 netdev->watchdog_timeo = 5 * HZ;
10170 strlcpy(netdev->name, pci_name(pdev), sizeof(netdev->name));
10171
10172 /* Setup hw api */
10173 hw->mac.ops = *ii->mac_ops;
10174 hw->mac.type = ii->mac;
10175 hw->mvals = ii->mvals;
10176 if (ii->link_ops)
10177 hw->link.ops = *ii->link_ops;
10178
10179 /* EEPROM */
10180 hw->eeprom.ops = *ii->eeprom_ops;
10181 eec = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_EEC(hw));
10182 if (ixgbe_removed(hw->hw_addr)) {
10183 err = -EIO;
10184 goto err_ioremap;
10185 }
10186 /* If EEPROM is valid (bit 8 = 1), use default otherwise use bit bang */
10187 if (!(eec & BIT(8)))
10188 hw->eeprom.ops.read = &ixgbe_read_eeprom_bit_bang_generic;
10189
10190 /* PHY */
10191 hw->phy.ops = *ii->phy_ops;
10192 hw->phy.sfp_type = ixgbe_sfp_type_unknown;
10193 /* ixgbe_identify_phy_generic will set prtad and mmds properly */
10194 hw->phy.mdio.prtad = MDIO_PRTAD_NONE;
10195 hw->phy.mdio.mmds = 0;
10196 hw->phy.mdio.mode_support = MDIO_SUPPORTS_C45 | MDIO_EMULATE_C22;
10197 hw->phy.mdio.dev = netdev;
10198 hw->phy.mdio.mdio_read = ixgbe_mdio_read;
10199 hw->phy.mdio.mdio_write = ixgbe_mdio_write;
10200
10201 /* setup the private structure */
10202 err = ixgbe_sw_init(adapter, ii);
10203 if (err)
10204 goto err_sw_init;
10205
10206 /* Make sure the SWFW semaphore is in a valid state */
10207 if (hw->mac.ops.init_swfw_sync)
10208 hw->mac.ops.init_swfw_sync(hw);
10209
10210 /* Make it possible the adapter to be woken up via WOL */
10211 switch (adapter->hw.mac.type) {
10212 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
10213 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
10214 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
10215 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
10216 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
10217 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_WUS, ~0);
10218 break;
10219 default:
10220 break;
10221 }
10222
10223 /*
10224 * If there is a fan on this device and it has failed log the
10225 * failure.
10226 */
10227 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FAN_FAIL_CAPABLE) {
10228 u32 esdp = IXGBE_READ_REG(hw, IXGBE_ESDP);
10229 if (esdp & IXGBE_ESDP_SDP1)
10230 e_crit(probe, "Fan has stopped, replace the adapter\n");
10231 }
10232
10233 if (allow_unsupported_sfp)
10234 hw->allow_unsupported_sfp = allow_unsupported_sfp;
10235
10236 /* reset_hw fills in the perm_addr as well */
10237 hw->phy.reset_if_overtemp = true;
10238 err = hw->mac.ops.reset_hw(hw);
10239 hw->phy.reset_if_overtemp = false;
10240 ixgbe_set_eee_capable(adapter);
10241 if (err == IXGBE_ERR_SFP_NOT_PRESENT) {
10242 err = 0;
10243 } else if (err == IXGBE_ERR_SFP_NOT_SUPPORTED) {
10244 e_dev_err("failed to load because an unsupported SFP+ or QSFP module type was detected.\n");
10245 e_dev_err("Reload the driver after installing a supported module.\n");
10246 goto err_sw_init;
10247 } else if (err) {
10248 e_dev_err("HW Init failed: %d\n", err);
10249 goto err_sw_init;
10250 }
10251
10252#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
10253 /* SR-IOV not supported on the 82598 */
10254 if (adapter->hw.mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB)
10255 goto skip_sriov;
10256 /* Mailbox */
10257 ixgbe_init_mbx_params_pf(hw);
10258 hw->mbx.ops = ii->mbx_ops;
10259 pci_sriov_set_totalvfs(pdev, IXGBE_MAX_VFS_DRV_LIMIT);
10260 ixgbe_enable_sriov(adapter, max_vfs);
10261skip_sriov:
10262
10263#endif
10264 netdev->features = NETIF_F_SG |
10265 NETIF_F_TSO |
10266 NETIF_F_TSO6 |
10267 NETIF_F_RXHASH |
10268 NETIF_F_RXCSUM |
10269 NETIF_F_HW_CSUM;
10270
10271#define IXGBE_GSO_PARTIAL_FEATURES (NETIF_F_GSO_GRE | \
10272 NETIF_F_GSO_GRE_CSUM | \
10273 NETIF_F_GSO_IPXIP4 | \
10274 NETIF_F_GSO_IPXIP6 | \
10275 NETIF_F_GSO_UDP_TUNNEL | \
10276 NETIF_F_GSO_UDP_TUNNEL_CSUM)
10277
10278 netdev->gso_partial_features = IXGBE_GSO_PARTIAL_FEATURES;
10279 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_GSO_PARTIAL |
10280 IXGBE_GSO_PARTIAL_FEATURES;
10281
10282 if (hw->mac.type >= ixgbe_mac_82599EB)
10283 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_SCTP_CRC;
10284
10285 /* copy netdev features into list of user selectable features */
10286 netdev->hw_features |= netdev->features |
10287 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER |
10288 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX |
10289 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_TX |
10290 NETIF_F_RXALL |
10291 NETIF_F_HW_L2FW_DOFFLOAD;
10292
10293 if (hw->mac.type >= ixgbe_mac_82599EB)
10294 netdev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_NTUPLE |
10295 NETIF_F_HW_TC;
10296
10297 if (pci_using_dac)
10298 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_HIGHDMA;
10299
10300 netdev->vlan_features |= netdev->features | NETIF_F_TSO_MANGLEID;
10301 netdev->hw_enc_features |= netdev->vlan_features;
10302 netdev->mpls_features |= NETIF_F_SG |
10303 NETIF_F_TSO |
10304 NETIF_F_TSO6 |
10305 NETIF_F_HW_CSUM;
10306 netdev->mpls_features |= IXGBE_GSO_PARTIAL_FEATURES;
10307
10308 /* set this bit last since it cannot be part of vlan_features */
10309 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER |
10310 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX |
10311 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_TX;
10312
10313 netdev->priv_flags |= IFF_UNICAST_FLT;
10314 netdev->priv_flags |= IFF_SUPP_NOFCS;
10315
10316 /* MTU range: 68 - 9710 */
10317 netdev->min_mtu = ETH_MIN_MTU;
10318 netdev->max_mtu = IXGBE_MAX_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE - (ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN);
10319
10320#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCB
10321 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE)
10322 netdev->dcbnl_ops = &ixgbe_dcbnl_ops;
10323#endif
10324
10325#ifdef IXGBE_FCOE
10326 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_FCOE_CAPABLE) {
10327 unsigned int fcoe_l;
10328
10329 if (hw->mac.ops.get_device_caps) {
10330 hw->mac.ops.get_device_caps(hw, &device_caps);
10331 if (device_caps & IXGBE_DEVICE_CAPS_FCOE_OFFLOADS)
10332 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_FCOE_CAPABLE;
10333 }
10334
10335
10336 fcoe_l = min_t(int, IXGBE_FCRETA_SIZE, num_online_cpus());
10337 adapter->ring_feature[RING_F_FCOE].limit = fcoe_l;
10338
10339 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_FSO |
10340 NETIF_F_FCOE_CRC;
10341
10342 netdev->vlan_features |= NETIF_F_FSO |
10343 NETIF_F_FCOE_CRC |
10344 NETIF_F_FCOE_MTU;
10345 }
10346#endif /* IXGBE_FCOE */
10347
10348 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_CAPABLE)
10349 netdev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_LRO;
10350 if (adapter->flags2 & IXGBE_FLAG2_RSC_ENABLED)
10351 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_LRO;
10352
10353 /* make sure the EEPROM is good */
10354 if (hw->eeprom.ops.validate_checksum(hw, NULL) < 0) {
10355 e_dev_err("The EEPROM Checksum Is Not Valid\n");
10356 err = -EIO;
10357 goto err_sw_init;
10358 }
10359
10360 eth_platform_get_mac_address(&adapter->pdev->dev,
10361 adapter->hw.mac.perm_addr);
10362
10363 memcpy(netdev->dev_addr, hw->mac.perm_addr, netdev->addr_len);
10364
10365 if (!is_valid_ether_addr(netdev->dev_addr)) {
10366 e_dev_err("invalid MAC address\n");
10367 err = -EIO;
10368 goto err_sw_init;
10369 }
10370
10371 /* Set hw->mac.addr to permanent MAC address */
10372 ether_addr_copy(hw->mac.addr, hw->mac.perm_addr);
10373 ixgbe_mac_set_default_filter(adapter);
10374
10375 setup_timer(&adapter->service_timer, &ixgbe_service_timer,
10376 (unsigned long) adapter);
10377
10378 if (ixgbe_removed(hw->hw_addr)) {
10379 err = -EIO;
10380 goto err_sw_init;
10381 }
10382 INIT_WORK(&adapter->service_task, ixgbe_service_task);
10383 set_bit(__IXGBE_SERVICE_INITED, &adapter->state);
10384 clear_bit(__IXGBE_SERVICE_SCHED, &adapter->state);
10385
10386 err = ixgbe_init_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
10387 if (err)
10388 goto err_sw_init;
10389
10390 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++)
10391 u64_stats_init(&adapter->rx_ring[i]->syncp);
10392 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++)
10393 u64_stats_init(&adapter->tx_ring[i]->syncp);
10394 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_xdp_queues; i++)
10395 u64_stats_init(&adapter->xdp_ring[i]->syncp);
10396
10397 /* WOL not supported for all devices */
10398 adapter->wol = 0;
10399 hw->eeprom.ops.read(hw, 0x2c, &adapter->eeprom_cap);
10400 hw->wol_enabled = ixgbe_wol_supported(adapter, pdev->device,
10401 pdev->subsystem_device);
10402 if (hw->wol_enabled)
10403 adapter->wol = IXGBE_WUFC_MAG;
10404
10405 device_set_wakeup_enable(&adapter->pdev->dev, adapter->wol);
10406
10407 /* save off EEPROM version number */
10408 hw->eeprom.ops.read(hw, 0x2e, &adapter->eeprom_verh);
10409 hw->eeprom.ops.read(hw, 0x2d, &adapter->eeprom_verl);
10410
10411 /* pick up the PCI bus settings for reporting later */
10412 if (ixgbe_pcie_from_parent(hw))
10413 ixgbe_get_parent_bus_info(adapter);
10414 else
10415 hw->mac.ops.get_bus_info(hw);
10416
10417 /* calculate the expected PCIe bandwidth required for optimal
10418 * performance. Note that some older parts will never have enough
10419 * bandwidth due to being older generation PCIe parts. We clamp these
10420 * parts to ensure no warning is displayed if it can't be fixed.
10421 */
10422 switch (hw->mac.type) {
10423 case ixgbe_mac_82598EB:
10424 expected_gts = min(ixgbe_enumerate_functions(adapter) * 10, 16);
10425 break;
10426 default:
10427 expected_gts = ixgbe_enumerate_functions(adapter) * 10;
10428 break;
10429 }
10430
10431 /* don't check link if we failed to enumerate functions */
10432 if (expected_gts > 0)
10433 ixgbe_check_minimum_link(adapter, expected_gts);
10434
10435 err = ixgbe_read_pba_string_generic(hw, part_str, sizeof(part_str));
10436 if (err)
10437 strlcpy(part_str, "Unknown", sizeof(part_str));
10438 if (ixgbe_is_sfp(hw) && hw->phy.sfp_type != ixgbe_sfp_type_not_present)
10439 e_dev_info("MAC: %d, PHY: %d, SFP+: %d, PBA No: %s\n",
10440 hw->mac.type, hw->phy.type, hw->phy.sfp_type,
10441 part_str);
10442 else
10443 e_dev_info("MAC: %d, PHY: %d, PBA No: %s\n",
10444 hw->mac.type, hw->phy.type, part_str);
10445
10446 e_dev_info("%pM\n", netdev->dev_addr);
10447
10448 /* reset the hardware with the new settings */
10449 err = hw->mac.ops.start_hw(hw);
10450 if (err == IXGBE_ERR_EEPROM_VERSION) {
10451 /* We are running on a pre-production device, log a warning */
10452 e_dev_warn("This device is a pre-production adapter/LOM. "
10453 "Please be aware there may be issues associated "
10454 "with your hardware. If you are experiencing "
10455 "problems please contact your Intel or hardware "
10456 "representative who provided you with this "
10457 "hardware.\n");
10458 }
10459 strcpy(netdev->name, "eth%d");
10460 pci_set_drvdata(pdev, adapter);
10461 err = register_netdev(netdev);
10462 if (err)
10463 goto err_register;
10464
10465
10466 /* power down the optics for 82599 SFP+ fiber */
10467 if (hw->mac.ops.disable_tx_laser)
10468 hw->mac.ops.disable_tx_laser(hw);
10469
10470 /* carrier off reporting is important to ethtool even BEFORE open */
10471 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
10472
10473#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA
10474 if (dca_add_requester(&pdev->dev) == 0) {
10475 adapter->flags |= IXGBE_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED;
10476 ixgbe_setup_dca(adapter);
10477 }
10478#endif
10479 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED) {
10480 e_info(probe, "IOV is enabled with %d VFs\n", adapter->num_vfs);
10481 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_vfs; i++)
10482 ixgbe_vf_configuration(pdev, (i | 0x10000000));
10483 }
10484
10485 /* firmware requires driver version to be 0xFFFFFFFF
10486 * since os does not support feature
10487 */
10488 if (hw->mac.ops.set_fw_drv_ver)
10489 hw->mac.ops.set_fw_drv_ver(hw, 0xFF, 0xFF, 0xFF, 0xFF,
10490 sizeof(ixgbe_driver_version) - 1,
10491 ixgbe_driver_version);
10492
10493 /* add san mac addr to netdev */
10494 ixgbe_add_sanmac_netdev(netdev);
10495
10496 e_dev_info("%s\n", ixgbe_default_device_descr);
10497
10498#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_HWMON
10499 if (ixgbe_sysfs_init(adapter))
10500 e_err(probe, "failed to allocate sysfs resources\n");
10501#endif /* CONFIG_IXGBE_HWMON */
10502
10503 ixgbe_dbg_adapter_init(adapter);
10504
10505 /* setup link for SFP devices with MNG FW, else wait for IXGBE_UP */
10506 if (ixgbe_mng_enabled(hw) && ixgbe_is_sfp(hw) && hw->mac.ops.setup_link)
10507 hw->mac.ops.setup_link(hw,
10508 IXGBE_LINK_SPEED_10GB_FULL | IXGBE_LINK_SPEED_1GB_FULL,
10509 true);
10510
10511 return 0;
10512
10513err_register:
10514 ixgbe_release_hw_control(adapter);
10515 ixgbe_clear_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
10516err_sw_init:
10517 ixgbe_disable_sriov(adapter);
10518 adapter->flags2 &= ~IXGBE_FLAG2_SEARCH_FOR_SFP;
10519 iounmap(adapter->io_addr);
10520 kfree(adapter->jump_tables[0]);
10521 kfree(adapter->mac_table);
10522 kfree(adapter->rss_key);
10523err_ioremap:
10524 disable_dev = !test_and_set_bit(__IXGBE_DISABLED, &adapter->state);
10525 free_netdev(netdev);
10526err_alloc_etherdev:
10527 pci_release_mem_regions(pdev);
10528err_pci_reg:
10529err_dma:
10530 if (!adapter || disable_dev)
10531 pci_disable_device(pdev);
10532 return err;
10533}
10534
10535/**
10536 * ixgbe_remove - Device Removal Routine
10537 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
10538 *
10539 * ixgbe_remove is called by the PCI subsystem to alert the driver
10540 * that it should release a PCI device. The could be caused by a
10541 * Hot-Plug event, or because the driver is going to be removed from
10542 * memory.
10543 **/
10544static void ixgbe_remove(struct pci_dev *pdev)
10545{
10546 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
10547 struct net_device *netdev;
10548 bool disable_dev;
10549 int i;
10550
10551 /* if !adapter then we already cleaned up in probe */
10552 if (!adapter)
10553 return;
10554
10555 netdev = adapter->netdev;
10556 ixgbe_dbg_adapter_exit(adapter);
10557
10558 set_bit(__IXGBE_REMOVING, &adapter->state);
10559 cancel_work_sync(&adapter->service_task);
10560
10561
10562#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA
10563 if (adapter->flags & IXGBE_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED) {
10564 adapter->flags &= ~IXGBE_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED;
10565 dca_remove_requester(&pdev->dev);
10566 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_DCA_CTRL,
10567 IXGBE_DCA_CTRL_DCA_DISABLE);
10568 }
10569
10570#endif
10571#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_HWMON
10572 ixgbe_sysfs_exit(adapter);
10573#endif /* CONFIG_IXGBE_HWMON */
10574
10575 /* remove the added san mac */
10576 ixgbe_del_sanmac_netdev(netdev);
10577
10578#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
10579 ixgbe_disable_sriov(adapter);
10580#endif
10581 if (netdev->reg_state == NETREG_REGISTERED)
10582 unregister_netdev(netdev);
10583
10584 ixgbe_clear_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
10585
10586 ixgbe_release_hw_control(adapter);
10587
10588#ifdef CONFIG_DCB
10589 kfree(adapter->ixgbe_ieee_pfc);
10590 kfree(adapter->ixgbe_ieee_ets);
10591
10592#endif
10593 iounmap(adapter->io_addr);
10594 pci_release_mem_regions(pdev);
10595
10596 e_dev_info("complete\n");
10597
10598 for (i = 0; i < IXGBE_MAX_LINK_HANDLE; i++) {
10599 if (adapter->jump_tables[i]) {
10600 kfree(adapter->jump_tables[i]->input);
10601 kfree(adapter->jump_tables[i]->mask);
10602 }
10603 kfree(adapter->jump_tables[i]);
10604 }
10605
10606 kfree(adapter->mac_table);
10607 kfree(adapter->rss_key);
10608 disable_dev = !test_and_set_bit(__IXGBE_DISABLED, &adapter->state);
10609 free_netdev(netdev);
10610
10611 pci_disable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
10612
10613 if (disable_dev)
10614 pci_disable_device(pdev);
10615}
10616
10617/**
10618 * ixgbe_io_error_detected - called when PCI error is detected
10619 * @pdev: Pointer to PCI device
10620 * @state: The current pci connection state
10621 *
10622 * This function is called after a PCI bus error affecting
10623 * this device has been detected.
10624 */
10625static pci_ers_result_t ixgbe_io_error_detected(struct pci_dev *pdev,
10626 pci_channel_state_t state)
10627{
10628 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
10629 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
10630
10631#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
10632 struct ixgbe_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
10633 struct pci_dev *bdev, *vfdev;
10634 u32 dw0, dw1, dw2, dw3;
10635 int vf, pos;
10636 u16 req_id, pf_func;
10637
10638 if (adapter->hw.mac.type == ixgbe_mac_82598EB ||
10639 adapter->num_vfs == 0)
10640 goto skip_bad_vf_detection;
10641
10642 bdev = pdev->bus->self;
10643 while (bdev && (pci_pcie_type(bdev) != PCI_EXP_TYPE_ROOT_PORT))
10644 bdev = bdev->bus->self;
10645
10646 if (!bdev)
10647 goto skip_bad_vf_detection;
10648
10649 pos = pci_find_ext_capability(bdev, PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_ERR);
10650 if (!pos)
10651 goto skip_bad_vf_detection;
10652
10653 dw0 = ixgbe_read_pci_cfg_dword(hw, pos + PCI_ERR_HEADER_LOG);
10654 dw1 = ixgbe_read_pci_cfg_dword(hw, pos + PCI_ERR_HEADER_LOG + 4);
10655 dw2 = ixgbe_read_pci_cfg_dword(hw, pos + PCI_ERR_HEADER_LOG + 8);
10656 dw3 = ixgbe_read_pci_cfg_dword(hw, pos + PCI_ERR_HEADER_LOG + 12);
10657 if (ixgbe_removed(hw->hw_addr))
10658 goto skip_bad_vf_detection;
10659
10660 req_id = dw1 >> 16;
10661 /* On the 82599 if bit 7 of the requestor ID is set then it's a VF */
10662 if (!(req_id & 0x0080))
10663 goto skip_bad_vf_detection;
10664
10665 pf_func = req_id & 0x01;
10666 if ((pf_func & 1) == (pdev->devfn & 1)) {
10667 unsigned int device_id;
10668
10669 vf = (req_id & 0x7F) >> 1;
10670 e_dev_err("VF %d has caused a PCIe error\n", vf);
10671 e_dev_err("TLP: dw0: %8.8x\tdw1: %8.8x\tdw2: "
10672 "%8.8x\tdw3: %8.8x\n",
10673 dw0, dw1, dw2, dw3);
10674 switch (adapter->hw.mac.type) {
10675 case ixgbe_mac_82599EB:
10676 device_id = IXGBE_82599_VF_DEVICE_ID;
10677 break;
10678 case ixgbe_mac_X540:
10679 device_id = IXGBE_X540_VF_DEVICE_ID;
10680 break;
10681 case ixgbe_mac_X550:
10682 device_id = IXGBE_DEV_ID_X550_VF;
10683 break;
10684 case ixgbe_mac_X550EM_x:
10685 device_id = IXGBE_DEV_ID_X550EM_X_VF;
10686 break;
10687 case ixgbe_mac_x550em_a:
10688 device_id = IXGBE_DEV_ID_X550EM_A_VF;
10689 break;
10690 default:
10691 device_id = 0;
10692 break;
10693 }
10694
10695 /* Find the pci device of the offending VF */
10696 vfdev = pci_get_device(PCI_VENDOR_ID_INTEL, device_id, NULL);
10697 while (vfdev) {
10698 if (vfdev->devfn == (req_id & 0xFF))
10699 break;
10700 vfdev = pci_get_device(PCI_VENDOR_ID_INTEL,
10701 device_id, vfdev);
10702 }
10703 /*
10704 * There's a slim chance the VF could have been hot plugged,
10705 * so if it is no longer present we don't need to issue the
10706 * VFLR. Just clean up the AER in that case.
10707 */
10708 if (vfdev) {
10709 pcie_flr(vfdev);
10710 /* Free device reference count */
10711 pci_dev_put(vfdev);
10712 }
10713
10714 pci_cleanup_aer_uncorrect_error_status(pdev);
10715 }
10716
10717 /*
10718 * Even though the error may have occurred on the other port
10719 * we still need to increment the vf error reference count for
10720 * both ports because the I/O resume function will be called
10721 * for both of them.
10722 */
10723 adapter->vferr_refcount++;
10724
10725 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_RECOVERED;
10726
10727skip_bad_vf_detection:
10728#endif /* CONFIG_PCI_IOV */
10729 if (!test_bit(__IXGBE_SERVICE_INITED, &adapter->state))
10730 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
10731
10732 rtnl_lock();
10733 netif_device_detach(netdev);
10734
10735 if (state == pci_channel_io_perm_failure) {
10736 rtnl_unlock();
10737 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
10738 }
10739
10740 if (netif_running(netdev))
10741 ixgbe_close_suspend(adapter);
10742
10743 if (!test_and_set_bit(__IXGBE_DISABLED, &adapter->state))
10744 pci_disable_device(pdev);
10745 rtnl_unlock();
10746
10747 /* Request a slot reset. */
10748 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_NEED_RESET;
10749}
10750
10751/**
10752 * ixgbe_io_slot_reset - called after the pci bus has been reset.
10753 * @pdev: Pointer to PCI device
10754 *
10755 * Restart the card from scratch, as if from a cold-boot.
10756 */
10757static pci_ers_result_t ixgbe_io_slot_reset(struct pci_dev *pdev)
10758{
10759 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
10760 pci_ers_result_t result;
10761 int err;
10762
10763 if (pci_enable_device_mem(pdev)) {
10764 e_err(probe, "Cannot re-enable PCI device after reset.\n");
10765 result = PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
10766 } else {
10767 smp_mb__before_atomic();
10768 clear_bit(__IXGBE_DISABLED, &adapter->state);
10769 adapter->hw.hw_addr = adapter->io_addr;
10770 pci_set_master(pdev);
10771 pci_restore_state(pdev);
10772 pci_save_state(pdev);
10773
10774 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, false);
10775
10776 ixgbe_reset(adapter);
10777 IXGBE_WRITE_REG(&adapter->hw, IXGBE_WUS, ~0);
10778 result = PCI_ERS_RESULT_RECOVERED;
10779 }
10780
10781 err = pci_cleanup_aer_uncorrect_error_status(pdev);
10782 if (err) {
10783 e_dev_err("pci_cleanup_aer_uncorrect_error_status "
10784 "failed 0x%0x\n", err);
10785 /* non-fatal, continue */
10786 }
10787
10788 return result;
10789}
10790
10791/**
10792 * ixgbe_io_resume - called when traffic can start flowing again.
10793 * @pdev: Pointer to PCI device
10794 *
10795 * This callback is called when the error recovery driver tells us that
10796 * its OK to resume normal operation.
10797 */
10798static void ixgbe_io_resume(struct pci_dev *pdev)
10799{
10800 struct ixgbe_adapter *adapter = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
10801 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
10802
10803#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
10804 if (adapter->vferr_refcount) {
10805 e_info(drv, "Resuming after VF err\n");
10806 adapter->vferr_refcount--;
10807 return;
10808 }
10809
10810#endif
10811 rtnl_lock();
10812 if (netif_running(netdev))
10813 ixgbe_open(netdev);
10814
10815 netif_device_attach(netdev);
10816 rtnl_unlock();
10817}
10818
10819static const struct pci_error_handlers ixgbe_err_handler = {
10820 .error_detected = ixgbe_io_error_detected,
10821 .slot_reset = ixgbe_io_slot_reset,
10822 .resume = ixgbe_io_resume,
10823};
10824
10825static struct pci_driver ixgbe_driver = {
10826 .name = ixgbe_driver_name,
10827 .id_table = ixgbe_pci_tbl,
10828 .probe = ixgbe_probe,
10829 .remove = ixgbe_remove,
10830#ifdef CONFIG_PM
10831 .suspend = ixgbe_suspend,
10832 .resume = ixgbe_resume,
10833#endif
10834 .shutdown = ixgbe_shutdown,
10835 .sriov_configure = ixgbe_pci_sriov_configure,
10836 .err_handler = &ixgbe_err_handler
10837};
10838
10839/**
10840 * ixgbe_init_module - Driver Registration Routine
10841 *
10842 * ixgbe_init_module is the first routine called when the driver is
10843 * loaded. All it does is register with the PCI subsystem.
10844 **/
10845static int __init ixgbe_init_module(void)
10846{
10847 int ret;
10848 pr_info("%s - version %s\n", ixgbe_driver_string, ixgbe_driver_version);
10849 pr_info("%s\n", ixgbe_copyright);
10850
10851 ixgbe_wq = create_singlethread_workqueue(ixgbe_driver_name);
10852 if (!ixgbe_wq) {
10853 pr_err("%s: Failed to create workqueue\n", ixgbe_driver_name);
10854 return -ENOMEM;
10855 }
10856
10857 ixgbe_dbg_init();
10858
10859 ret = pci_register_driver(&ixgbe_driver);
10860 if (ret) {
10861 destroy_workqueue(ixgbe_wq);
10862 ixgbe_dbg_exit();
10863 return ret;
10864 }
10865
10866#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA
10867 dca_register_notify(&dca_notifier);
10868#endif
10869
10870 return 0;
10871}
10872
10873module_init(ixgbe_init_module);
10874
10875/**
10876 * ixgbe_exit_module - Driver Exit Cleanup Routine
10877 *
10878 * ixgbe_exit_module is called just before the driver is removed
10879 * from memory.
10880 **/
10881static void __exit ixgbe_exit_module(void)
10882{
10883#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA
10884 dca_unregister_notify(&dca_notifier);
10885#endif
10886 pci_unregister_driver(&ixgbe_driver);
10887
10888 ixgbe_dbg_exit();
10889 if (ixgbe_wq) {
10890 destroy_workqueue(ixgbe_wq);
10891 ixgbe_wq = NULL;
10892 }
10893}
10894
10895#ifdef CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA
10896static int ixgbe_notify_dca(struct notifier_block *nb, unsigned long event,
10897 void *p)
10898{
10899 int ret_val;
10900
10901 ret_val = driver_for_each_device(&ixgbe_driver.driver, NULL, &event,
10902 __ixgbe_notify_dca);
10903
10904 return ret_val ? NOTIFY_BAD : NOTIFY_DONE;
10905}
10906
10907#endif /* CONFIG_IXGBE_DCA */
10908
10909module_exit(ixgbe_exit_module);
